Glydar.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon glides using the single wing on its back that also acts as a warning sign. Its colors tell predators to stay away although it is not poisonous.

Airaknid.Pokedex Entry: Using its eerie wing, this Pokemon spends its time gliding throughout the night, devouring other bugs. It is able to shoot webs from its front and back ends.

Camopper.Pokedex Entry: They use their strong back legs to leap at high altitudes. They use camouflage to blend in with the grass and avoid predators.

Bloatea.Pokedex Entry: It loves to drink blood. It latches onto unsuspected people and Pokemon and drain them of their bodily fluids.

Damsegg.Pokedex Entry: Its body stays encased in a clear shell as it awaits evolution. It is still capable of attacking despite being in its shell.

Scarabea.Pokedex Entry: The coin on its back is extremely valuable, as it is said to give its owner strange and otherworldly power. It was highly worshiped by Egyptians.

Bananug.Pokedex Entry: It is covered it a slimy film that lets attacks slide off of it. It disguises itself with rotten banana peels in order to keep its hidden from predators.

Slugana.Pokedex Entry: When it is asleep, it goes into its banana peel and cloaks itself, making it look like the normal fruit. They sometimes hang from trees until their peels are ripened and they fall off.

Shimie.Pokedex Entry: They remain motionless in their soft, transparent egg shells as they await evolution. The single antenna on its head allows it to read its surroundings.

Silarva.Pokedex Entry: It wraps itself with silk it creates in its body. Many fashion designers use Silarva to make silk for them.

Chrysilk.Pokedex Entry: They hang from trees using their silk as they await evolution. The silk it creates entangles anyone who steps through it.

Feemosk.Pokedex Entry: They usually live around areas with moist land around it. They use their feelers to sift through mud and dirt.

Slumbug.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are usually found in the beds of abandoned houses. Always asleep, they protect themselves with a combination of Counter and Mirror Coat.

Concumba.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are always sleeping as they hang from trees and ceilings in homes. Despite being asleep, they still attack, as they use Counter and Mirror Coat to protect themselves from predators.

Pilarisk.Pokedex Entry: They reside inside of homes and abandoned buildings, sleeping against the walls. It is able to support the weight of even a very large human and will still not wake from its slumber.

Hearwig.Pokedex Entry: When these Pokemon bite, they cause people to hear at frequencies that they normally would not. They love eating earwax and will sometimes crawl to their trainers' ears to eat it.

Gelatyne.Pokedex Entry: Anything that these Pokemon eat can be seen in their bodies. Their plump, squishy bodies are actually impenetrable.

Bugger.Pokedex Entry: They are able to both taste and smell with their antennae, giving them more power to those senses. There are little hooks all over their fur, allowing them to stick to any surface.

Rollo.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon never stop moving from place to place unless they are completely exhausted or hungry. When in cities and towns, these Pokemon are usually seen alongside cars in the street.

Gaudago.Pokedex Entry: It has to roll everywhere to get around, often rolling into different things while dizzy. They have the power to go straight through concrete blocks.

Rydalon.Pokedex Entry: They allow people to ride on their backs in order to get from place to place. They can sense the emotions of those who grab their antennae while riding it.

Skinnib.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon have a natural desire to eat flesh. They mainly hunt for Scrawnude in order to devour them.

Atlarva.Pokedex Entry: They gorge on fallen fruits of certain trees that they deem worthy. Their brains are like maps, so they can reach any new destination without ever getting lost.

Atticurl.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon act as compasses for travelers who are unsure of where to go. They usually hang from tree branches using their curls, their bodies and head spinning in different directions.

Mapillar.Pokedex Entry: To slow people down, they release a syrupy substance from their backs and mouths. The syrup that they produce is very sweet, making them sought out by manufacturers.

Maplunge.Pokedex Entry: They spin around in one spot, spraying syrup everywhere in hopes of trapping people. Their syrup is considered a rare delicacy, as it tastes how you want it to taste.

Melobee.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon have a very distinct odor and are often collected to help make perfume. Their bodies' insides resemble actual watermelon, but because they are small, they are sometimes ignored by humans.

Melonide.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon spit out seeds that grow into watermelons and sometimes Melobee. Their scent was said to have been used to calm enemies during a large war.

Clawshank.Pokedex Entry: For some odd reason, Drownage flee at the sight of them. They fashion their hard shells from sediment and abandoned scales.

Anoma.Pokedex Entry: Anoma are extremely curious, crawling around an entire area in order to inspect its surroundings. Being a relatively weak Pokemon, it loves living alongside humans, avoiding wild battles.

Lamsil.Pokedex Entry: After evolving from its shell, its body had more room to develop fully. Its feathery tail acts as a sensor, alerting it if danger is near.

Selefly.Pokedex Entry: It flies silently through forests and plains. Its colorful body and wings are said to hold a mystery.

Wormound.Pokedex Entry: It burrows underground in order to shield itself from harsh sunlight. Its lower body is encased in soil but it is still able to move above ground by hopping on its single white foot.

Drillurm.Pokedex Entry: Their hard, durable bodies are covered in a metal alloy that can deflect any attack that doesn't effect it. They drill tunnels for hours on end to entertain themselves and make their own homes.

Beatroph.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon carry treasures inside of their bodies that are extremely valuable. The coins on its body are able to be launched like bullets.

Grubrr.Pokedex Entry: Its coat-like body protects it from the cold weather. To sleep, it creates a small icy dome for protection.

Cryoon.Pokedex Entry: It hangs in icy caves and mountains like an icicle as it awaits evolution, and once that time is near, it falls. The inside of its body is very cold and rugged.

Himalayoth.Pokedex Entry: By flapping its icy wings, it can create a snowstorm in a matter of seconds. They are said to be the reincarnations of ancient ice gods who died while trying to save their people.

Hissano.Pokedex Entry: Hissano use their rattles at the end of their tails to communicate with each other. They mainly feast on leaves, but love to eat rodents on occasion.

Disgoon.Pokedex Entry: This peculiar Pokemon's appearance has puzzled scientists for centuries. It hangs from trees and closes its actual eyes, which are on its bottom half, making it appear as a doll as it awaits evolution.

Hebirash.Pokedex Entry: It uses its collar as wings to fly around. When not in flight, it folds its wings and lies in bushes to avoid being bothered.

Mantor.Pokedex Entry: It hides in gardens, disguised as a plant. Its tail gives off spores that can create more plants.

Orchin.Pokedex Entry: They stand still in large flower patches, blending in so that they can stay hidden. They can make their leafy claws sharp enough to slash though tempered steel.

Insecrest.Pokedex Entry: It stands on its tail whenever a full moon appears. They are known to get signals from the moon whenever their green eyes glow.

Crescoon.Pokedex Entry: It clings to tree branches and absorbs moonlight through its horns. Its little legs don't allow it to walk correctly.

Lunoth.Pokedex Entry: Its moon-shaped wings absorb moonlight in order to give it its power. It only appears on nights of crescent moons.

Odoripe.Pokedex Entry: Accidentally stepping on this Pokemon triggers a special gland inside its body to spread a terrible odor to the surrounding area. It hides under its covering in order to avoid predators.

Ripomb.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is one to be reckoned with when its antenna is pulled. When threatened, it releases gases inside its body that causes its shell to expand and eventually explode, releasing the noxious gas.

Stenchar.Pokedex Entry: Stenchar's tail is able to spray a repugnant odor that can curl noses from miles away. The button on its chest releases an odor from its head that acts as a knockout gas.

Sawee.Pokedex Entry: It gives the impression of having two heads when it is on all four of its legs. They poke and stab fruits, injecting them with poison as they eat it.

Sharpod.Pokedex Entry: Their claws release a potent toxin that can cause paralysis. They can rotate their claws in opposite directions like propeller blades.

Knifly.Pokedex Entry: They release a deadly poison that can kill in one minute. They fly in silence and strike when they feel threatened.

Assasect.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon have the agility and grace of a silent assassin. It never makes a sound when battling, making it able to defeat opponents quickly.

Bomini.Pokedex Entry: It protects itself with an unused bomb shell. Because it resembles a toy, it is often taken and tossed around by children.

Lepismite.Pokedex Entry: They are technically eyeless, but their brains are so large that it gives the appearance of an eye. They bite and crawl around aimlessly, attempting to make their way around vast areas.

Lepasarch.Pokedex Entry: They have a extremely high knowledge of its past life as well as the life of others. They have the power to resurrect dead people and Pokemon by adjusting their antennae.

Weavinid.Pokedex Entry: They weave marvelous webs that are said to keep peaceful dreams at bay. They trap unwanted dreams and nightmares in its web and devour them with their red fangs.

Drearch.Pokedex Entry: They devour bad dreams and create webs that give off powerful, calming energy. Because of their ability to devour bad dreams, some people like having Drearch stand by their beds.

Thorunt.Pokedex Entry: They are extremely nervous Pokemon that shudder and shake whenever they move. They generate electricity thanks to special organs in their antennae.

Shocoon.Pokedex Entry: They create long chains of electricity and throw them towards opponents. The two heads communicate through electrical pulses.

Electrifly.Pokedex Entry: They absorb sunlight through their wings to help them generate electricity. Touching their abdomens result in high voltage shocks.

Abilifly.Pokedex Entry: They are often used to treat people with mental disorders by sprinkling powders from their wings. Abilifly are usually sentimental and will remember everyone that they have healed.

Zafirlatus.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are often seen helping doctors and nurses with patients who are having trouble breathing. Using the sack on its back, it sprays a powder that can heal chest pains.

Knowlor.Pokedex Entry: When resting, their wings are sometimes mistaken for real books. These Pokemon's brains are very advanced, as they know almost everything, and are able to share their knowledge via telepathy.

Escargum.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are usually found slowly slinking down trees and across grass. Their bodies are made of a sticky substance that is similar to gum.

Gumnail.Pokedex Entry: The females carry gumball shaped eggs in their 'shells' in order to get them to safety. They sometimes end up getting stuck on hard surfaces because of their bodies' stickiness.

Bomorilk.Pokedex Entry: They are used by fashion designers to provide silk. In battle, they are able to tie up opponents in their silk, giving them free hits while their opponents are immobilized.

Frootot.Pokedex Entry: They find fallen apples and make them their homes by softly chewing holes inside of them. If their apples are damaged, they will quickly attempt to find new ones.

Grupple.Pokedex Entry: Their 7 foot tall bodies can intimidate even the toughest fire-types. Its fruit can be used to block hard attacks.

Pinchest.Pokedex Entry: Their tails are able to do mystical activities. They can jab their claws quickly and with lots of accuracy.

Mosquench.Pokedex Entry: As it takes blood away, it actually fills it with toxins and disease before re-administering it. They fly around and silently land on the backs of other Pokemon in order to drain them of their blood.

Gruberal.Pokedex Entry: It is thought to be one of the smartest Pokemon in existence, though the claim is heavily disputed. They are known to only eat spicy berries.

Spitder.Pokedex Entry: Spitder reside in caves and in some houses, defending themselves by spitting venom. They move fairly quick, making it hard to catch them.

Drearwig.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can cause temporary to permanent deafness if one is bitten by one. They are very sneaky and move without making a sound, making it unknown if one is near you.

Larvacius.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are able to induce a state of intoxication just by belching a bubble. They are extremely foolish and silly Pokemon who take pleasure in banging their heads against trees.

Munchela.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's soft and colorful wings can mesmerize those who see them. They love to eat, and it is said that anything that they eat can add colors to their wings.

Gaspiro.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies look soft, but they are actually very rough. Their shells are able to withstand over 400 lbs of pressure.

Spirodon.Pokedex Entry: Its body is surrounded by a scaly 'skirt' that can repel attacks. Its shell can withstand multiple explosions.

Dermeat.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon will go as far as to eat their trainer's skin to ease their hunger. Scrawnude and Nuderma are its main prey.

Maluspic.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon help trees grow amazing tasting fruit by biting into their trunks. They dance around fallen fruits.

Tonpella.Pokedex Entry: When in flight, their wings rotate quickly, producing an irritating buzzing sound. They travel in groups of ten or more.

Geogratt.Pokedex Entry: Their wings have a special scale that tracks their location, appearing as a red dot. These Pokemon unknowingly help lost trainers, as their wings help them locate where they are.

Spidorb.Pokedex Entry: Their sticky threads are full of energy that they form into large balls. Their threads have the ability to slowly erase the memories of those caught in them.

Pumpler.Pokedex Entry: By lifting and lowering its tail, it is able to produce an ample amount of water. They spray water in a sprinkler-like fashion.

Geridouse.Pokedex Entry: They skate across water at high speeds in different directions to create temporary patterns on the surface. They spray water from the tips of their arms.

Glowurm.Pokedex Entry: The bulbs on these Pokemon's backs are actually organs that emit bright light when they are startled. They feed on different berries, which can change the color of the light they emit.

Lampeet.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can communicate to each other with the flickering of their tails. A group of twenty has the ability to light an entire football stadium.

Nectini.Pokedex Entry: These small Pokemon travel in groups of thirty, going from flower to flower, collecting pollen into their bodies. They are very fond of humans and often fly around their heads, tickling them with their curl.

Florallen.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon spread pollen that help flowers bloom instantly. They often pick flowers that they have helped bloom and give them to humans that they like.

Fluffly.Pokedex Entry: Their fluffy fur never stops growing, so these Pokemon often have to rub themselves against the trunks of trees to shorten the amount. Their fur is extremely warm and often infused with other materials to create coats and jackets.

Prosuture.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are known to help injured travelers by closing their wounds with their pincers. They dig elaborate tunnel systems to carry food to and from their nests.

Cybug.Pokedex Entry: Scientists suspect that this Pokemon has connections to the future because of the data that they receive after it bites a piece of modern technology. They make technology more advanced by eating cables connected to them.

Chiprane.Pokedex Entry: They drain power from technology and travel into them, giving off numerous viruses. Scientists despise this Pokemon, as it is able to travel into the future using its powerful wings and take their prized information with them.

Herculift.Pokedex Entry: Using their heads alone, these Pokemon are able to lift things more than 100 times their own size. The amount of courage that they have is unmatched, as they will battle even if there is a type-advantage.

Mapillon.Pokedex Entry: When flapping their wings, some of their tasty maple scales flake off. They are often used as toppings for desserts. They usually eat small leaves from the tops of trees.

Tungot.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon always aim for the mouths of opponents, as they are able to drain them of all of their energy through the tongue. They only feed by latching onto a tongue, which is unwanted.

Floofer.Pokedex Entry: The soft hair covering its body is very poisonous, so one must approach it with caution. There have been stories of people, specifically bald males, waking up with Floofer on their heads.

Crystalis.Pokedex Entry: The transparent crystals embedded in its body are very poisonous, but also extremely valuable. The hair surrounding it protects it from severe damage as it waits to evolve.

Dalcerega.Pokedex Entry: Its wings and body produce valuable gems that fall easily in cold climates. Dalcerega were owned by royal families and treated like kings and queens due to their ability to create priceless jewels in their bodies.

Plateross.Pokedex Entry: The plates covering its body are as hard as diamonds. Plateross have a diet consisting mainly of tree bark, so if you see a fallen tree with majority of its bark removed, it is a sign that one or more live nearby.

Tembake.Pokedex Entry: Their craggy skin is a result of their diet of stone and gravel. Their backs erupt with lava and emit small flames when they are startled.

Agegio.Pokedex Entry: They cover stalks in a flaky, flammable substance that keeps them intact before using them in battle. Wielding two large stalks, they set them on fire before using them in combat.

Raween.Pokedex Entry: They swim in groups of up to twenty in order to swarm their enemies. The organ on their backs allow them to absorb water into their bodies, allowing them to survive on land for extended periods of time.

Sushamaki.Pokedex Entry: Their fluffy bodies allow them to absorb enough water for them to live on land for a month. They often secrete a sticky fluid that causes minerals to latch onto their bodies.

Agrubt.Pokedex Entry: After evolving from Anoma, Agrubt tend to go on a rampage, not used to the new power that they now possess. It takes a highly patient and skilled trainer to get an Agrubt under control after it has evolved.

Miniscale.Pokedex Entry: They are regarded as both the smallest and most useless Pokemon, battle-wise. Miniscale mainly eat sand and dirt and can reside in any body of water, acting as food for much larger Pokemon.

Stiltream.Pokedex Entry: Groups of them inhabit ponds and lakes and skate across the surface. They're able to reach speeds of over 40 mph while on water, but they're unusually slow on land.

Skiisect.Pokedex Entry: Thousands of them are able to inhabit a lake at one time. They use their long legs to ski across water, and sometimes snow, at high speeds.

Hemoglee.Pokedex Entry: Hemoglee hides in water, waiting for prey to come close it. Once close, it latches onto its host, draining them of their blood and bodily fluids.

Suclot.Pokedex Entry: Suclot never stops drinking blood until all three of their stomachs and its meter-like organ on the side of its body is full. It swims quickly, using its spikes to drain blood from its victim.

Symbia.Pokedex Entry: It is commonly found in the mouths of MOLLUSYM, as they protect their pearls. They eat sand and sediment at the bottom of the sea.

Tonex.Pokedex Entry: It gives off a melodious sound when happy. Its voice is said to be the most beautiful out of all Pokemon in the Qiloh Region.

Xylotone.Pokedex Entry: Its "tail" is actually its intestines, which it uses to let out different tones for its melodious sounds. It eats kelp and plankton in order to keep its throat moist.

Magga.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon love the taste of flesh and enjoy helping humans get rid of dead or infected tissue. They are used by doctors and nurses to clean out gashes and cuts in order to keep patients from getting infections.

Jingrub.Pokedex Entry: The orbs on its back contain tiny seeds that can make trees grow faster. It is thought that these Pokemon produced special orbs on its back and the orbs were turned into the ornaments that we use today.

Hollurm.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are taken from their undersea homes in order to harvest the trees that grow from their backs. Their leaves are very colorful and can change color whenever they want.

Kashigan.Pokedex Entry: Their long legs allow them to climb buildings in a minimum of 10 seconds. Their claws are small, but are still strong enough to snap steel.

Buterphan.Pokedex Entry: Said to be the spirits of dead butterflies, these Pokemon float around aimlessly. They hardly ever smile, despite the circumstances.

Icharp.Pokedex Entry: Using their tails, they can create a wall of ice to defend its territory. Their claws allow them to climb up mountains with ease.

Froscorp.Pokedex Entry: Their tails can fire cold spears of ice to protect themselves. They make ice walls to protect themselves.

Scorizzard.Pokedex Entry: They are able to create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air with their tails. Their claws can pierce glaciers.

Larphan.Pokedex Entry: They seem to always be sad or look like they are sad. They do not seem to do much of anything but float as they await evolution.

Bombug.Pokedex Entry: When threatened, they release flames from the spike on their backsides. Their insides are completely made of lava.

Flambeet.Pokedex Entry: Anything that they eat gets turned into energy for their flames. They blast 3,000 degree flamethrowers from their backsides.

Nymphlow.Pokedex Entry: They lay at the bottom of ponds and lakes, eating the grime and dirt at the bottom. They communicate with each other by clicking their tails.

Odonyxpa.Pokedex Entry: From behind, it looks like it has a second head, deterring would-be predators. They are often seen carrying Nymphlow to different ponds as they prepare to evolve.

Arachnom.Pokedex Entry: They travel on land using their arms as opposed to their feet. They are able to spit out webs from their mouths and trap prey with ease.

Atelimb.Pokedex Entry: Using their four large arms, they bash and destroy anything in their path. Their red eyes can strike fear into their prey.

Imper.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies give the illusion of them being crawling heads. The extra eyes on their bodies see through evasion attempts such as SmokeScreen.

Araknimp.Pokedex Entry: Their backsides can cause opponents to see them as a completely different Pokemon. They are able to see through illusions and tricks and head for their opponents immediately while in battle.

Transpram.Pokedex Entry: They find deceased insect corpses and use them as a suit to survive underwater. They control the suit's limbs professionally, being able to initiate numerous attacks in a small amount of time.

Carmolash.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are often found deep in abandoned caves, strengthening themselves by whipping each other. They slink on the ceilings of caves and fire spikes from their shell towards the targets below.

Hardia.Pokedex Entry: Evidence of its existence can be traced back over 200 thousand years, making it known as one of the oldest Pokemon in existence. They scurried along the ocean floor, sucking up sediment and zooplankton for food.

Lobstar.Pokedex Entry: Using their antennae, they are able to sense incoming attacks and move out of the way quickly. Their spiny scales offer them a lot of protection from predators.

Yelpex.Pokedex Entry: Their off-putting color scheme and appearance frightens smaller Pokemon, keeping them from making other friends. They create dens in the ground using their six legs and spray webs to seal the entrances off.

Fenrarch.Pokedex Entry: They are relentless when on the prowl for prey, setting up intricate web systems and pit traps to catch their prey. If you ever find yourself lost in a barren area and you find red webs along the ground, you are in a Fenrarch's territory; it is advised that you hide immediately before it is too late.

Mimadge.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon defend themselves by transforming into other objects, people, and Pokemon. They're extremely tricky and difficult to identify if you are seeking one.

Badgeange.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are known for their unique ability to change their shape at will. They will change into different Pokemon and humans and lie to unsuspecting victims, usually leading to the victim's bodily harm.

Shreverine.Pokedex Entry: Groups of them catch and devour prey while still alive, thriving off of their suffering. If angered these Pokemon attack with their sharp teeth and claws.

Wolvered.Pokedex Entry: If you get it angry, it will lunge at you and start slashing. When it starts attacking, it will not stop until you are dead.

Weashar.Pokedex Entry: It extends the sickles on its wrists in order to defend itself. Each one has scars that act as a sign of respect for others.

Bladinski.Pokedex Entry: It extends its 5 foot blades from its wrists to intimidate enemies before slashing them. It trains itself by slashing at hard objects, such as stones, and trying different techniques.

Huntear.Pokedex Entry: They are known to have the highest accuracy of all Pokemon because of their amazing hunting techniques. They chase down prey until they are exhausted and once caught, then devour it while still alive.

Lunaporin.Pokedex Entry: A legend says that, after defeating Taikin, it kept the sun from rising for a month, resulting in the deaths of millions. The colorful lights adorning its body flash when it is angered.

Evyl.Pokedex Entry: It blends in with the shadows so nobody knows if it follows them at night. Their tail is so dangerous that it can rip out someone's heart out with one stab.

Vylent.Pokedex Entry: It lures lost travelers into the woods with its cry, which it is able to make sound like a child. According to old tales, those who have encountered it are said to be sent to an eternal abyss of pain and agony.

Kalique.Pokedex Entry: They feign innocence to get on the good side of people, only to steal from them when left alone. They are said to lay a curse on anyone who pets its tail.

Jakunn.Pokedex Entry: They are extremely sneaky and devious Pokemon who are known to be vicious and hostile thieves and intruders. They hide stolen items in their fur.

Dibolika.Pokedex Entry: They use their pants-like fur to hide everything that they steal. Their glare can force anyone who tries to stop it into submission.

Daiuno.Pokedex Entry: It is difficult to find, capture, train, and please this Pokemon. It is said to have taken a successful trainer 3 years to completely get their DAIUNO to appreciate and like them.

Daudegoch.Pokedex Entry: No matter what you do for them, these Pokemon are always unsatisfied. Sometimes, they disappear and expect their trainers to come after them and tend to their wants.

Triragoch.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are very greedy when it comes to their power and will only use their full strength when they wants. If their trainer does not pay attention to them or does what they want, they will not hesitate to attack other them.

Seborgo.Pokedex Entry: It slowly moves around as it tries to strengthen itself for evolution. Its shell protects it from most attacks.

Boragon.Pokedex Entry: Its antennae help it locate faraway or invisible opponents. It is strong enough to throw a mountain.

Ascomini.Pokedex Entry: They travel in groups and charge into cities, taking whatever they want. They swing their tails to attack.

Scandrake.Pokedex Entry: Their tails can slice through the toughest of metals. They steal from cities in large groups in order to be protected.

Nogard.Pokedex Entry: They train each other in caves and mountain ranges. Their eyes are rather sensitive to bright lights, so they are mostly seen during sunsets or at night.

Strago.Pokedex Entry: They reside in caves far from civilization and try to come up with their own strategies to win battles against one another. They despise bright lights, so they only stay in caves that have no way of receiving light.

Shorave.Pokedex Entry: Their hunger is almost never satisfied, so they will look around wildly for items to eat, whether they're edible or inedible. They sometimes stay in caves, but for an odd reason, you may see them living on the tops of buildings.

Krashank.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon will eat whatever they can in order to stay energized. They will not hesitate to resort to their trainers for food, but there has never been an account of it happening.

Richreau.Pokedex Entry: Richreau are known to be treasure hoarders and will take anything of value to keep for itself. They are highly defensive about the treasure that they keep and will even go as far as to devour it in order to keep it from others.

Volanor.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon act as guardians over buildings and sacred areas. It is said that there is a secret area in the world where these Pokemon gather in peace.

Slicoup.Pokedex Entry: Slicoup's two heads never argue and are always very calm, regardless of the situation they are placed in. If one of its heads become enraged, the other head always tries its hardest to calm them down.

Amphlight.Pokedex Entry: Their wings don't allow flight, so their bodies enable them to levitate subconsciously. They take pleasure in destroying the homes of smaller Pokemon.

Phiteragon.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon roam the skies, destroying everything in its path. It has a sadistic personality and will always watch its prey suffer before devouring it.

Omnomon.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon enjoy biting their own tails because the sweet tasting nectar in the end of it strengthens their Psychic-type moves. They spend hours on end playfully chasing and gnawing on their tails.

Nomogon.Pokedex Entry: By gnawing on its long tail, it increases its mental power. It can use its tail as a shield from dangerous attacks and it will not have any effect.

Munchanon.Pokedex Entry: It is able to clamp down on its tail and continuously gnaw on it while it is battling. The nectar at the tail is far more concentrated, making its Psychic-types be at their highest level of intensity.

Kibbelgo.Pokedex Entry: They are extremely frightened of humans in the wild, but once captured, it bonds instantly. They never use their wings because they are scared of heights and as a result their wings are stiff.

Drigano.Pokedex Entry: When KIBBELGO evolves, it gets over its fears and gains confidence, but it also gains a cold personality. This Pokemon doesn't care about the pain it causes or the condition its trainer is in; because of this, many trainers refuse to evolve KIBBELGO, causing a depletion in the species.

Pityka.Pokedex Entry: They have been known to attack anyone and anything that invades their territory. They mark their territories by spraying a fruity liquid from their mouths.

Fruitang.Pokedex Entry: They sleep with their spikes out as a defense against possible attacks. Its piercing glare paralyzes smaller insects, which it then feasts upon.

Thoragon.Pokedex Entry: They waste no time in attacking anything and everything that gets on its bad side. With their sharp claws, they shred their enemies to pieces.

Vikodon.Pokedex Entry: They use their ax tails professionally, using precise strikes and dices to fight off enemies. Their fur helps them survive in cold temperatures.

Menagron.Pokedex Entry: Even though it despises shiny objects, its presence in caves and mountains is said to be a sign that there is treasure inside. It is normally very defensive and hostile, but if it is around kind Pokemon and people, it becomes very uncomfortable.

Treashard.Pokedex Entry: The jewels and treasure adorning its body act as protective armor. These Pokemon are very valuable, as they are able to turn anything they want into treasure.

Draegar.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon steal and guard anything of value with their lives. They are able to turn anything into gold, making them sought after by those who are greedy.

Vendraco.Pokedex Entry: They are able to fly easily thanks to the vents in their wings, as the vents allow air to push them. Their claws and wings are sharp enough to slice through a boulder with little difficulty.

Volaniro.Pokedex Entry: Their wings can slice through a cave. Their wings can absorb any air, allowing it to hover around.

Volante.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are able to withstand missile strikes. They fly by using air flowing through the vents inside of their wings.

Chydusela.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon has been around for millions of years, making it one of the oldest known that never went extinct. Throughout history, this Pokemon has been praised for saving the most people in the sea.

Dorolite.Pokedex Entry: Those who dive in the deep seas in which it lives are said to never return. It blinds its prey with its harsh lights before swallowing and burning them inside of its body, making its organ's light even brighter.

Stranaka.Pokedex Entry: Stranaka are very peculiar Pokemon, as they hardly ever blink or breathe, but still survive normally. When battling, they only stare at their opponents, taking a brutal beating before knocking them out in one attack.

Manaxor.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon's strange appearance gets it a lot of attention that it does not want, making it extremely hostile. Flying at 80 mph, this Pokemon's wings can slice clean through solid, tempered steel.

Maxavis.Pokedex Entry: Thought to be a myth, these Pokemon appear in numerous folklores and legends. They have been said to be able to destroy entire mountains with a single strike.

Mongodra.Pokedex Entry: One of the rarest Pokemon to find, they barely interact with humans and stay deep underground. It generates electricity thanks to a generator-like organ in its chest.

Pagioskoul.Pokedex Entry: Dwelling in the depths of the Earth, this Pokemon avoids sunlight at all costs in order to store its energy. When it is on the move, it is said that the entire region violently shakes.

Drakoura.Pokedex Entry: It resides high in the sky, feasting on clouds. They rarely show themselves to humans, but protect the region nonetheless.

Drownage.Pokedex Entry: They usually reside in swamps, marshes, and lakes, devouring other Pokemon that live there. They suck in a vast amount of water in an area, leaving other fish Pokemon exposed. When fisherman get close, it drags them into the water and swallows them whole.

Toxila.Pokedex Entry: Its poisonous jaws are able to melt through metal and bone. Its markings are warning signs to everything that approaches it.

Dryvern.Pokedex Entry: Using its drill-like tail, it burrows underground for shelter. If spotted, they bury themselves in sand to remain unnoticed.

Wyvast.Pokedex Entry: By spinning its body at high speeds, it can burrow underground. They are one of the main reasons that there are holes in the desert.

Vyrnound.Pokedex Entry: Its wings are full of sand, so when threatened, they dispel an extreme amount to disguise itself and escape. They spent majority of their time underground, so they have no real urge to eat anything; they only eat when food comes close to them.

Jalausaur.Pokedex Entry: Its bodily fluids can be harvested, heated, hardened and ground into fine spices. Its glare is able to intimidate and frighten any Pokemon.

Tyram.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon cannot see, so they use the purple sensors on their heads to navigate. They ram into opponents with great force, sometimes knocking the wind out of them.

Tantyra.Pokedex Entry: Their jaws are full of razor sharp teeth that are able to reduce boulders to pebbles. If they see you, they will immediately ram into you, attempting to knock you unconscious.

Sergalak.Pokedex Entry: Its noble, yet dangerous appearance make it an amazing sight to see. These Pokemon were once hated all around Xenioh because of the destruction they caused, but are now loved because of their chivalrous and graceful abilities.

Tawartagun.Pokedex Entry: It fought with FASUTAGON over whether the earth should fall into darkness or purity. After the battle, it was confined to a Dark Shard, which now resides in the Dark Palace. It breaks free and awakens when it feels the time is right to spread its malevolence, which leads to FASUTAGON awakening and causing their battle to commence.

Mercotical.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is the leader over Fasutagon and Tawartagun; it is said that it is able to control these two because of the shards that it keeps hidden. Mercotical will only appear when people are in danger or when the world is in danger; It is able to spread light dust across an area that can calm down any situation.

Turategon.Pokedex Entry: Its whiskers and fins are able to detect when a tsunami or massive rainstorm is about to occur. It is highly recognized for helping civilians that are plagued by said disasters.

Crocodon.Pokedex Entry: Their jaws were strong enough to snap a semi-truck in half. Their spikes could quintuple in length and they would spin with their prey impaled on them to rip them into pieces.

Spyno.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are extremely emotional and dislike when people argue. Their spikes can release a fluid that can heal wounds, making them sought by doctors and pharmacists.

Dynospyke.Pokedex Entry: The orb on its chest can detect anger and spite, which makes it very upset. Its spikes can be used to calm and make hostile enemies friendly.

Spykosor.Pokedex Entry: It is highly regarded as a peacemaker in times of trouble. It sends a barrage of its spikes that can calm down whatever they touch.

Betenorn.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are avoided because of their wretched tendencies. They wrap their long bodies around its victims, and like a snake, slowly compresses them until they suffocate.

Dybetenor.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are known to separate their spirit from their bodies and possess humans so they may bring them to their lairs. They suffocate and devour helpless victims, and smiles as they do so.

Lusiforus.Pokedex Entry: Said to be a guardian of the underworld, they create portals and kidnap humans to devour them. They use their feelers to separate souls from the bodies of humans and destroy them.

Hydrake.Pokedex Entry: According to legends, this Pokemon and its evolved forms climbed up a waterfall and brought rain to a large area plagued with a drought. It tries its best not to be seen by humans.

Kuname.Pokedex Entry: Blending into its aquatic habitat makes it easier to catch prey and also avoid being captured. It can cause showers that lasts 40 days and 40 nights.

Omamigon.Pokedex Entry: Worshiped by many, it brings rain to those in desperate need. It is hardly ever seen because of its color.

Shivren.Pokedex Entry: They freeze moisture in the air and make shards to attack its opponents. They can hang upside down from ceilings and drop icicles from above.

Guivrelid.Pokedex Entry: They can make blizzards by flapping their wings, which have icy particles. Despite their hostile appearance, they are actually very respectable and kind.

Drackap.Pokedex Entry: Disguising themselves as harmless plants makes it easier for them to catch prey. They use their sweet odor to lure victims in before snaring them with vines.

Podraco.Pokedex Entry: They scatter spores from their tails in order to put  their prey to sleep before eating them. Their spiky seeds are fired rapidly into the ground, causing more DRACKAP to emerge.

Dermadon.Pokedex Entry: Their beads are very toxic, but also very valuable, which prompts jewel makers to risk their lives to get them. Their poisonous saliva can paralyze any part of your body.

Versetile.Pokedex Entry: Any Psychic-type move it does affects everything around it. It is able to use moves of every type with ease.

Versadon.Pokedex Entry: When their spikes glow, it is a sign that something terrible is going to happen or is happening at that time. By channeling its brainpower, it can create a psychic wave that is strong enough to reduce an entire city to dust.

Skidurt.Pokedex Entry: It has a very crafty and mischievous nature, as it is known to fling mud at passing trainers. They keep their bodies completely filthy so they are able to blend in with the swampy environment in which they live.

Mudator.Pokedex Entry: They sometimes eat other weak Pokemon. They leave muddy footprints wherever they go, striking fear in people who are in dark, shady areas.

Spikinka.Pokedex Entry: Their saliva contains more than 1000 different toxins. They can fire spikes at their enemies and severely poison them.

Peacerene.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are rarely seen in the wild. They have mystical powers that allow them to aid in the growth of plants.

Trankilin.Pokedex Entry: Rarely seen in the wild, these Pokemon have strange powers that allow them to protect flourishing fields. If spotted by humans, these Pokemon will immediately disappear.

Drakelp.Pokedex Entry: Drakelp lie in wait, letting their leaf-like feelers sway to and fro order to lure smaller fish Pokemon toward it. They are hardly ever seen due to their great camouflage, sometimes leading people to believe that their population has decreased exponentially.

Origon.Pokedex Entry: It is said to be the ancestor of all dragon-types. They never understood their power, so they fought with small sticks and rocks.

Draconkur.Pokedex Entry: The ancestor of all Dragon-types, they were proud of their immense power. The would often devour the weaker ones among them as a way to convince others to get stronger.

Ynch.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon eat all day every day, not stopping until they are full. They will eat absolutely anything given to them.

Dewynch.Pokedex Entry: The two heads are always arguing with each other, as they are aggressive when it comes to food. At night, they take turns sleeping, as one will always act as a lookout.

Truigor.Pokedex Entry: When they run out of food, they devour any and everything that they find, excluding humans and other Pokemon. The head in the center acts as the leader over the other two, commanding them to do things telepathically.

Celsiose.Pokedex Entry: They use two icy rocks as arms in order to defend itself, as well as attack. Their bodies are 86 percent cold air, so its head is its only weak point.

Globee.Pokedex Entry: To protect themselves from harm, they spit out a red, burning sap. The most unimpressive and strangest Dragon-type Pokemon, its type is often debated and questioned by professors.

Hemogrowth.Pokedex Entry: The sap that they produce can cause permanent blindness if it gets on any part of the face. They are exceptionally large Pokemon that can destroy entire cities just by slithering through one.

Basileer.Pokedex Entry: They use their ghostly arms to attack those who get to close to them. Their glare is able to paralyze anyone in place for up to two months.

Gemasil.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are very blunt and aggressive, grabbing prey tight and wringing out their bodily fluids out before devouring them. If you upset one, it will curse you for an entire month without remorse.

Diatogama.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon disappear to evade attack before using their four arms to disable opponents and drain them of their life energy and bodily fluids. There was a case of a young man who angered this Pokemon, so it placed a curse on him that lasted until he died at age 112.

Gracidra.Pokedex Entry: They love little children and are always determined to protect them from the harsh realities of the world. These Pokemon originated when small children's dreams became a reality and took their own forms.

Tormegon.Pokedex Entry: They take pride in terrifying humans and Pokemon of all shapes and sizes, plaguing them with horrific depictions in their heads. These Pokemon originated when small children's nightmares became a reality and took their own forms.

Rustang.Pokedex Entry: Its large arms are able to break through bedrock as if it was paper. Their rusty bodies are capable of causing disease with just one touch, so trainers must be wary.

Geodra.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon thrive by eating nothing but wet dirt. They primarily reside in caves and battle each other to make each other stronger.

Terrofigra.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can eat straight through the Earth's core and come out unscathed because of its body's intense insulation. They are rather quick-tempered and will attack anything and anyone who harms their living environment.

Anaclipso.Pokedex Entry: Tales involving it usually say the same thing: It once completely blocked the sun, plunging the world into darkness. Sunlight makes it weak, so if it senses any light, it will try to either hide or destroy the source.

Seawee.Pokedex Entry: They expel a stream of bubbles to propel themselves forward and back. Riding in ocean currents, it is able to travel to different regions in just a few weeks.

Nesshor.Pokedex Entry: It lives in warm seas, but is hardly ever seen. Its speed in water never exceeds 50 mph.

Mysteran.Pokedex Entry: It creates whirlpools by unleashing a torrent of bubbles from its mouth. Few have actually come across them, as they often spoken of as a myth.

Nessinorch.Pokedex Entry: Their entire existence has been debated by researchers and adventurers for years. It is often said that flash floods occur when this Pokemon cries.

Myogon.Pokedex Entry: They freeze smaller Pokemon into statues in order to decorate the caves in which they live. Despite their elegant appearances, they are known to be very dangerous.

Shockwyrm.Pokedex Entry: When they feel weak, they wrap themselves around larger Pokemon, disrupting their electrical impulses. They are often sought after because their electricity is used in shock therapy sessions.

Voltagen.Pokedex Entry: When they are filled with electricity, they discharge it across vast distances. When catching prey, they coil around it, paralyze it, and devour it whole.

Kaminaros.Pokedex Entry: They are known to create thunderstorms when they roar. Using a special organ in its body, it is able to produce enough electricity to power an entire city.

Slimyxi.Pokedex Entry: Residing in the depths of the sea, these Pokemon strive by devouring other Pokemon like Raween and Sushamaki. Their bodies produce a viscous slime that allows them to evade capture.

Celuxera.Pokedex Entry: It is said to be a manifestation of light and power. Watching over the world from the thermosphere, it has been said to fire bright beams of electricity wherever it sees darkness.

Celaneron.Pokedex Entry: Celaneron has complete control over sound, being able to mute the entire world with a swipe of its claws. It is thought to be the embodiment of sound itself; it breaks the sound barrier whenever it travels.

Jerblitz.Pokedex Entry: They nuzzle each other and share electricity as a sign of friendship. These Pokemon are mostly nocturnal and gather in groups during thunderstorms in order to absorb electricity through their thunderbolt-shaped tail.

Monkurren.Pokedex Entry: It can generate electricity by spinning its tail around. They are not very agile when it comes to trees, as they always fall from them.

Monkilo.Pokedex Entry: If it absorbs too much electricity, it goes crazy and shoots electricity all around. It plugs its tail into outlets and generators in order to strengthen its power.

Gorillect.Pokedex Entry: It bangs it arms on the ground repeatedly in order to create electricity. When it is fully charged, its electric attacks can have 100,000 volts of electricity.

Ikarode.Pokedex Entry: It loves to shock anything that comes close to it with its tail. They plug their tails into outlets in order to gain more electrical power.

Livolt.Pokedex Entry: It is able to create over 9,000,000 kilowatts of electricity with its tail. They throw orbs of electricity from their pouches that can reduce a tank to ashes.

Ionatt.Pokedex Entry: It is said to have a special relationship with the Pokemon VIRUBIC2. It assists scientists in labs, charging and powering their inventions.

Raiote.Pokedex Entry: They raise their tails during thunderstorms to charge themselves. They are very excitable and playful Pokemon that need to keep moving in order to keep up their energy.

Ampark.Pokedex Entry: It is hypothesized that when they reach a certain level of enjoyment and excitement, their power reaches their full level. They are usually the cause of unusual thunderstorms.

Coyatt.Pokedex Entry: They unleash thunderbolts from their palms. They absorb electricity through their tail and use it to gain energy so it is able to move quickly.

Pakina.Pokedex Entry: It can generate sparks by rubbing its fur together. It almost never realizes the kind of situation it is in, whether it be good or bad.

Paralite.Pokedex Entry: They absorb and deliver electricity from their opponents in battle using their palms and soles. They cackle maniacally when they prepare to launch a powerful attack.

Billectric.Pokedex Entry: The horn on its bill can interfere with radio transmissions and short out generators. They're unable to see very well, so they rely on electric stimuli to get around.

Generec.Pokedex Entry: They crawl into power plants and feed on the electricity. If they are out of energy, their fur turns a pale gray.

Thundrec.Pokedex Entry: They drain power plants of their energy, causing major blackouts. They hunt in groups of 2-4 in order to catch their prey.

Degloom.Pokedex Entry: It generates electricity in its body thanks to the an organ in its chest, but it is unable release it. Lacking the energy and strength to fully unleash the electricity in their bodies, they are always seen with a gloomy expression.

Cynogy.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon always live underground, yet their electric-type capabilities still work, causing confusion in many scientists and professors. They shoot up from the burrows they dig when their opponents get close.

Shocach.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon have four eyes in total, two on top of its head to scout out passing prey, and two on its front to see forward. When prey gets close, they unleash a controlled 10,000 volts to it.

Elektro.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon always release negatively charged energy, which actually drains the energy away from other power sources. They are usually found near Power Plants, absorbing the electricity into their bodies.

Elektrio.Pokedex Entry: Comprised of three ELEKTRO, these Pokemon are able to give off 30,000 volts of electricity at any given time. They are able to create large clouds that can paralyze the moments of those who are enveloped in it.

Elekloud.Pokedex Entry: Elekloud is formed when Elektrio is somehow pulled closer together when exposed to electrical stimulation. It releases numerous mini-trons in order to aid in its attacking.

Hirod.Pokedex Entry: Their antlers give off electric discharge when they are startled. They are able to draw in electricity with their tails and antlers, charging up their own power.

Rolampe.Pokedex Entry: During thunderstorms, they use their antlers to communicate with clouds in order to cause a large surge of power to come to them. They charge  headfirst into trees and end up destroying them with electricity.

Siemux.Pokedex Entry: Farmers who raise these Pokemon often do so for protection from bad thunderstorms. These Pokemon are able to absorb and release over 3,000,000 megawatts of electricity in a single setting.

Guraden.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon hop and run around using their long legs, creating shock waves all around. Bouncing helps them generate electricity; they are able to disintegrate an entire oil tanker if they bounce for a long time and store their electricity.

Krishocka.Pokedex Entry: When around other Electric-types, it is compelled to cling to them and drain them of their electricity in order to power itself up. They are extremely fast, being able to take down prey within mere seconds.

Wattsun.Pokedex Entry: They absorb sunlight into their fur in order to convert it into electricity. Their fur glows in the dark.

Xulux.Pokedex Entry: When angered, their fur spikes up like needles. A special organ in their bodies is what causes their fur to glow radiantly.

Bossurge.Pokedex Entry: Said to have been born from lightning, these Pokemon discharge an immense amount of electricity. Their fur glows radiantly, blinding their enemies and allowing them to defeat them with relative ease.

Blitzat.Pokedex Entry: They are often seen flying around power plants at night. It can cause electronic devices to malfunction just by flying next to them.

Thudat.Pokedex Entry: They are able to electrify their claws in order to paralyze opponents with slashes. It apparently has the ability to drain the electrons from your atoms.

Zapour.Pokedex Entry: These playful Pokemon love using their paws to shock people. They are able to absorb electricity through the horns on their heads.

Xolect.Pokedex Entry: They hide in water, waiting for others to unknowingly approach it; once they are close, they shock them. Absorbing electricity through its horns, it is able to discharge more than 450,000 volts of electricity.

Duorb.Pokedex Entry: They spin opposite of each other in order to generate electricity. They are able to function individually if they generate enough power in their bodies.

Matonic.Pokedex Entry: Its 'arms' are actually separate heads that each have their own brain and personality. It generates electricity by rotating the heads against its body.

Autogenate.Pokedex Entry: Its three heads use electromagnetic signals to communicate with each other. Its lower half spins at over 60 mph in order to generate over 1,000 megavolts of electricity.

Nezumika.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon keep themselves buried, using their flower-like tails to absorb sunlight that they can convert to electricity. Nezumika stores electricity in its cheeks and send it into its paws, but because its power is so weak, it only gives an enemy a tingling sensation.

Kwillo.Pokedex Entry: Its body is covered in hot quills that are able to release bursts of electricity. They shoot their quills at berries to roast them before eating them.

Spikwill.Pokedex Entry: One stab from one of its quills can cause a burning pain that will last for weeks. Oddly enough, their quills are sometimes used by hairdressers to curl or straighten hair.

Slaplus.Pokedex Entry: They rub their hands together in order to generate electricity. Whenever it smacks something, the recipient receives a high voltage shock.

Puncharge.Pokedex Entry: Its punches can disintegrate a small building. It absorbs electricity through its horns and spikes on its arms.

Galvanatt.Pokedex Entry: They are very resilient and able to produce more than 50,000 gigawatts of electricity. It is often fired into outer space to help with extremely massive power outages.

Kwillord.Pokedex Entry: They fire over a dozen of their spikes at their enemies, which immediately grow back. Getting stabbed by one of their quills will leave your skin deeply burned and your limbs paralyzed.

Bulaka.Pokedex Entry: They use their blue light to lure foolish people and Pokemon towards them. Once a victim is close enough, it wraps its arms around it, draining their life energy in order to make its light brighter.

Shadakue.Pokedex Entry: They extend their rope-like attachments to drain unsuspecting people and Pokemon to make their light glow brighter. It is rare, but in a desperate attempt to make their lights keep glowing, they will turn on their trainers.

Phlikur.Pokedex Entry: They work together to trick people into using them for decorations, then drain the life energy of anyone who comes near. Their blue lights can have a hypnotic effect on those who stare.

Rorelic.Pokedex Entry: They gather in groups and roar in a mysterious pattern during the night time. Sparks emitted from their bodies often send signals to others in their pride.

Zamp.Pokedex Entry: They are so fast that they are often mistaken as bolts of lightning. They rest in nests made from wires and sticks.

Amplume.Pokedex Entry: They fly so fast that they sometimes cause sonic booms. They discharge electricity from the organ in its chest

Fuzztic.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can generate electricity by simply rubbing against something. Articles of clothing sometimes cling to this Pokemon's fur, making it feel uncomfortable.

Surgeus.Pokedex Entry: The organ on its chest stores poison that courses through its body. Their claws have a paralyzing agent that not only poisons their target, but immobilizes them as well.

Cerebolt.Pokedex Entry: Getting shocked by one of these Pokemon can cause short term memory loss, a lack of awareness, and a loss of consciousness. They are known to be innovative if they see someone with a problem.

Corthun.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon were discovered in an old abandoned laboratory, exhibiting strange behaviors similar to that of scientists. A common rumor is that these Pokemon are actually scientists that were accidentally mutated in an experiment gone awry.

Hangen.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon love to sit on the tops of trees and watch thunderstorms. Their tails act as generators, and they are able to bounce on them in order to create electricity.

Generet.Pokedex Entry: They like teasing other Pokemon with their charm and zapping them once they are close enough. They rotate their tails in order to generate electricity.

Generai.Pokedex Entry: By spinning their tails, they can generate enough electricity to vaporize a helicopter. They are extremely fast Pokemon who can sometimes only be seen as blurs.

Gulash.Pokedex Entry: The pent up electricity from when it was a Degloom has now been released, giving it confidence and energy. They are able to dish out 300 punches in under 3 seconds.

Spunder.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon fly around while spinning, zapping anything that it pleases. Their electricity is strong enough to power up a house for 30 years.

Twisthun.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can travel through power lines, causing blackouts. By spinning on its tail at high speeds, it can overload any electrical device within a 100 foot radius.

Voltorna.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can cause an entire state's appliances to malfunction and go haywire. They can create rotating thunderstorms that can damage homes and businesses without a problem.

Olmectric.Pokedex Entry: They reside in caves with water inside, enjoying the bountiful nutrients. They are able to actually devour electricity, charging their bodies from the inside out.

Shockholm.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon live in lakeside areas and wait for thunderstorms to come by. The red orb on their tails blink when a dangerous thunderstorm is about to occur.

Zappa.Pokedex Entry: They are able to drain an entire skyscraper of their power supply by just placing their tails into outlets. They coil their bodies around their prey and electrocute them until they are unconscious.

Tidonor.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon gather objects that are the same color as its body, no matter how large or small it is. They deliver intense shocks through their feet when hunting for prey or gathering living things to add to their collection.

Kimarisu.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are often found around power plants gnawing on wires, causing an interference with the circulation of electricity. They make their homes near transmission towers.

Coulimba.Pokedex Entry: After being struck by lightning, this Pokemon absorbed the electricity, causing it to evolve. The electricity in its body is discharged from its chest and claws.

Arfib.Pokedex Entry: When someone tells a lie, its hair stands on end and its tongue extends and retracts repeatedly. It charges up its electricity by shaking its rough fur.

Ariguso.Pokedex Entry: It tongue is comprised of electricity and flesh, making every lick of it painful. It can sense when someone tells a lie and will immediately shock them into telling the truth.

Geraina.Pokedex Entry: Running allows them to charge up electricity in their bodies. They are able to walk on their hind legs in short intervals and land devastating blows with their hard hooves.

Faradra.Pokedex Entry: They are often seen standing on their hind legs in order to reach trees with extremely high branches. Their hooves are electrified, causing anyone who touches them to become paralyzed.

Zaparrot.Pokedex Entry: They are often found during thunderstorms, flying high in an attempt to absorb electricity. They use electricity to cook food in their mouths.

Beaktric.Pokedex Entry: Their crests stand on end when a thunderstorm is approaching. Their beaks store most of their electricity.

Sumastorma.Pokedex Entry: A dangerous Ultra Beast, it has been seen vaporizing entire buildings with a single lightning strike. Dark clouds roll in wherever it goes, causing storms that last from weeks to months.

Leerup.Pokedex Entry: Staring into its eyes is said to put you in a trance. During thunderstorms, it follows humans that are wandering in the mountains and once asleep, they steal the electrons from their body.

Howlurk.Pokedex Entry: Its eyes are said to be able to control anyone who looks into them. Their howls can summon thunderstorms.

Shockris.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon roams around Power Plants, absorbing electricity through its thunderbolt-shaped arm. It loves short-circuiting electronic devices and scaring innocent people and Pokemon.

Glitzap.Pokedex Entry: It shoots through electronics and causes them to explode. They feed off of the screams and static from people they prank.

Zapris.Pokedex Entry: It is able to use its long thunderbolt shaped arm to travel inside power wires and short them out, causing blackouts. It enjoys pulling pranks on people and Pokemon.

Electray.Pokedex Entry: They lie at the bottom of the ocean with their sharp, poison-filled tail hung out in the open in order to lure prey. When prey is near, it jabs it with its tail, delivering poison and electricity into its system.

Transphin.Pokedex Entry: Its grim appearance and disturbing actions make most people believe that it is a spirit. It swims upside down and attacks other Water-type Pokemon with electrified teeth.

Stwinkle.Pokedex Entry: They are able to blind enemies by letting the electricity inside their connected body bounce around and escape. It is often targeted by poachers and jewel thieves.

Sparklug.Pokedex Entry: The green gem in the center is the main control unit of all of the other diamonds. They are able to blind their enemies by reflecting light in their direction.

Parazeed.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon secretes a substance that can cause paralysis on contact. They hang from trees by their stems and absorb sunlight.

Nervent.Pokedex Entry: Eating one of its fruits can cause paralysis over the entire body. Groups of them sing during thunderstorms in order to gain electricity.

Tentacute.Pokedex Entry: Despite its cute appearance, this Pokemon is widely hated in Zinco due to its electrified tentacles. These Pokemon love interacting with others, but they unintentionally shock their friends with their tentacles, driving them away.

Tenpara.Pokedex Entry: They hide among the weeds and grass underwater in order to feed on zooplankton. Its playful nature, along with its electrified tentacles, make it a Pokemon to be wary of.

Kudzap.Pokedex Entry: The spots on its body glow as a result of the electricity in its bloodstream. When it is storming outside, this Pokemon will find the highest point it can find and raise its tail in order to absorb the lightning.

Fresthor.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon glide into thunderstorms in order to absorb electricity via both its tail and the horn on its head. Its blood is now completely electrified and can be seen through its body as a light.

Plopillar.Pokedex Entry: When sick, the light in its head dims and it turns pale. They are usually seen playing in the snow and slipping and falling onto each other due to their little legs.

Skiplunge.Pokedex Entry: The lights that it can emit from its eyebrows are seen as a spectacle to those who see them. They are able to create balls of electricity and freeze them before throwing them towards opponents, causing double the damage.

Rokzz.Pokedex Entry: The electrical discharge they give off can restore life to almost any being. They embed themselves in the walls and ceilings of caves to sleep and give off bright lights that illuminate the whole cave.

Electrok.Pokedex Entry: They can discharge over 100,000 kilowatts of electricity. They are able to revive thousands of deceased individuals at one time using their electricity.

Voltoast.Pokedex Entry: They spit out soot in order to temporarily blind their opponents, giving them time to escape. They stay near volcanoes and come out during thunderstorms to absorb the electricity.

Ahmeltric.Pokedex Entry: The smoke around its neck can combust, allowing it to create devastating fires. They produce electricity that can causes whatever it hits to melt.

Coppence.Pokedex Entry: It is speculated that this Pokemon is the reason that electricity is commonly used around the world. Its body is mostly made of a highly conductive metal, allowing it to absorb and distribute electricity with ease.

Tadart.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon communicate by staring into each others' eyes for a long period of time. They are able to both eat and poison tree sap just by zooming into the bark of a tree.

Dartox.Pokedex Entry: Getting stabbed by this Pokemon's nose or licked by its long tongue will cause severe poisoning and paralysis. It devours sour berries and old food in order to keep itself energized.

Tubranch.Pokedex Entry: They convert the nutrients that they absorb from the ground into power in order to fire balls of electricity. To move, they hop around while leaving electrical charges.

Lichannon.Pokedex Entry: They fire electric cannonballs from their arms when threatened. They enjoy eating dry rocks and stones.

Zappie.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is very slow-witted, not registering any type of pain given to it; it even shocks itself when using Electric-type moves! When it is sleeping, it inserts its antennae into electrical sockets that are nearby, compromising the flow of electricity.

Gillisten.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon only has one organ that controls all of its bodily functions. The organ in its body makes different areas of its body glow in the dark, making it easy for it to hunt for prey in the dark seas in which it lives.

Sinaru.Pokedex Entry: Grabbing its tail delivers a shock that changes  a person's personality. It is said to be an embodiment of sin.

Malarund.Pokedex Entry: Full of hate and negativity, these Pokemon take pride in stalking those who are pure of heart. They unleash thunderbolts full of negative energy that can cause anyone to become cold and brooding.

Sietruaro.Pokedex Entry: Hatred and sin radiate throughout its body, causing its fur to change colors. Being shocked by one of these Pokemon causes a sharp pain to surge throughout your body, giving you the feeling of impending death.

Tengam.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can link together to increase their magnetic attraction. They float around while spinning, as their arms keep trying to pull towards each other.

Nawtchu.Pokedex Entry: They are said to be living gates to an alternate world, as looking into their stomachs shows another you that is not like you at all. It is said that they create duplicates, as well as switch people between the real world and the alternate world to stir up trouble.

Ottorrid.Pokedex Entry: They use their whiskers to electrify prey before devouring them. Thunderbolts shoot from its smoky tail when it is angry.

Amperoast.Pokedex Entry: They show no mercy in battle, not stopping until their opponents are burnt to a crisp. It has an electricity-producing organ that allows it to unleash devastating thunderbolts whenever it is in danger.

Dirapyx.Pokedex Entry: For whatever reason, every six hours, if they are left alone, they face different directions. It is said that if you follow a Dirapyx while on a beach, you may find hidden objects in the sand.

Vauveau.Pokedex Entry: VAUVEAU never lets go of the ring it carries. It loves suckling on rings because it enjoys the metallic taste.

Veaula.Pokedex Entry: It loves to use the rings it collects as toys, using them mostly as hula hoops. The rings are able to form a barrier around VEAULA that is able to deflect attacks.

Molaby.Pokedex Entry: According to legends, Molaby will appear when kids put teeth underneath their pillows. Its floss-like tail is able to cleanse anything it wraps around.

Cuspix.Pokedex Entry: Its floss-like tail tangles around its teeth-like legs constantly. They are very friendly, but will always try to take others' loose teeth without consent.

Enamelle.Pokedex Entry: It has very large internal jaws full of teeth that it has collected. When they take teeth from children, they slowly swipe their floss across their mouth, causing the growth of new teeth faster.

Tolum.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are covered in a sweet, powdery substance that attracts unwanted attention to it. It loves to dance and can always cheer someone up.

Suitee.Pokedex Entry: Its sugar can cause whoever eats it to dance. It can sense when others are upset, prompting it to give off more sugar.

Woolish.Pokedex Entry: Its wool is said to give good luck to those who are pure of heart. It pulls its wool over its head in order to defend itself better.

Luscmor.Pokedex Entry: It is extremely hard to find these Pokemon in the wild, but it still searched for on a regular basis. It is said that owning a LUSCMOR will result in having instant success in anything you want.

Sloshweet.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon leave a trail of marshmallow-like ooze wherever they go, causing other people and Pokemon to slip or get stuck. It is known to be very lucky if you actually encounter a SLOSHWEET in the wild.

Kindichi.Pokedex Entry: It is known as a bringer of happiness and kindness. It appears during times of intense tragedy and hostility in order to try to calm the situation.

Pupuff.Pokedex Entry: Their fur is very sweet, prompting them to lick them themselves more than usual. They are loved by children.

Cottaste.Pokedex Entry: Their fur is able to expand in order to protect them from harsh blows. They are admired for their gracious personalities and appearance.

Teddwa.Pokedex Entry: TEDDWA are mostly inanimate, as they never move from a place they are put down or if they are called out. Oddly enough, they don't breathe or blink and are still able to survive in any environment.

Zwursa.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon do not eat, sleep, or even breathe, they only stand in one place. They watch over homes and gardens by standing there and staring.

Powdus.Pokedex Entry: These whimsical Pokemon float around large castles and mansions, spreading a special powder. Their powder is said to allow people to float for shot periods of time.

Rillix.Pokedex Entry: Its pink shell gives off mystical energy ever so often. It curls into a ball to protect its furry body.

Armadiluk.Pokedex Entry: They curl into spiked balls to generate a mysterious energy. They are said to be able to overcome any challenge.

Rushuga.Pokedex Entry: They were discovered in a candy manufacturing company in the aftermath of a huge explosion. Their bodies are packed with a sweet, sugar-like substance that makes them easy prey for larger Pokemon.

Pegustar.Pokedex Entry: They guide lost travelers using stardust. They fly in a special formation that is said to bring protection.

Trollic.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are highly mischievous, pulling tricks on those who encounter it. Most of the time, its pranks prove to be good, but when they backfire, it always gets caught in the cross-hairs.

Sneakimp.Pokedex Entry: If you find that one of your shoes is missing, there is a high chance that a Sneakimp has taken it. It usually takes a Sneakimp weeks to months to find a suitable home, as they are very picky.

Imboot.Pokedex Entry: Imboot typically reside in larger shoes, usually boots, and float around in them, often startling those around them. They are known to invite smaller Pokemon into their shoe homes; it dislikes Pokemon bigger than itself.

Moneni.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon stay inside of their pots hardly ever come out unless they needs or wants to. The pots they reside in can transport them to another realm.

Panecilli.Pokedex Entry: When approached by possible predators due to their muffin-shaped heads, Panecilli increase the weight of any and all creatures around them, giving them a chance to escape. Born of a flower, these Pokemon spend most of their time in fields.

Sankira.Pokedex Entry: It is known to leave confectionery on the doorsteps or next to of those who have a good heart. They are able to create different sweets using its sweet tasting sweat.

Pawim.Pokedex Entry: Having these Pokemon nearby will grant you success, no matter how hard the challenge They are able to headbutt into trees and snap them with one punch.

Pawtluck.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon love to be around their trainers, no matter how mean they are. They are said to give luck to anything that their rope-like tail swipes across.

Myracis.Pokedex Entry: Nobody knows where it originated from or why it behaves the way that it does; all that is known is that it is a kind and sympathetic Pokemon. There have been stories heard of it helping the poor and less-fortunate become very prosperous.

Wobball.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's bodies are very malleable and able to be changed into different shapes. It is often flying around during festivals and celebrations, absorbing the positive energy.

Flexiball.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon disguise themselves as balloon animals in order to absorb positivity from children. Their bodies are very flexible and durable, not even able to be harmed by a Giga Impact.

Calapix.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are very affectionate and will often choose to ride around their trainers' necks rather than being in their pokeballs. They are able to shoot rainbow-like beams from their necks.

Fragras.Pokedex Entry: It is able to give off a multitude of odors that can either be pleasant or repugnant. They stand on their arms and spray the air with a sweet odor when they are happy.

Aromunk.Pokedex Entry: It has a fairly arrogant attitude and will not listen to its trainer unless it accepts its stench. Their waste generally smells nice, so it is often collected and transformed into some of the best perfume.

Dynamos.Pokedex Entry: Representing masculine strength, this Pokemon was said to have stop an earthquake from destroying Mirus by holding the splitting plates. One punch from it is said to collapse an entire mountain.

Valyant.Pokedex Entry: They are always in a rush to have more fun. It has a bold and brave nature, taking on any opponent, large or small.

Servalor.Pokedex Entry: It is very protective of younger Pokemon and would rather die than see one get injured. It loves to go on journeys and adventures in order to assert itself as brave and courageous.

Frankraze.Pokedex Entry: It is able to lift 20 times its own weight. If it wins a fight, it will dance joyfully.

Steinack.Pokedex Entry: They unconsciously toss rocks, other Pokemon, or even their trainers, when they are happy. One punch from it can collapse a skyscraper.

Badem.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are often seen fighting each other in front of crowds of other Badem. Their sweat contains caffeine, so coffee brewers capture them and allow them to battle other Pokemon in order to collect it.

Knochain.Pokedex Entry: Knochain are known to attach heavy items, such as stones, to their arms and legs in order to give themselves more of a challenge when fighting each other. Coffee made from their sweat is said to give someone enhanced strength for a limited amount of time.

Whicom.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon practice their whip techniques on trees, often causing them to fall. They move very swiftly using their whip-like tails.

Powhip.Pokedex Entry: They practice their whipping techniques on each other. Their whips are able to strike through steel with ease.

Etchizur.Pokedex Entry: In legend, this Pokemon taught humans about the importance of value and confidence. It often appears when feuds between Naitizar and Anaitizor rear their ugly heads.

Soom%27oh.Pokedex Entry: They train by jumping from high areas onto each others' stomachs. They are extremely competitive and will not stop fighting, even if it they have lost.

Omusize.Pokedex Entry: Their large hands can destroy concrete with one clap. To toughen themselves, they tug on the rope around their waists.

Calfoal.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon train themselves by randomly hitting large objects. When they are born, they immediately attempt to fight anyone that is near them.

Liffin.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon love showing off their strength by lifting things more than 10 times their own size. They are very competitive and will always try to outdo Fighting-types larger than them.

Tuffin.Pokedex Entry: By constantly lifting the dumbbells they carry around, they increase their strength by a tremendous amount. They have enough strength to lift up an entire skyscraper with one hand.

Sauki.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon always protect their trainers, no matter how terrible they are. Very loyal to their trainers, they always prepare to attack anything and anyone that approaches him or her.

Toumie.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's paws are strong enough to go straight through concrete with little to no resistance. Despite them walking on all fours, they are able to stand upright and fight professionally thanks to their well developed hind legs muscles.

Brawlick.Pokedex Entry: To strengthen each other, they train under Pokemon that are much stronger than themselves. They try to develop new battle styles in order to throw their opponents off.

Juniar.Pokedex Entry: As soon as they are born, they are eager to fight and train. Very energetic, they often get themselves into trouble when trying to pick fights that they can't win.

Gobblord.Pokedex Entry: Its appearance likens it to a man in a costume, so its true identity is still a mystery to many. It only appears when the Fiendish Four appears in order to save those affected by them.

Kowallop.Pokedex Entry: They train themselves daily by punching trees and rocks. They are excitable Pokemon that enjoy the thrill of fighting and snack on shrubs for nutrition.

Taurough.Pokedex Entry: Their hooves are strong enough to penetrate an AGGRON's armor. They work in groups in order to protect PONTAUR.
