Roostrong.Pokedex Entry: They often fight with each other using their claws and muscular wings in order to see who will take care of Henna and Chickling. They are able to toss boulders with one wing.

Bearable.Pokedex Entry: They shred anything that they see as a threat to bits. They always watch the stars from the caves in which they live.

Gallion.Pokedex Entry: It will always take on others that are stronger than itself, even if the odds are against them. They push themselves very hard, which leads to stress in some cases.

Griffear.Pokedex Entry: Their pure green eyes strike fear in even the toughest opponent. It would rather risk its life than let anything bad  happen to its trainer or weaker Pokemon.

Beatwig.Pokedex Entry: When their sticks break, they immediately find new ones. They fight harshly with their twigs until they break.

Sticklor.Pokedex Entry: They practice their nun chuck techniques daily in order to strengthen themselves. They train with each other by taking blows from each other's nun chucks.

Timbrawl.Pokedex Entry: They handle their branches with extreme care. If their branches break, they become extremely aggressive and will fight even harder.

Terrabull.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon guard their territories at all costs, no matter what. They spar with each other in order to raise their attacks and defenses.

Tufforse.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are hard fighters that never back down. Their hooves can crack bones with one kick.

Scuffowl.Pokedex Entry: They love to fight and will look for any reason to do so. The practice numerous fighting styles in order to do more damage.

Powork.Pokedex Entry: They move quickly and land devastating blows to their opponents, often with enough enough force to keep the Pokemon knocked out for hours. They come up with their own strategies and fighting styles for battles, often ignoring their trainers' directions.

Myzopop.Pokedex Entry: They are able to deliver hard blows that leave a sticky, viscous fluid on their enemies' bodies. They cling to the walls of caves using their sticky hands.

Aurithrash.Pokedex Entry: Their hands and feet are covered in a viscous fluid that allows them to stick to any surface. When battling, their hands often get stuck to their opponent, leaving them open to more damage.

Extravagale.Pokedex Entry: They travel in groups of three, with the one with the most bruises and battle scars acting as the leader. They are extremely hostile; locking eyes with them will result in an immediate attack.

Ninda.Pokedex Entry: It uses its bamboo stalk as a weapon. It is said that if you find a Ninda’s stalk if it has lost it, it will be forever grateful.

Pandaolin.Pokedex Entry: It swift and agile movements are unmatched by any other fighting-type. The bamboo staff it holds calms it down; when a Pandaolin loses its staff, it grows enraged, lashing out at everyone and everything around it.

Smokauf.Pokedex Entry: They sneak up behind others and use their smoke to suffocate them. Their wavy arms are able to knock you out in one hit.

Kaufite.Pokedex Entry: They use their arms to punch brick and concrete. Their bodies are comprised of a potent gas that can kill anyone just by having them inhale it.

Brawleti.Pokedex Entry: It has a very abrasive and independent personality. It will always avoid contact with other humans and Pokemon.

Dattapoch.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is the cause of the need to fight in order to solve problems. Its wings can double as fists and are powerful enough to punch down a pyramid.

Beavah.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon's IQ is extremely low. They lay on dams that they create with their powerful, flat tails, and stare at the sky.

Nawurk.Pokedex Entry: It always gnaws on a toothpick in order to keep itself calm. They work hard to create large, stable dams that they can use to block their territory.

Wallabound.Pokedex Entry: Wallabound's feet pose a hindrance to it, as it always trips over them when walking, so it instead relies of bouncing on its tail to get around. Its large feet are strong enough to demolish solid concrete.

Gurmrr.Pokedex Entry: They attack without mercy, biting and clawing at an attacker until they stop moving. They were known to guard and watch over special castles and buildings in olden times.

Chomutila.Pokedex Entry: They are known to shred their enemies into pieces. Their bodies are covered in a mixture of their own, as well as their victims', blood.

Oferinch.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies and powerful and limber, giving them enough speed to land 30 blows in only one second. They are very prideful Pokemon who won't accept help from anyone or anything.

Deferinch.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon never back down or give up, even when they've taken a critical amount of damage. They are extremely protective of their trainers and fellow teammates.

Purruf.Pokedex Entry: They fight each other in order to strengthen themselves. They attack using sharp claws.

Rorec.Pokedex Entry: Their large bodies give them great defense. They can slice down a tree with one swipe of their claws.

Ughly.Pokedex Entry: They used their clubs to crack bones and rocks. Many of them still exist today, but they are hard to locate, as they are constantly on the move.

Oogone.Pokedex Entry: It was able to spear prey in the back by throwing its club, and bashed it repeatedly until it  stopped moving. It is hypothesized that some of them were able to survive and avoided going extinct, but evidence has yet to surface.

Mummite.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are completely hollow, so they keep their bandages on in order to keep things from going inside. The spirits of mummified children, they roam around abandoned tombs.

Mumman.Pokedex Entry: If their bandages are removed, the 'body' and spirit fall apart. They curse those who enter its territory with five plagues.

Bollem.Pokedex Entry: They are presumed to be over 1,000 years old. Their hands are strong enough to crush a boulder with no resistance.

Aimono.Pokedex Entry: It is able to detect its opponents' next moves using it eye. It has acute mental and physical strength, making it tough to beat.

Solonk.Pokedex Entry: They can use their opponents moves against them by countering. According to legend, SOLONK was the main Pokemon used by powerful monks.

Agresyc.Pokedex Entry: They are able to launch a psychic sucker punch that could break 100 bones. They can destroy an entire town in half an hour

Goldix.Pokedex Entry: Because they've now outgrown their pots of gold, they now carry them around to build up their strength. They only put down their gold when they are sleeping and always watch over it with one eye open.

Strengold.Pokedex Entry: They lift their pots of gold like weights and carry them on their shoulders to strengthen themselves. They are often seen devouring gold coins.

Kangareck.Pokedex Entry: They have a very violent temper, destroying whatever they see fit when agitated. Despite their tail being able to destroy truck in one punch, they mainly rely on their feet during combat.

Crustide.Pokedex Entry: They have a very high speed rate, as they can give over 100 blows within seconds. It has four back legs, but when moving at high speeds, it retracts two of them so that they won't disrupt its momentum.

Champodin.Pokedex Entry: A strike from this Pokemon's arms can collapse a building. It moves so fast and strikes so hard that it is not even seen when in battle, you only see the other Pokemon faint.

Gekalore.Pokedex Entry: They are able to stretch their legs longer in order to distribute harsher kicks. Their antlers can penetrate bedrock.

Northrash.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are quick to fight when they see a formidable opponent. The amount of scars on their body represent their age, as older ones are known to be much more violent.

Muskuff.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can release a powerful, musky odor from their wrists in order to immobilize their opponents. They usually follow Musneak's command, pummeling any Pokemon that causes problems for them.

Delinkid.Pokedex Entry: It constantly pursues by HUEVAL, as they are enemies. They are not afraid to hurt their trainers or larger Pokemon.

Brutanor.Pokedex Entry: It is very fond of VALEXCEL, always looking to beat them. They always try to show their trainer that they are the boss, but end up wussing out in the last minute.

Gorung.Pokedex Entry: They are able to punch straight through trees. They gather stones and rocks and pile them up before knocking them back down with an arm thrust.

Yongoro.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon grab hold of their opponents tight so that they can't escape before recklessly throwing and slamming them into whatever is around. They can toss trainers a distance of 200 kilometers with only one arm.

Gulflota.Pokedex Entry: By filling their arms will air or water and locking their palms, they can inflate them to large proportions. They are able to float in water will ease because of the holes in the arms and legs.

Kiwreck.Pokedex Entry: They train in the harshest weather to build up resistance to different elements. They attack with sharp strikes from their claws.

Twirlu.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are essentially scared of themselves, so they run away in a manner that looks like dancing. These Pokemon are scared of their own flames, as well as flames in general, so if it sees fire, it tries to run away.

Luspin.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are skilled with their flaming poles, spinning them at such a fast rate that they create flaming rings. Often used by performers, these Pokemon's combat techniques are often looked over to prioritize its pole spinning.

Soaklaw.Pokedex Entry: Their claws are able to absorb water and grow larger. They eat Absorage and use their absorbent bodies to cushion the blows from attacks.

Judekai.Pokedex Entry: Its body is as hard as steel. These quick tempered Pokemon are always ready to fight someone, but their lack of arms and small legs make it seem less threatening than it is.

Lyconfure.Pokedex Entry: It ignites its fur when it is ready for battle. It delivers a flurry of fiery punches and kicks that can reduce a semi-truck to ashes.

Shieluck.Pokedex Entry: By attaching discarded Clammince shells to smooth sticks, they create plentiful weapons to use in battle. They are often seen finding shells to fashion as armor.

Mustelleo.Pokedex Entry: It practices its fighting techniques with its shells by striking trees and boulders. The shell around its body is able to be removed when it is practicing so that it does not hinder its speed.

Papyrough.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are so thin and light that they are easily blown away by wind. These Pokemon fight by delivering devastating slashes towards their enemies' weak points.

Tesscoga.Pokedex Entry: Many people enjoy watching these Pokemon battle and train due to their grace and expertise with the fans they wield. Their fans are able to slice clean through bedrock with ease.

Lumescian.Pokedex Entry: They have been known to save people and Pokemon who were caught in shipwrecks. They prefer warm seas so that their kelp-like hair can grow stronger.

Catager.Pokedex Entry: When startled, they kick the things closest to them, whether they be living or inanimate. Despite their small size, they are able to launch people as far as 200 miles.

Nageruf.Pokedex Entry: They are able to unleash 150 kicks in a single minute. If you approach these Pokemon from behind, they will instinctively kick and send you flying.

Launger.Pokedex Entry: When riding one of these Pokemon, you will have to hold on tight, as they are known to stop abruptly, sending riders flying. Their kicks are strong enough to crack bedrock.

Lumbash.Pokedex Entry: Carrying large blocks of wood, these Pokemon are highly defensive of their territory. These Pokemon are skilled craftsmen, as they are able to create beautiful statues and intricately designed pieces by eating away at their wooden blocks.

Zomblow.Pokedex Entry: They are very tricky opponents, being able to move quickly and dodge attacks within seconds. The talisman on their heads are the source of their power; if it is removed, it crumbles to the ground, no longer animated.

Shaotic.Pokedex Entry: It loves causing mass hysteria and chaos by manipulating the minds of humans and Pokemon. They have enough strength to throw a tree with one arm.

Deboneigh.Pokedex Entry: They charm female humans and Pokemon with its kind gestures before leading them into the woods where they are never heard from again. They are known to steal and destroy items from unsuspecting people and Pokemon for their own amusement.

Phantussle.Pokedex Entry: Said to be the ghosts of fallen warriors, they rise from shadows caused by moonlight in order to spar with each other. When one is alone, it clones itself in order to have a capable partner.

Umbrawl.Pokedex Entry: Their shadows have minds of their own and can form whatever shapes that they want. They are said to deliver punches that can separate one's soul from their body.

Sizzabre.Pokedex Entry: They use their sharp fangs to catch and devour prey. If their fangs get dull, they sharpen them on rocks.

Vaarkin.Pokedex Entry: They roam deserts and plains, absorbing sunlight through their backs. They cook berries by heating them on their backs.

Sweltoad.Pokedex Entry: It loves basking in the rays of the sun. They get stronger by hopping around and burning trees and shrubs in forests.

Toadaze.Pokedex Entry: It runs around forests burning trees and bushes and eating the ashes. Its hands are hot enough to melt concrete.

Taikin.Pokedex Entry: It creates numerous fireballs that can dry areas that have experienced numerous floods. It leaves fiery footprints in its wake.

Jersinge.Pokedex Entry: The stripe on their heads glow when they use Fire-type moves. Their wings allow it to fly short distances, allowing them to attack from above.

Bursinge.Pokedex Entry: It loves to laugh at the misery of others. It is said that their flames can never be extinguished and will burn hotter and hotter.

Buranda.Pokedex Entry: These cute Pokemon run and play in forests. Their tails are naturally dormant and will ignite when they are excited or frightened.

Ailite.Pokedex Entry: Sometimes people use their flames for major worldwide sporting events. They can launch the ends of their tails at their enemies in order to immobilize them.

Blazesta.Pokedex Entry: When angered, their tails give off heat that is 10x hotter than surface of the sun. It is said that their flames can melt the skin off of bone in an instant.

Penneswel.Pokedex Entry: The females of this species of Pokemon are known to be more attractive because of their fur, making them targets for hunters. The males will always try to protect the females from harm.

Lagomelt.Pokedex Entry: The males of this species are very defensive and protective, but can be known to have a sweet, mischievous side. The females use their beauty in order to manipulate the males into doing what they want.

Harupt.Pokedex Entry: The females' fluffy fur is very durable and comfortable in order to protect their young. The males are extremely violent and will attack anyone who approaches its territory.

Coalidi.Pokedex Entry: They always given their full effort in battle, not backing down until completely exhausted. The angrier they are, the stronger their flames are.

Kazanogi.Pokedex Entry: Born from the lava of a now dormant volcano, its entire body is as hot as the sun. When it is very angry, it will erupt lava from the retractable volcano on its back.

Sukstion.Pokedex Entry: Using their hands and feet, they race to the tops of large buildings to determine who is the fastest. They are able to move and spy on others in silence.

Ignerate.Pokedex Entry: They are able to zip around in the form of a fireball to frighten passersby. Their fur is naturally white, but turns reddish-orange when they are older.

Walpyre.Pokedex Entry: Its back and neck are able to erupt with lava when WALPYRE are upset. They sleep in groups in order to keep their body temperatures up.

Pyroti.Pokedex Entry: They absorb different fire-type moves in order to strengthen its own power. The fire and lava in its body erupt from different parts of its body.

Myrmolten.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies can absorb any fire-type and convert it into extra energy for its own attack. The lava in its body is very unique because of its color, but also because it is hotter and has toxins in it.

Cupcon.Pokedex Entry: The fire on its head can never be extinguished. A Cupcon was once a suspect in case in which a fire claimed the lives of twenty people in an apartment complex.

Magama.Pokedex Entry: Its entire body is composed mostly of magma, allowing it to melt into puddles and move swiftly. These Pokemon are often found in caves alongside volcanoes.

Agamelt.Pokedex Entry: A special gas produced by its body causes its flames and magma comprised body to turn blue. It is able to melt anything just by grabbing it.

Duikin.Pokedex Entry: Inhaling smoke from its tail causes you to feel valuable and beautiful. It is rare, but you may see a newborn DUIKIN float slightly for five seconds before dropping softly.

Kindelo.Pokedex Entry: The smoke that emanates from their tails and horns from the flames can soothe those who are feeling stressed or angry. It can engulf itself in flames and teleport from one place to another.

Tungshon.Pokedex Entry: They use their long, hot tongues to extract bugs from trees and holes in the ground. You may sometimes see them sneaking into Sticute dens in order to steal their honey.

Voraciun.Pokedex Entry: Its drool is partially composed of magma, giving it the ability to eat nearly anything. One must be wary when in a Voraciun's territory, as one bite from them can result in severe burns.

Choprowl.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon leaves a trail of blazing footprints wherever it goes, leaving a shock for those who find them. It is said to have helped in the of the concept of understanding and learning by using the sound of its muzzle and tail's swipes.

Balmox.Pokedex Entry: They are extremely playful Pokemon who take interest in even the smallest of things. Smoke comes out of its horns when it is scared or upset.

Warmild.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are known for their tasty odor and their usage with chefs. Its wings are unable to help it fly, so instead it uses them to make foods mildly spicy.

Fuegold.Pokedex Entry: Fuegold are usually caught and used by chefs to enhance the flavors of dishes. Their feathers can be used to create delicious spices and sauces.

Shelight.Pokedex Entry: They love to eat embers and charcoal. Their tough shells can help it repel water and rocks, keeping its soft body safe.

Ignishell.Pokedex Entry: Their shells act as lanterns as they glow in the dark. Almost anything that they touch melts instantly.

Aspyre.Pokedex Entry: Its tail can ignite because of the friction from its smoke-like skin. Their flames have toxic ingredients inside of them that can cause harsh poisoning.

Sukshine.Pokedex Entry: Using their suction-cupped fingers, they stick to walls and ceilings with ease. The spots on its body generate intense heat.

Frisun.Pokedex Entry: They absorb sunlight by staring at the sun. Their frills are hot to the touch and extend as blades.

Solarize.Pokedex Entry: They are able to see opponents' heat signatures in order to attack in the right direction. They absorb sunlight in their tails and frills.

Crebusola.Pokedex Entry: When their frills are full of energy, they smoke and flash, signalling that they are ready to attack Their breath is hot enough to evaporate one's body fluids.

Charial.Pokedex Entry: To disorientate their prey and opponents, they release smoke from their nostrils. If the smoke surrounding its eyes begin to dissipate, it means that it is close to dying.

Whelpyre.Pokedex Entry: When it encounters humans or Pokemon that are larger than itself, it immediately tries to flee in fright. They spit embers at each other playfully when they are bored.

Infernote.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon have a burning passion to fight and can unleash a flurry of fiery punches in seconds. They have a very quick-temper and will risk others' lives in order to fight.

Magmaw.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's saliva is comprised of 99% molten lava, allowing it to easily devour whatever it wants with ease. They unintentionally cause fires when they venture away from their habitats due to their constant drooling.

Salava.Pokedex Entry: Their drool is able to cause anything it touches to spontaneously combust. Their strong jaws are able to crush and melt a dump truck simultaneously.

Abolm.Pokedex Entry: The red sap that expels from its head is very warm and is known to treat hypothermia. It spends most of its time buried near the bases of volcanoes.

Caliboom.Pokedex Entry: It drips off a mixture of a white and red ooze from around the rim of its cap that can be used to treat colds. They usually stay in one place for their entire lives, only moving if the ground underneath it or it, itself, is moved.

Turtorch.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon release harsh flames from their shells to defend themselves. People and Pokemon often end up stepping on them when they enter their territory, earning them a Flamethrower to the back.

Fahrenheat.Pokedex Entry: Its long neck allows it to grab and roast fruit from tall trees. Its shell is extremely hot and can reach temperatures of over 500,000 degrees.

Prismara.Pokedex Entry: When light hits its body, it absorbs it and fires a colored beam towards its enemies. Its body radiates heat when it has absorbed a vast amount of light into its body.

Elephlint.Pokedex Entry: It is able to entertain itself by watching the smoke it exhales, as it able to see things in it that no other people or Pokemon can. Their bodies turn brown when they are very sick.

Dermyst.Pokedex Entry: By staring into its flames, it is able to predict what will happen in the future. Its flames are able to keep burning even when it is raining.

Coonferno.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon's internal flame sac allow it to breathe flames at more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit. They spend most of their time burning trash cans and small trees for fun.

Coonflagra.Pokedex Entry: They hardly ever leave from the caves in which they live, as they are mostly content when alone. When they do leave their caves, they usually cause a massive heat wave to spread across the environment in which they are in because of their mobility.

Bursten.Pokedex Entry: They always fly around while rotating with their tentacles outwards. They are able to form high temperature fireballs using their intense body heat.

Manowrath.Pokedex Entry: Being grabbed by its tentacles gives you an intense burn on that part of your body. It is able to retract its tentacles and take the shape of a large fireball before zooming around at high speeds.

Lutred.Pokedex Entry: These rowdy Pokemon are known to spit embers towards anything they are curious about. Groups of them have been discovered watching thunderclouds from their dens.

Barafusa.Pokedex Entry: All of its organs are comprised of lava, allowing it to eat as much as it wants without getting sick. Its tail acts as a bright light to guide it at night, as it dislikes dark places.

Infernaut.Pokedex Entry: Its entire body radiates intense heat due to its internal organs' composition. A person is able to get third degree burns from the heat of its breath alone.

Charret.Pokedex Entry: Charret live in groups of up to twelve; they despise being alone. More often than not, they are found digging up old graves and gnawing on remains.

Vormelta.Pokedex Entry: Its body is covered in a flammable, waxy substance that allows it to burst into flames at any given moment. They are able to melt into a liquid state in order to ambush confused enemies.

Tititorch.Pokedex Entry: Tititorch travel in groups of ten and live in caves hidden in dense forests. You can tell the age of a Tititorch by the length of the fur around its head and how brightly the tip of its tail glows in the darkness; the brighter the tail glows, the older it is.

Warmoset.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are known to be great with children, so great that parents usually catch one and leave it to watch their children while they're away. Warmoset is a very friendly and compassionate Pokemon, always wanting to hug any new people and Pokemon that it sees.

Saburn.Pokedex Entry: It has a violent temper and will lash out at anything that approaches it. If they lose a tooth, it will return within 24 hours.

Blazabre.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are sometimes called the Devil's Pet because of their bad temper and high temperature flames. If this Pokemon burns you, the burn will last forever.

Arsonite.Pokedex Entry: According to folklore, if a person dies, an ARSONITE will burn the body, but leave the soul for its consumption. It loves the screams of agony it causes when it burns a human, knowing that its flames' burn will never go away.

Hawte.Pokedex Entry: Its molted feathers are made into beautiful clothing. They are very combative at birth and always confident in their abilities despite their weaknesses.

Valiame.Pokedex Entry: As it flies, its fiery feathers sometimes fall out, but are immediately replaced by new ones. By flapping its wings, it can cause a massive heat wave that can reduce anything to ash in a matter of seconds.

Frostoala.Pokedex Entry: If they have a weak trainer, they will be disobedient, prompting most trainers to release them. To torture its enemies, it will make a cold environment, and then burn them to give them an intense scalding feeling over their bodies.

Pyoreala.Pokedex Entry: It will only listen to a strong and experienced trainer, which is worth it because of its power. It half freezes an enemy and watches in amusement as they endure the cold shock before incinerating them with its flames.

Flaemark.Pokedex Entry: It is said to be the ghost of a man who was cremated while still alive. It will roll into enemies and burn them with its 200,000° flames, reducing them to ash.

Wyburn.Pokedex Entry: It grows angry and sad whenever it loses a battle, so it trains extremely hard. Their wings are full of magma, so whenever they flap them, there is nothing but hot air.

Vernace.Pokedex Entry: Their wings are very blunt and able to give off extreme levels of heat. They train hard near active volcanoes to build up their strength.

Lavyrn.Pokedex Entry: Their wings are made out of lava, so they are able to melt anything that makes contact with them. They are able to blast out 257,000 degrees of flame from their maws.

Blazoom.Pokedex Entry: They wait motionlessly until someone approaches it, then it bursts into flames to frighten them. They will chase their victims into exhaustion and then burn them by tackling them.

Singero.Pokedex Entry: They ignite the flames on their backs when they sense people near them. They will cause confusion and blindness if you stare in their flames, then they burn down the area around you while you're still inside.

Achenwy.Pokedex Entry: They explode when they are frightened or excited about something. They are usually found on the nights of holidays.

Gundrukae.Pokedex Entry: Known to be the most rambunctious of the beasts, Gundrukae forces different scents onto different pieces of land. The exotic odor of its fur made it irresistible, making it the most sought after of the three beasts.

Rufure.Pokedex Entry: It lives inside of the Earth's core, absorbing the heat into its body in order to become stronger. There was once a cult that dedicated their time to digging to the Earth's core in order to catch this Pokemon, but nearly all of the members perished.

Loriza.Pokedex Entry: It ignites the flames on its wings to do major burn damage. Its feathers are always hot, so people use them to make sweaters and coats.

Blazary.Pokedex Entry: It controls the flames on its wings with ease. Their feathers are used to make winter coats on occasion.

Dolphlame.Pokedex Entry: They spend most of their time underground, creating small dens filled with magma in which they can live. Flames erupt from its blowhole when it is excited.

Bulleve.Pokedex Entry: It ignites the star on its forehead in order to engulf itself in flames. It is said that they are able to launch a human so high with so much force that you may hit the moon, though no one has dared to test it.

Duithikal.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon charge and gallop on air, releasing a sweet odor as their flames burn. They can turn into smoke and move freely to get into different areas that are sometimes restricted.

Whalit.Pokedex Entry: They are said to be the cause of massive earthquakes that plague the Marva Region. Whalit typically reside in volcanos, causing eruptions by constantly breaching.

Bullorch.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon always mean business when it comes to battling. It is able to make an entire lake evaporate by releasing smoke from its horns.

Freylter.Pokedex Entry: To help itself power up, it dries up entire environments so that its opponents feel dreary and hot. It staff releases fire when it senses an environment that is too moist.

Volcanail.Pokedex Entry: They withdraw into their shells to sleep, but they let out a very bright light as they do so. Their bodies are extremely hot and can melt flesh from the bones of humans if they make contact.

Hissinge.Pokedex Entry: They can ignite the smoke stored in its underbelly, giving it a more intense appearance. All of their flames come out in a serpentine fashion and can actually cause poisoning.

Vipyro.Pokedex Entry: They are able to ignite their entire underbellies and blast intense toxic flames from their tails and mouths. This Pokemon can cause one's entire body to combust from the inside out with a single bite.

Vividon.Pokedex Entry: The icy growths on their backs absorb heat, giving the appearance of a rainbow. They are able to completely change a human or Pokemon's color.

Rialaze.Pokedex Entry: By shrouding itself in smoke, it is able to evade numerous attacks. Their internal fire must keep burning or else they will die.

Flessol.Pokedex Entry: Their saliva contains toxins that are able to melt away skin. Those who are bitten by this Pokemon experience intense pain as their own skin essentially melts off and is replaced by a patch of dry, scaly skin.

Bodissol.Pokedex Entry: Their saliva dissolves anything it touches. Pieces of its body occasionally chip and fall off, unable to handle the toxins in its body

Bubboil.Pokedex Entry: It is able to drink any type of water and boil it, making it healthy for it. They are able to boil water by releasing heat from its body in bodies of water.

Boilake.Pokedex Entry: With a touch of one of its claws, it can cause an entire lake to boil. They drink a large amount of boiling water in order to keep themselves powered up.

Vulcanient.Pokedex Entry: Its ears can emit psychic pulses that can enchant any object within a 50 mile radius. It creates intense fireballs in the palms of its hands that can never be extinguished.

Coondle.Pokedex Entry: When this Pokemon is excited, it gives off small embers from its tail. They are relatively social Pokemon that are known to cause mischief every once in a while.

Schnizzle.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon reside near volcanoes eating lava and ash. Their large noses hold a lot of magma and once they attack, they leak lava.

Wisinge.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon is able to control the movements and attacks of others by waving its arms. The orbs on its body amplify its power.

Scorchoe.Pokedex Entry: It appears in Saigo-region myth as a destroyer of forests and crops. Its flames are able to incinerate almost anything in mere seconds.

Phlogusnoa.Pokedex Entry: It has been known to incinerate bodies in graveyards and absorb the souls into its body. When it is ready to attack, its lower body immediately ignites. The flames surrounding its body are said to be fueled by the souls that it burns.

Geckore.Pokedex Entry: They are considered to be bad omens by many. Groups of them are known to raid nests and cook the eggs they find before eating them.

Geckrim.Pokedex Entry: They steal eggs and berries from different habitats in order to eat them burnt. They exhale smoke in order to make quick getaways.

Muertecko.Pokedex Entry: They are very cruel Pokemon that take pleasure in setting things on fire for their own amusement. There was once an incident in which a group of them set an apartment complex on fire.

Pyorpse.Pokedex Entry: Pyorpse are said to frequent graveyards, digging up the bodies of those who had done malicious things, and taking them to the spirit world. They are often used to help in the process of cremating bodies.

Necropyre.Pokedex Entry: They carry the bodies of the recently deceased in their tails before disappearing to the spirit world. If they are tasked with carrying more than one body, they create a platform of fire to hold them on.

Mureti.Pokedex Entry: Said to be a symbol of rebirth and longevity, this Pokemon has been worshiped for centuries. Those who are in possession of its ashes are said to be given the power to bring the deceased back to life.

Peppaur.Pokedex Entry: Its body sweats out spicy juices when it gets tired. Its flames are extremely hot and are almost the same temperature as the sun.

Wispur.Pokedex Entry: Its flame is so intense that it is confined to a jar. If opened, WISPUR will burn the spirit of the person or Pokemon who opened it as fuel for its flame.

Wisphlare.Pokedex Entry: The heat of its flame has caused its jar to crack and expand, allowing the fire to escape. It is able to burn an entire body to pieces while also stealing the soul of the person it kills.

Flarispur.Pokedex Entry: Because it was confined so long inside of it, its body is unable to leave through the opening. Its six flaming arms can absorb a human's body and burn them from the inside out, feeding on its soul's pain and agony...

Metaurost.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are covered in a bronze coating that is able to repel attacks. They each have an internal flame in their chests that can melt anything in a matter of seconds.

Hurchin.Pokedex Entry: If you step on one of its spikes, which are full of poison, it will not only burn, but leave a permanent scar on your foot. This Pokemon's spikes are very hot despite it living underwater.

Urchar.Pokedex Entry: If you were to step on one of these Pokemon's spikes, your foot would melt from the inside out. When flames erupt from the ends of their spikes underwater, it means that they are about to explode.

Kindlyth.Pokedex Entry: KINDLYTH are highly territorial and will attack anything that invades its territory. Their high temperature flames can be compared to that of a volcano.

Cerberok.Pokedex Entry: They are extremely aggressive, attack anything that they see moving. Each head has a brain and a different personality, but they all do the same thing.

Martal.Pokedex Entry: MARTAL's hands are able to be set ablaze to help it in battles. It hates intimidation and will always lunge at enemies that anger it.

Flammapple.Pokedex Entry: The flames that erupt from FLAMMAPPLE's body resemble leaves, fooling many people who encounter them. Their bodies are hollow, but can still pack an explosive charge when these Pokemon are startled.

Peachar.Pokedex Entry: Its able to envelop its body in its green flame if humans get too close. The fuzz on its body can get stuck to your body and will cause a burning sensation on the skin within twenty minutes.

Pyrear.Pokedex Entry: It explodes when it is frightened. Pokemon and humans who attempt to eat it end up getting a very unpleasant surprise.

Pyrapt.Pokedex Entry: The heat from its fur can roast berries and meat. Its flames could melt the rocks of caves.

Raptoast.Pokedex Entry: It was the cause of many fires over 100 million years ago. It ran at a speed of 126 mph and slashed prey with its long nails.

Flamur.Pokedex Entry: The flames they breathe are black and will destroy anything that it touches. Groups of them sometimes charge into small towns and burn everything around it.

Bealzuburn.Pokedex Entry: Their black flames can incinerate an entire forest in seconds. They always appear during times of strife to make everything worse.

Oblimodor.Pokedex Entry: Its dark flames incinerate anything they touch. It is widely feared because of its evil tendencies.

Zinchar.Pokedex Entry: When they are first born, their bodies are a pale yellow and as they grow, the lava in their body begins to spread throughout it, giving it its red coloration. The bodies are 85 percent steel, but the lava makes trainers think that it is composed of magma.

Blazinc.Pokedex Entry: They are sometimes used to incinerate trash or dead bodies for cremation. Their bodies can reduce flesh to ash.

Titanius.Pokedex Entry: Their body temperatures can reach 800,000 °F when they are furious. The metal outside of its body cannot be melted.

Tephlare.Pokedex Entry: Tephlare have the power to sense the past and future by staring into fire. Their brains are somewhat larger than the average canine, making their senses and obedience better.

Esphlare.Pokedex Entry: Their brains allow them to speak to their trainers via telepathy. They hate being given too much attention and sometimes prefer to be alone to keep their concentration.

Maginax.Pokedex Entry: It has been said that these Pokemon were born when a volcano erupted more than 300 million years ago. Their spines were filled with magma that erupted into lava when they were excited.

Volcaniax.Pokedex Entry: They are said to be connected to volcanic eruptions that happened during the times that they were alive. When they were threatened, their backs erupted, scaring off their enemies.

Rusizzle.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are unable to melt because of the insulation in their skeleton. They can breathe out soot to act as a smokescreen.

Rodanador.Pokedex Entry: Found near active volcanoes, these Pokemon feed off of the fire and magma inside. Their flying technique is unique based on how much experience they have.

Danidor.Pokedex Entry: They live inside active volcanoes, feasting on the magma inside. When a volcano erupts, it is indicated that evolution is close.

Taidon.Pokedex Entry: They blast intense flames at their enemies, incinerating them in seconds. Their swift aerial mobility makes them a force to be reckoned with.

Pyrok.Pokedex Entry: Flames erupt without warning from the cracks in its body. The flames can reach over 30,000 degrees.

Infernore.Pokedex Entry: Flames erupt from their cracks, scaring people who see them as normal rocks. They reside in hot areas and absorb heat using their claws.

Holocore.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies never melt because the iron and nickel in its body is too packed up and insulated. The temperature of their bodies can reach well above 75,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

Piglutt.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are able to cook whatever they eat inside of their bodies, so they are able to eat almost anything without getting sick. Their iron bodies are unable to melt, no matter the temperature.

Hoglutt.Pokedex Entry: Chefs feed these Pokemon their ingredients in order for them to cook. The internal fire inside of their bodies can rise and lower depending on how their owners want the food.

Triggroup.Pokedex Entry: The numerous heads on its body each have their own personality and strength. By building up pressure in its body, it is able to blast itself high in the sky and keep flight until plummeting back to the ground.

Solarius.Pokedex Entry: It is said to have been born from the Sun. It appears in areas where the view of the sunrise is the clearest.

Lantomb.Pokedex Entry: It supposedly stated that these Pokemon's flames are actually the souls of the departed... With its one eye, it is able to see directly through you and know what you are thinking instantly.

Bursturn.Pokedex Entry: By staring into its flames, you are able to see the faces of those whose souls have been burned by them. They are able to see right through you and envelop you in flames immediately.

Fowlite.Pokedex Entry: They unleash small smoke clouds from their wings to hide themselves. These Pokemon are often the causes of fires around farms.

Consowl.Pokedex Entry: It appears during times of trouble to absorb the fear and anxiety in the air. The more pain and suffering it causes, the brighter its flames glow.

Apparowl.Pokedex Entry: With its fiery wings, it incinerates whatever it grabs onto. They have been known to torch major buildings and centers simply for the fun of it.

Colonite.Pokedex Entry: The six heads work together to propel their body into the air by increasing the heat inside. By adding more Triggroup, this Pokemon can extend its body more and more.

Kawan.Pokedex Entry: They only attack with smoke when they are born. Eating flowers allows their internal flames to burn harsher.

Flagaza.Pokedex Entry: They are almost always seen with Kawan by their side. Their horns are able to heat up and release high temperature flames when they sense that their young are in danger.

Sablast.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are very aggressive towards negative influences and will do anything in their power to eliminate them. They travel in groups of five to gather food for Flagaza and Kawan.

Steamee.Pokedex Entry: It boils water in is body, creating a large amount of steam that can envelop an entire area. It likes to eat hot objects.

Charboil.Pokedex Entry: The water in its body is quickly replenished after being evaporated into steam thanks to an organ in its body. Its steam is very thick and hard to see through, so it is able to sneak up on its opponents without difficulty.

Scorpine.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon love to singe pinecones and eat them whole. When threatened, its head spikes are able to stand up like needles.

Ashered.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon spent their time speeding through forests, trying to cause as much burn damage to the environment as possible. It eats the ashes of trees it burns.

Expelamell.Pokedex Entry: They release a highly flammable gas through their pores, allowing them to cause underwater explosions. Up to five of Expelamell can be a part of the same dirt patch.

Doomaka.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon's skin turns a dark gray and black when it is approached by humans. It opens its large mouth in order to suck out the souls of Pokemon and humans that disturb it.

Cumulite.Pokedex Entry: Millions of them fly around the skies on peaceful days. They are mainly responsible for all of the weather changes.

Darbat.Pokedex Entry: Its ears are able to absorb air and sound waves in order to charge its tail, which acts as a radar and sonar. It hides in the darkness of caves.

Nyctinar.Pokedex Entry: They use sonar to make their way around. Highly territorial, it uses its tail to communicate to all invaders, effectively scaring them out of the territory.

Patanoros.Pokedex Entry: It is able to keep away all storm clouds, but also allow them when they are needed for vegetation. It has helped protect Qiloh from hurricanes and tornadoes by devouring them.

Calfly.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are full of air, which allows them to fly in any direction that it wants to. They are very docile Pokemon that will not mind letting others ride on its back.

Bisoar.Pokedex Entry: Their fur makes them appear very fat and hairy, when they are actually very light. Its fur helps it deflect attacks extremely well and it is able to charge at extremely high speeds.

Colorota.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon sometimes bury themselves in lawns and let their pinwheels spin to energize them. It rotates very quickly, which can cause it to get dizzy and fly out of control.

Sorkune.Pokedex Entry: It can fly at 250 miles per second. It is able to break the sound barrier with a single flap of its wings.

Angelift.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are seen in the sky riding on clouds. They fly in a graceful fashion and are extremely friendly towards other Flying-types.

Skyte.Pokedex Entry: The refraction of its glossy tail gives it its vivid colors. These Pokemon are free spirits, gliding wherever the wind takes them.

Aerya.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's feathers can refract light, allowing them to either vanish or give off vivid colors. They have been known to dive bomb towards humans holding food.

Soarank.Pokedex Entry: It is nicknamed "The Flying Rainbow" because of its beautiful colors. It is often mistaken for a legendary because of its large size and great power.

Tezcapanas.Pokedex Entry: The levitating orb in his crescent-shaped crest is the main part of its body that allows its power to reach its full potential. It is able to change its color from black to blue depending on the time of day,in order to keep itself hidden.

Xipenagor.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is very intelligent and giving; it is able to spread a ray of light that will make any grassland or farmland prosper. It is known as "The Giver of Life" because of its magnificent ability to make dead plants, humans, and Pokemon come back to life.

Blowind.Pokedex Entry: Their fan-like tails are strong enough able to blow away a boulder. Oddly enough, they are sometimes able to defeat Fire-types with ease despite their weakness to them.

Windraft.Pokedex Entry: A professor once observed a trio of Windraft covering the opening of a volcano with ice with ease. They were formed by ice that was awakened by the radiation of the rising Sun.

Bravalia.Pokedex Entry: They are said to signify bravery. They appear to those who have shown tremendous courage.

Neswing.Pokedex Entry: Their chest patterns are known to faintly glow when they change directions. They have a very acute sense of direction and can easily navigate through the toughest of areas without needing an overhead view.

Cresouth.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon spend most of their time in frigid water, but can also fly on occasion. Their feathers are glossy, allowing them to move quickly across ice and through hailstorms.

Wiseast.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are very wise and one of the only ones that can actually communicate with humans. They have calm natures and will not fight unless threatened.

Westalon.Pokedex Entry: Very territorial and violent, these Pokemon attack whatever they see entering their territory. The spikes hidden in its wings deliver extra damage when it hits a target.

Wingur.Pokedex Entry: They scan the bottom of seas using the single light on their chests looking for food. They are often seen gracefully flying out of water for brief moments and into the air before dropping down abruptly.

Aeriurna.Pokedex Entry: Using their large fins, they illuminate their way through the deep sea. They are able to glide in short intervals in and out of water.

Ibice.Pokedex Entry: They tuck their wings into their deep feathers when not in flight to avoid frostbite. They sleep in groups of up to twenty with their legs buried in the snow.

Petu_Kuna.Pokedex Entry: The most heartless and savage of the 'Fiendish Four', it tears apart anything in its path. Retrieving a feather from its wings is said to fill one with devious thoughts.

Tweetum.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon flies at speeds of over 40 mph and skewers prey with its sharp beak. TWEETUM love to hum and sing and always travel looking for others, people and Pokemon alike, to serenade.

Dartum.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon can fly as fast as a jet. Its extremely sharp beak can reduce a boulder to gravel with just three pecks.

Hummidar.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon's beak can skewer straight through a boulder. It flies at Mach II speeds and pierces prey and enemies with its beak.

Nutchir.Pokedex Entry: For some odd reason, this Pokemon are hatched from nuts as opposed to eggs. Because their wings are merged with the nut they were hatched from, and they are not strong enough to fully break out of their shell, they keep them on for protection.

Wingorn.Pokedex Entry: It is able to retreat into its nut shell to defend itself and also camouflage itself. Its body parts have been freed, allowing it to fly and walk better.

Azuron.Pokedex Entry: Its glowing blue feathers have baffled scientists for centuries. AZURON are able to brighten an entire stadium by standing in one spot.

Toucaw.Pokedex Entry: It is nicknamed "The Flying Rainbow" because of its vivid feathers. They stand atop tall trees in order to get a better feel of their surroundings.

Macawlur.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are admired for their beautiful colored feathers. They are able to emit a bright light due to the glossiness of their feathers.

Salift.Pokedex Entry: By boiling water inside of its body, it is able to produce enough pressurized steam to fly. They ingest large amounts of water through their gills and burn it all inside to let it speed up while swimming.

Shiphlon.Pokedex Entry: They shoot out of water like rockets. Many of them have been discovered flying in outer space because their great speed and velocity.

Limbetaur.Pokedex Entry: They swing from branches and vines using their long tails. Their movements are so swift and graceful that they are nicknamed "The Grove Gymnasts."

Taurgile.Pokedex Entry: The seed in its tail has sprouted, giving it more agility. Its tail allows it to swing from tree branches, before it lets go and takes off with its larger wings.

Brevithe.Pokedex Entry: The flower at the end of its tail gives off wind that allows it to move quicker and precisely. Its fluent motions and agility as it leaps from branches cannot be matched by any other Pokemon.

Ruffeatz.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's colors vary depending on their location. The beautiful feathers they shed can be collected and used for many articles of clothing.

Quetzuff.Pokedex Entry: There are over 30 different known feather color patterns on QUETZUFF. When their feathery "hoods" start molting, it is sign that they are about to evolve.

Fethetz.Pokedex Entry: The "hood" it had as a RUFFETZ and QUETZUFF has molted off, giving it better sight and coordination. It molts its feathers once every month, and each time they change colors.

Belkin.Pokedex Entry: These playful bird Pokemon love to battle and will playfully wrestle on the surface of water. They use their beaks to crack Mollusym shells for food.

Ingorina.Pokedex Entry: Their beautiful movements can put anyone in a trance. They dance on the surface of water, with the one in the center being the leader.

Terove.Pokedex Entry: It flies over gardens and fields, shaking spores from its tail to help the plants grow. They enjoy planting flowers and have a euphoric feeling after they bloom.

Dactove.Pokedex Entry: It keeps seeds in its tail in order to plant flowers wherever they go. They do not need to eat, and instead photosynthesize using their tails to create food for themselves.

Meadactyl.Pokedex Entry: They guard fields and meadows, attacking anything that might hurt its plants. The spores in its tail can help a flower grow within seconds.

Sproket.Pokedex Entry: They were discovered by scientists in a mechanical engineering factory. Their bodies are not well structured, but they are still able to fly perfectly by adjusting the weight of their underdeveloped arm and leg.

Litekore.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies, now fully developed, allow it to travel at the speed of light. Its crest holds special coordinates that tell it where to go.

Gravoyle.Pokedex Entry: It perches itself atop buildings and treetops, watching whoever goes by. It occasionally goes by and attacks who it sees without a particular reason.

Hachubba.Pokedex Entry: Flocks of them gather during sunsets in order to find mates. It is said that if a trainer owns a Hachubba, it will cause the trainer or the trainer's other Pokemon to fall in love with the first thing that they see.

Amorver.Pokedex Entry: They are known to sense passion and love between individuals. The hearts on its wings beat like actual hearts when they stop moving.

Skwakiss.Pokedex Entry: Their hearts beat quicker when they are weak. It is said that if a Skwakiss pecks you, you will be blessed with eternal love.

Greakwine.Pokedex Entry: They are seen flying when rainbows are formed. They are able to run at high speeds when they are on land.

Pegasoar.Pokedex Entry: They are said to be able to gallop across rainbows. They are highly regarded because of their beauty.

Webbeak.Pokedex Entry: They splash water at fisherman that are in their territory for fun. They are able to fly underwater at high speeds.

Comoran.Pokedex Entry: They prank and anger fisherman by stealing their catches and tipping their boats. They are prone to losing feathers after emerging from water, but they grow back after a few days.

Nipper.Pokedex Entry: It has a sensitive part of its head that hates being in the cold environments it lives in, so it covers it with its ear. It creates ice crystals by blowing its breath.

Mimicaw.Pokedex Entry: Their special vocal chords allow them to mimic any sound that they hear, including human speech. Their tails allow them to adjust their tones.

Vocalyre.Pokedex Entry: Their tails flash based on the notes that they sing. They can screech loud enough to break multiple windows.

Allyring.Pokedex Entry: Their singing is considered a nuisance, as they sing for hours on end nonstop. They can mimic any sound that they hear almost perfectly.

Aerox.Pokedex Entry: They love to swoop around and scare those who enter their territory. They are very playful when they do not feel threatened.

Kitsoar.Pokedex Entry: They hide in the darkness of caves and frighten intruders by blinking light from the mark on its chest. They are very shy and independent Pokemon who live in caves to avoid contact.

Vixoar.Pokedex Entry: They pretend to be guides to travelers in caves, but they actually take them somewhere so that they are never seen again. By flashing their pink lights, they can take control of anyone's mind.

Protok.Pokedex Entry: Discovered in a landfill, these Pokemon are very naive and unstable. They crash and attack anything that they see for no real reason...

Dumboc.Pokedex Entry: They use the ear-like flaps on the side of its head to fly in the air. They are able to squeeze into the smallest of crevasses thanks to their squishy bodies.

Flapoct.Pokedex Entry: They use their flaps to glide and fly around in the air. They can rotate their bodies so fast that they can bore into concrete.

Monochrow.Pokedex Entry: They have the power to change its settings in which it lives by giving off a saturating aura. Monochrow normally hate anything vivid and colorful, so they immediately try to attack anything too bright.

Crowme.Pokedex Entry: They're known to gather together at midnight and give off eerie cries similar to baby's scream. When faced with a colorful Pokemon as an opponent, they will not stop trying to defeat it, and will continue to attack until its owner recalls it.

Glida.Pokedex Entry: It jumps off of the tops of trees and glides using its "wings". They love sitting on their trainer' shoulders to relax.

Sundark.Pokedex Entry: They love to eat sweet fruit to calm themselves when they are upset. They fly along air currents and can deliver devastating blows when they land.

Colugon.Pokedex Entry: They are known to steal food from townspeople in retaliation for taking their fruit. They are not social Pokemon, as they always steer clear of others.

Condont.Pokedex Entry: It flies in the dark of night in order to hunt for prey. They are able to move diligently and are quick to fight.

Buzzador.Pokedex Entry: They are known to devour unconscious humans and Pokemon while they are still alive. They make nests out of the remains of their victims.

Chironum.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are completely numb because their potent poison accidentally leaked into their skin cells. There was a case in which an explorer was bitten by this Pokemon, and over time, his entire body became paralyzed, eventually leading to his death.

Parafang.Pokedex Entry: Their poison is strong enough to eat through steel. There was once a story about how a PARAFANG caused the deaths of many because of its poison eating away at a building's support beams.

Thruss.Pokedex Entry: They use their skin to fly across vast distances. They lie in wait from high points before launching themselves toward unsuspecting prey.

Typuff.Pokedex Entry: They hang from the ceiling of caves and abandoned houses. If approached by humans, they tuck their wings into their fluff and pretend to be cotton balls.

Ghastlur.Pokedex Entry: They disappear and reappear instantly, frightening anyone who sees them. They let out a terrifying screech that is similar to a little girl's scream.

Chickling.Pokedex Entry: They are very curious Pokemon who always seem to find something to interest them. Their cute looks and nice personalities make them irresistible to nearly everyone they meet.

Henna.Pokedex Entry: They keep Chickling tucked in the fluffy feathers on their backs to protect them. They are motherly Pokemon who always care for ones with little experience.

Tarmin.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon love to play in snow and use their prehensile wings to throw snowballs at each other. They are able to see through snowstorms thank a special film covering their eyes.

Rotargan.Pokedex Entry: Because of their huge weight gain, they can barely fly more than 70 ft without taking at least one break. They spend most of their time asleep in snowy nests.

Blizzigan.Pokedex Entry: With one whip of its tail, it can cover an entire city in snow. They can disappear into the snow and reappear within the blink of an eye.

Windoink.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can only fly in short bursts, as their ear-like wings are underdeveloped. Their feathery tails help them steer around when in the air.

Aerihog.Pokedex Entry: Seeing a group of Aerihog flying is said to give someone good luck, as they don't take flight that often. Their fur is known to be very similar to feathers.

Kingribel.Pokedex Entry: Kingribel can walk on the surface of water to a desired location in order to fish with its tail. Their feathery tails have a hook-like bone that sticks out at the end, allowing them to lure fish Pokemon toward them for easy capture.

Rekkieh.Pokedex Entry: They terrorize towns and villages, destroying every building or structure that they see. Using their claws, they slash efficiently and fluently, determined to cause major damage.

Washion.Pokedex Entry: If faced with an opponent larger than itself, it will cower in fear and rush back to their trainer. These Pokemon have bad nerves and get scared very easily.

Dusbun.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon float around absorbing dust particles into their body. It is able to move its face around its body with ease, making it able to look in all directions to avoid certain danger.

Ladust.Pokedex Entry: They hop around and fly, leaving dust particles wherever they go. They move their faces wherever  they want on their body

Horizor.Pokedex Entry: When it takes flight, its wings scatter feathers that change colors. Its body disappears once in the sky and a rainbow strip appears in its place.

Chidrupe.Pokedex Entry: Their tails grow small berries on occasion when they are very happy. Their large ears help it get around, as their eyes are not very helpful.

Chiripe.Pokedex Entry: The berries on their tails can grow to be 10 lbs. each, occasionally weighing them when in flight. They are very confident and honorable Pokemon who like making their trainers proud.

Terosidon.Pokedex Entry: By letting out a special shriek, it can help with the growth of plants. They are very territorial and will immediately attack each other if together for too long.

Scorly.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's tails are full of poison that can cause a feeling of intoxication. The small wings on their backs allow them to fly in short bursts.

Gargor.Pokedex Entry: They mainly target the necks of humans to inject with poison. They are able to glide for long periods.

Mesagor.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are able to glow in the dark thanks to a special coating covering their bodies. They always aim for the faces of humans and opponents when it comes to attacking.

Trunibb.Pokedex Entry: They can create large holes in trees in order to use them as shelters. Their beaks can drill through concrete.

Woodrill.Pokedex Entry: Their wings can slice through bedrock with little difficulty. Their beaks can drill through the roofs of twenty cars cleanly.

Renice.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon love being alongside humans despite being in the wild for long periods of time. They have been known to have strange powers that even they don't know how to control.

Faeren.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are very knowledgeable and able to go to shops for their owners and buy items they need. They are very loyal and protective of their trainers.

Whimsiclaw.Pokedex Entry: Using mystical powers, they protect homes from intruders. They have the ability to share their powers with those who are in danger.

Fritox.Pokedex Entry: Their small wings barely offer them the ability to fly. Groups of them enjoy going around poisoning things.

Toxifrit.Pokedex Entry: Their legs are extremely toxic and just one touch can make someone extremely sick. When they flap their wings, they spread toxic particles.

Hoatch.Pokedex Entry: Their lower bodies give off a pungent odor when they are scared or stressed. They can't fly for long because their wings are still a bit underdeveloped.

Smellurk.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon cannot fly that well, as they have a serious lack of coordination. They help each other catch prey by releasing a horrible stench that drives prey out of their homes.

Odoraptor.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon emit an odor so pungent that they can curl noses from over 100 miles away. In a group, the one with the worst stench is considered the leader.

Comiwi.Pokedex Entry: The most common flying Pokemon in all of Ocramia, they establish friendships with everyone that they meet. They use their curved beaks to get at grubs that are in tight areas.

Iwing.Pokedex Entry: The fuzz that grows on their bodies is very sensitive. They use their beaks to drink honey out of Swidonery dens.

Terobite.Pokedex Entry: It is believed that this Pokemon actually enjoyed electricity and the current that went through it. They could not glide anywhere without falling at least twice or thrice.

Terowise.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon, despite their typing, loved electricity and were practically immune. They always flew into thunderstorms to absorb electricity, no matter how severe they were.

Derfus.Pokedex Entry: Despite their extremely low IQ, these Pokemon are very strong. When they are being beaten badly and their eyes both face forward, they are able to blast opponents over 200 ft away.

Paregal.Pokedex Entry: They are able to unleash a large wave of psychic energy capable of demolishing a tank. Highly intelligent Pokemon, their IQs are often compared to that of geniuses.

Chuter.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon use their frills to glide around. Popular with small children, these Pokemon enjoy playing games and hardly ever get tired.

Glysia.Pokedex Entry: By constantly flying, they kept their blood pressure at a neutral level. If they are unable to fly for a prolonged period of time, they grow extremely depressed.

Beakala.Pokedex Entry: It only flies during the night, moonlight giving it all of the energy that it needs. Its wings flicker brightly when it is under extreme stress.

Astara.Pokedex Entry: It is mainly nocturnal, hunting for prey in the dead of night while they are sleeping. It absorbs moonlight into its wings in order to strengthen itself.

Galapheza.Pokedex Entry: They are said to be able to fly into outer space with no trouble at all. They are able to make their bodies invisible so that only their colorful feathers are exposed.

Abdak.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are known to kidnap children and take them to caves, never to be seen again. They use their large noses to locate unseen figures in the dark.

Predakal.Pokedex Entry: They abduct adults and children while they're sleeping, bringing them to their lair to eat them. They hang upside down in caves in order to surprise intruders.

Snoturk.Pokedex Entry: They make small nests out of ice and frozen twigs. Their feathers are sold during the summer because they are always cold.

Winterkey.Pokedex Entry: Using their wispy feathers, they are able to drop the temperature to less than -700°. Keeping their wings tucked against the their chest provides them with comfort and protects their weak point.

Chansarima.Pokedex Entry: Clothing created by the feathers of this Pokemon can reach ludicrous prices due to the softness and rarity of them. It has been said that hanging one of Chansarima's feathers inside of a building brings good fortune to all who reside inside.

Creeklaw.Pokedex Entry: They attack in flocks of up to ten so that they always able to be backed up. They are mischievous, yet very focused workers.

Flapscal.Pokedex Entry: They spread their wings and feel air currents in order to locate water sources. Flocks of them are often seen stealing food from homes and shops.

Bagoul.Pokedex Entry: They fly around slowly, leaving dust-like spirit particles behind them. It was once reported that one of these Pokemon accidentally suffocated a child while playing with it.

Dancura.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon always preen their feathers and avoid getting dirty in order to look their best to attract mates. They always strut and show off their bodies to distract the opposing side while in battle.

Turashow.Pokedex Entry: They always put on shows in the springtime to attract mates. Their beauty comes from good hygiene and training.

Cresture.Pokedex Entry: Staring into its eyes is said to lay a curse on you. They fly without ever making a sound, making you unable to know when an attack is coming.

Clarmor.Pokedex Entry: They fly at speeds up to 100 mph, slicing the air around them. Covered in a tough armor, these Pokemon are able to block many hits and will sometimes even take attacks for others.

Strykrush.Pokedex Entry: Their beaks are able to chew through solid cinder blocks. The steel armor is able to absorb heat, making any fire related attacks useless.

Carimy.Pokedex Entry: It is unable to fly that well, so it usually relies on Caretorker to carry it everywhere. They are able to sense the emotions of others when they are picked up.

Caretorker.Pokedex Entry: They carry around Carimy and take care of them until they are able to evolve. Their feathers have healing properties that allow them to heal any ailment.

Vespoke.Pokedex Entry: It creates small ice crystals by flapping its wings rapidly. They are known to freeze small insects and eat them when they run out of berries to eat.

Giftigar.Pokedex Entry: Known as 'The Great Plague Bearer', this Pokemon is infamous for scattering its feathers across Renue, infecting all of the inhabitants with an awful sickness. Many people and Pokemon have fallen victim to its toxic feathers, losing their lives to this treacherous legendary.

Terusee.Pokedex Entry: Their feathers produce an oily substance that repels fluids. They often sit on trainers' heads in order to protect them during storms.

Enveilopt.Pokedex Entry: Their feathers fall out extremely often, so they are often collected in order to create waterproof clothing. Their eyes are often obstructed by their feathers, causing them to fly into buildings and trees unknowingly.

Brellurker.Pokedex Entry: They use their long tail feathers to cover themselves, and sometimes others, during harsh storms. Brellurker's waterproof feathers and tenacity allow it to fly through strong storms without a problem.

Nusole.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon have an odd fascination with shoes, and will go to extreme lengths in order to retrieve them. They often carry large leaves in their bills so that they are able to carry multiple shoes at a time.

Poshick.Pokedex Entry: Their feathers are extremely soft, and grow at a rapid rate, so trainers are advised to groom them often and style their feathers to keep them in check. There are often competitions held in Heiro centered around grooming the most stylish Poshick.

Squebble.Pokedex Entry: They are often found near rocky areas, pecking at different stones in order to find ones that they like the best. Squebble often fight amongst themselves if a group happens upon a rock that they all want.

Bouldevard.Pokedex Entry: Bouldevard decorate their feathery ruffs with rocks collected by Squebble. These Pokemon are considered extremely photogenic, making any pictures taken by them worth thousands.

Shrievil.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are found around graveyards during the ceremonial burying of a body. After seeing the body in the ground, it lets out a horrifying shriek of happiness.

Demariek.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon love sneaking behind people and Pokemon, shrieking, and making their victims jump. There was one case where a DEMARIEK was responsible for a heart attack inflicted on an elderly woman.

Spookie.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is said to be the formation of ghastly spirits that try to destroy lives. However, its sweet appearance and jolly personality leave scientists puzzled.

Enemigma.Pokedex Entry: It inhabits abandoned buildings and haunted houses, living in the darkness. It passes through people's bodies and steal their plasma from their body.

Scleros.Pokedex Entry: It hides in the shadows and stalks wanderers at night, stealing their life force as it stares at them until they are unable to continue moving. It is known to steal the eyes of dead and sometimes live humans.

Demeyes.Pokedex Entry: It stalks wandering humans at night, emitting a bright light on its chest to steal the victim's eyesight, leaving the permanently blind and unable to see where they are going. After stealing a victim's eyesight, it will still stalk them; and when the victim is asleep, it claws their eyeballs out and keeps them.

Googoust.Pokedex Entry: GOOGOUST is the result of a malevolent and frightening spirit possessing the body of an infant. When it is frightened, the spirit comes out of its mouth, putting the host body in a zombie-like state.

Kuselass.Pokedex Entry: KUSELASS are spirits of dead schoolgirls that met gruesome fates. They seek vengeance over themselves by following others at night and once close they are close enough, they attack.

Zashaunt.Pokedex Entry: They are said to be cared for children that changed into this Pokemon on the night of a full moon. They never leave the house they live in and enjoy frightening trespassers.

Baneffus.Pokedex Entry: After being left alone for centuries after the children that played with it grew up, this Pokemon became possessed by passing spirits, bringing it to life. It blinks the lights on its body to warn others to stay away, but it only brings more attention to itself, especially if there is a PUPRIEVE around.

Softite.Pokedex Entry: They use their tails to trip up people and Pokemon. They find themselves taking pleasure in wrapping smaller Pokemon in their tails until they stop moving.

Tapphan.Pokedex Entry: They stalk wary travelers, stepping right behind them to give them the sense of being followed. They stomp on sleeping trainers until they are unconscious before using their sharp teeth to devour their legs.

Stomphan.Pokedex Entry: They frighten lost travelers by following them, causing their anxiety to rise tremendously. Using their ears, they are able to increase their volume by expanding them, producing a louder sound.

Chirplump.Pokedex Entry: They absorb loud soundwaves into their bodies, which causes them to grow larger and larger. They have the power to freeze time, and whoever they want, in place.

Artrik.Pokedex Entry: They are known to ruin any work of art by inserting themselves into or onto it. They are very reckless and will bounce out of paintings or statues if one is not careful.

Hedread.Pokedex Entry: Its head is able to be detached from its body at any time, allowing it to travel faster. It has been said that it constricts those who dare to enter its territory without something of value.

Lebantro.Pokedex Entry: Lebantro has been said to lay a curse on those who speak its name. It is said that Lebantro's body is harboring two separate entities, one that controls its head and the other that controls its body.

Anelo.Pokedex Entry: It is said to represent the spirits of those who died alone. Unlike Ascilo, this Pokemon is always alone and avoids any and all contact unless it is in trouble.

Ascilo.Pokedex Entry: It is said to represent the spirits of those who died with many friends and good memories. They always group together with others of its kind and travel to an unknown location for days at a time.

Darkid.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are said to have arisen from the bodies of dead children. They follow travelers at night, slowly draining their energy until they collapse, allowing them to drag them into a shadow world.

Frishade.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon follow travelers at night and rise from the ground once they are exhausted to take them away. If you are ever wandering around at night, you may want to be careful, as FRISHADE may find and follow you, draining your energy while doing so.

Maskare.Pokedex Entry: A mask possessed by the spirit of the wearer who died in a battle, it is found in old museums. If one gets too close, these Pokemon may attach themselves to his or her face, the spirit going into the body of the new wearer.

Givid.Pokedex Entry: These disturbing Pokemon are the first known to give a choice of what it does to you. It is able to speak telepathically, asking whether you prefer its red or blue wing; if you choose the red, it drags you to the underworld, while if you choose the blue, it possesses you and stops your breathing.

Negoul.Pokedex Entry: They hide in the darkness of abandoned homes and buildings, waiting for men to arrive. Said to be the spirits of dead, lonely women, they stalk males at night, unnoticed.

Mademoir.Pokedex Entry: They are said to be the spirits of widowed women who committed suicide shortly after their husbands' deaths. They sit in the darkness and kidnap grown males, thinking that they are their husbands .

Ghomoh.Pokedex Entry: Said to be from another planet, these Pokemon are a must have for scientists. They are very curious Pokemon that often observe the behaviors of humans and other Pokemon in order to be the same as them.

Aurest.Pokedex Entry: Said to be incarnations of familial spirits, these Pokemon are often spoken of as myth. Visions of this Pokemon around cemeteries have been reported multiple times, but no evidence of its appearance has ever been found.

Hungroan.Pokedex Entry: The animated bodies of those who died of starvation, they wander around trying to eat any and everything. They have been known to steal food from restaurants and homes and devour it all in a single day.

Hungirth.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon have very limited normal movement, as their large weight makes it hard for it to move on foot. It is able to float up for a short period of time and can sometimes demolish floors by landing too hard.

Curswap.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon often pretend to be lost in the forest in order to get unsuspecting trainers to take them before they attack. Their visually dull teeth and claws are actually very sharp up close, so be careful.

Grimorte.Pokedex Entry: It appears in the shadows of children's bedrooms, frightening them by taking off its face. At night, they are able to enter the dreams of adults and children alike and drain them of their energy using their claws.

Casboo.Pokedex Entry: Unraveling the knots that contain its spirit is said to drain away life energy. They like to pop out in front of people and Pokemon, scaring them, but they are easily startled themselves.

Spectrace.Pokedex Entry: They have been known to grab people and devour them, making them a splotch of paint on their face. Their inky arms allow them to ruin any color.

Hauntrixx.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon reside around graveyards, devouring the dirt around coffins and corpses. On occasion they have been known to steal dead bodies and use different parts of them to scare those who are related to the victim.

Grovaunt.Pokedex Entry: They wander around forests and marshes, causing sadness all around. It is said that if you look into its eyes, you will be cursed with eternal torment.

Coltergeist.Pokedex Entry: They follow unsuspecting people and Pokemon, and once they stop, it lifts them onto its back and takes them to the spirit world. They gallop in silence, allowing their prey to stay calm before it attacks.

Phanteke.Pokedex Entry: It is said that it wanders haunted houses and museums, scaring anyone who comes into them at night. The spirits of those it has taken are what forms its mane.

Ecalpsim.Pokedex Entry: It came to life from a fortune teller's old rag doll. It lurks in haunted houses and is the cause of the weird occurrences that effect any, if not all, household objects.

Acored.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon came to life when a dead acorn was brought to life from the moon's X-rays. Its entire body is hollow; it is said that if you stare into an ACORED's body, your spirit vanishes forever.

Hollark.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are possessed by spirits of the dead. They stand motionless in forests waiting for others to walk by; they use their vines to leech the life energy of anyone who pass it by.

Hopo.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon came into existence when a rabbit died in a magician's hat during a magic act. It uses magical power in order to defend itself.

Pumkid.Pokedex Entry: They were born from the spirits of those killed on Halloween night. Each Halloween night, they roam cities looking for more victims in order to increase their species number.

Gourdaver.Pokedex Entry: It uses its three legs to stab trees and take their life force, making them die. Its creepy look and body gave it the nickname, The Grotesque Gourd.

Tiklok.Pokedex Entry: According to folklore, whenever the hands on its face strike midnight, a life is taken. It hangs on walls, pretending to be a clock, and frighten others that walk past it by rattling its pendulums.

Awteau.Pokedex Entry: Possessed by the spirits of engineers, these Pokemon build strange items and place them in palaces and museums. They cover their V-shaped eye hole and retract their arm and legs in order to make it appear as an artifact.

Damedge.Pokedex Entry: Sometimes, the spirit inside escapes through its eye hole to personally attack those who have angered it to a certain extent. It can change its claws and use them as tools to help fix broken machinery and make them even better.

Stablunt.Pokedex Entry: Over time, its armor's legs fell off, allowing the ghostly spirit inside to partially escape. It shoots metal shrapnel from its body to pierce its enemies.

Grovenge.Pokedex Entry: Over their sorrowful phases, they now seek vengeance on anything it sees. It knows the bad things trainers and Pokemon have done in the past and will hold it against them forever.

Ghasoft.Pokedex Entry: They reside in haunted houses as average pillows, but when they sense intruders, they come out of their dormant stage. Brought to life by the spirit of someone who was murdered via pillow, this Pokemon awkwardly seeks vengeance with poor results....
