Sofdurr.Pokedex Entry: The possessed being in its body has been trapped and has now moved to its tongue, adding to its ridiculous appearance. It is able to stun enemies with its tongue and swallow them, turning them into cotton for its body.

Soxite.Pokedex Entry: They spend their times in haunted houses, pretending to be simple toys. They are able to quickly rearrange items in homes and in the wild in order to either scare or confuse people.

Haunee.Pokedex Entry: Their flowers on their heads give off a stench that can make anyone miserable. Many trainers avoid this Pokemon at all costs.

Voodark.Pokedex Entry: By sticking pins in its head, it causes extreme pain to those within a 10 mile radius of it. The dark, disembodied soul that resides inside of its body always watches, making opponents wary and uneasy.

Creedoo.Pokedex Entry: They are said to steal and torture the souls of humans who find them. Once it is locked onto a victim, it will continue to puncture itself repeatedly, giving the victim excruciating pain.

Enalidire.Pokedex Entry: The dirt and sand that it creates can reduce trees to their stumps immediately. They devour anything and everything that it sees fit in order to make the world suffer, little by little.

Honko.Pokedex Entry: If you ever hear any honks or squeaks around you at night, you must be on high alert, as it is a sign that a Honko is nearby. Feeding off of the fear it causes, it is able to remove its head and emit a gas that causes it to be seen as your worst nightmare.

Trepidious.Pokedex Entry: Known as the emissary of fear and loathing, this Pokemon has terrified thousands in legend.

Kasabrell.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon's true appearance is so disturbing and horrendous that it keeps itself covered with an umbrella. A spirit whose original body was extremely disgusting, it attacks those who are seen as beautiful.

Zombew.Pokedex Entry: It has been experimented on and examined for over 50 years. This Pokemon is the first to show evidence of the ability to be dead and alive at the exact same time.

Fintom.Pokedex Entry: Fintom are extremely difficult to come across, as they often blend in the shadows of the deep extremely well. Those that come across Fintom are known to come down with a mysterious illness that has no cure.

Treaship.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon came to be when the spirit of a pirate possessed a treasure chest. Its body is left wide open, revealing the coin inside; if one tries to take it, it will bite down on the victim, severing their arm.

Shipwrath.Pokedex Entry: Full of the souls of those who died aboard it, these Pokemon are rightfully named "The Spirit Vessels". Those who board it unknowingly end up going missing, no matter where they are or who they're with.

Loquoll.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon appear in small bodies of water such as ponds and lakes, and sometimes in children's pools. They are very friendly towards all humans, especially children, as they will play with them until the children get tired.

Wavecto.Pokedex Entry: They emerge from water in a slow fashion, striking fear in those who see it when they are actually very kind. Their bodies are 85 percent water, allowing them to melt and blend into any liquid they come across.

Quollure.Pokedex Entry: When a thick fog appears to be surrounding a lake or pond, it is a sign that it is nearby... It imitates the sound of someone drowning, luring those brave enough to help towards itself; when they get close, it is said that they devour them whole and the fog gains a red tint.

Spicin.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is able to breathe fire and disintegrate at will. By touching or gnawing different foods, they cause a surge of extreme heat to enter them.

Caliuerte.Pokedex Entry: Eating food touched by this Pokemon will cause immediate death from overheating. After a person dies, it takes their body away and leaves a spirit that it will later burn for food.

Blankros.Pokedex Entry: It is said that the diamonds on its body hold the souls of those who it has killed with a single touch. When their diamonds glow, that means that a soul that it has collected is trying to escape.

Radiashroom.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon glow in the dark and spread tiny, deadly spores from the their tops. They are usually immobile when around humans, but if given the chance, they will hop onto them and poison them.

Toxiglow.Pokedex Entry: The mushrooms on its back are extremely toxic and eating them will result in immediate death. They often bury themselves underground and stay there, only letting their mushrooms be seen.

Creadiss.Pokedex Entry: A Legendary Pokemon that focuses on spirit and enchantment, it is believed to have created all life with its crest. It is often debated whether it or Felifevo has influenced the world more.

Sandalous.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon came to be when a spirit possessed an old sandal. With its surprisingly strong arms, it is able to rip the legs off of any person or Pokemon that unknowingly passes by it.

Dollure.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon often aid farmers by bringing good weather. They enjoy the sunshine, but always vanish when it rains or storms.

Petu_Konto.Pokedex Entry: It thrives by stirring up chaos and causing damage wherever it wanders. Its wings are comprised of a gas that causes mania in whoever breathes it in.

Bunnipalp.Pokedex Entry: It uses its rabbit-like head to lure unsuspecting people and Pokemon toward it in order to drain them of their life energy. Looking into its piercing red eyes is said to cause you to lose free will, with it taking control of your body.

Foobay.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are said to be the spirits of kids who died by drowning. It pretends to be in danger by flailing in water and, once someone is close, drags them down deep into the water, never to be seen again.

Maskoon.Pokedex Entry: Born without a face, these eerie Pokemon use masks to give the appearance of having a face. Legends say that if you are ever alone in an enclosed space with this Pokemon, it will steal your face and the mask it wears will become your own.

Tabex.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon pretends to be an ancient artifact in order to lure grave robbers; once they pick it up, the markings on its body glow and the person is cursed forever. The markings are different on each one; it is said that the markings are actually words that can release an evil spirit unto the world if it is read correctly.

Yureibb.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon haunts sandy areas, floating in place and just staring at a victim, causing paranoia. It seems to have no emotions, as it shows no pain from attacks and it never seems to do anything but stare into space.

Crustition.Pokedex Entry: It occupies old hermit shells and only comes out when disturbed. Trainers who have this Pokemon are said to have no emotions later on.

Spectrib.Pokedex Entry: Discovered in a cemetery, it is theorized that these Pokemon are the deformed skeletons of humans and Pokemon. Scientists have discovered that this Pokemon can survive even if it taken apart.

Ribone.Pokedex Entry: It is able to launch its body parts at enemies and immediately have it come back. The smoke around its body keeps it in check and without it, its body becomes nothing more than a pile of bones.

Flecto.Pokedex Entry: It terrorizes people by playing a terrible scene about them when they look into its face. They are known to be very mischievous.

Glassame.Pokedex Entry: It creates a scary illusion of anyone who looks at it by transforming into them. It is said to be from a parallel universe.

Doppetom.Pokedex Entry: It is widely feared by everyone and anyone who has encountered it. Said to be from a parallel universe, it takes residence in homes, particularly those in which children are present, and once they are close enough, it takes the child, never to be seen again.

Cursnow.Pokedex Entry: It is able to possess humans and do whatever they want to with their bodies, freezing their spirits in the process. Its slushy scarf can be placed over a victims mouth and nose in order to render them unconscious.

Angelug.Pokedex Entry: One of the most peaceful Ghost-types, they reside in small lakes and rivers. They try not to bother humans and will sometimes simply float in one place.

Halone.Pokedex Entry: They aimlessly float about in ponds and the ocean. Their hearts give off majority of their power, so their small 'hands' are extremely powerful.

Shrecho.Pokedex Entry: The spirits of singers, they screech nonstop once they have a captive audience. By bringing their arms closer to their mouths, their voices are amplified.

Pyrex.Pokedex Entry: They can grow and shrink as they please, enlarging the size of anyone that enters it. They sometimes devour those that get too close to it, leaving the bones that are seen inside.

Savenge.Pokedex Entry: They roam the deep sea and blind anything that sees their bright, red lights. For some odd reason, it evolves from Piravage when it sees bright light.

Wasepach.Pokedex Entry: It battles against Minsurro savagely over control of Zinco every ten years. Its body is full of a strange mist that overpowers all that inhale it.

Hiddark.Pokedex Entry: The ghosts of overworked miners, these Pokemon keep themselves hidden in the darkness of caves. Staring into glowing white eyes is said to cause nausea, which gives them the perfect time to strike.

Luminite.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon stalk trainers who enter caves that they used to work in, blinding them. They creep behind those who enter its cave territory and take them deep into the cave, never to be seen again...

Orgath.Pokedex Entry: In ancient times, these Pokemon collected the viscera of deceased humans and Pokemon in order to use them for energy. It was thought to have come to life when a wretched spirit occupied a jar used during embalming.

Grentrails.Pokedex Entry: These grim Pokemon used to steal the organs from people and Pokemon while they were sleeping. It is unknown how their species went extinct, but it thought that disease was a cause.

Camodasen.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon thrive by drinking and licking the dirt from the toilets, walls, and sinks in bathrooms. It does not appear before humans, but if a human does see it, it immediately vanishes out of embarrassment.

Boddyk.Pokedex Entry: It is said to have arisen from a discarded bottle that was possessed by an evil spirit. If someone grabs its body, it will immediately grab onto its holder's arm and steal their soul.

Necata.Pokedex Entry: When they expose their bony legs and spin their heads, it is said that a bizarre disaster or accident will befall you. They are said to be the causes of the disasters, but the true cause is unknown....

Vasoul.Pokedex Entry: Their stare can paralyze you, and while you are unable to move, it will steal your soul. The souls that erupt from its top can knock others out.

Biowale.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon live in depths 60,000 feet below sea level. The soul inside of its body glows a bright blue color to help navigate through the dark depths of the sea.

Walumine.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's souls emit a bright light throughout their body. Blue light pillars that are often seen emerging from the sea; those pillars are caused by this Pokemon.

Ghabell.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon came to life after a mischievous spirit possessed an old, cracked bell. These Pokemon silently follow those who unknowingly pass by them, their life force slowly draining as they continue walking. Once a victim has died, it will eerily let out a bell tone.

Tissimorte.Pokedex Entry: If you ever hear an eerie melody when you approach a pond or lake, it is likely these Pokemon attempting to revive dead spirits. They create vortexes in bodies of water with their songs that, if one gets trapped inside, drags them to the spirit realm.

Bearly.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon melt into the shadows of humans and Pokemon alike, waiting for the right moment to take everything that they have. They harass Wamoo frequently, always trying to kidnap them, but they fail miserably.

Goonite.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon reside in the mountains and blend in with the darkness of their caves in which they live. They knock out Wamoo and carry them to their dens, where they devour them while still alive.

Chimalgra.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon was created with the limbs of deceased Pokemon as a science project. They show little to no emotion and act very strangely when in large groups.

Navagra.Pokedex Entry: Its limbs have become much stronger and well-developed, making it a greater threat than once before. They were once contained in secret lab, but escaped and started reproducing, increasing their population.

Medex.Pokedex Entry: An artifact look alike that was stolen on a consistent basis by grave robbers, these Pokemon grew tired of human contact. If it is picked up, its ribbon wraps around the subject's head before absorbing them into its body, creating the marking seen on it.

Zumen.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon stalk unsuspecting travelers, showing strange and disturbing signs that cause unease. They feed off of the fear they cause when causing paranoia.

Snogo.Pokedex Entry: Snowy mountains are where these Pokemon usually reside. Said to be the ghosts of children who died of hypothermia, they can absorb heat in any given area, leaving the area extremely frigid.

Madafrost.Pokedex Entry: Snowy valleys are their domains. Legends say that this Pokemon was once a human mother that died looking for her lost child in the snowy mountains.

Timbegrave.Pokedex Entry: Constructed from wood over 10,000 years ago, these Pokemon serve as storage units for the souls of the deceased. They are often seen around grave sights, absorbing the souls from the departed before sitting at the head of their grave.

Jarous.Pokedex Entry: The physical body is always dormant, never disturbed by anything. If one gets close, purple fog will emerge from the body and attack those closest to it.

Cuboo.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon carries its bamboo everywhere so it will always have nourishment. The bamboo on its back grows back and provides the energy it needs to evolve.

Bulbloom.Pokedex Entry: BULBLOOM hang from trees, absorbing the nutrients. They inhabit gardens and help plants grow by poking them with its vine, sharing the nutrients that it gained.

Eftini.Pokedex Entry: They live in trees and use their tails and tongues to move from branch to branch. They hide in trees, as well as underground, if they're threatened.

Sireft.Pokedex Entry: They hang from trees to relax using their long tails. Their tails are strong enough to knock down trees.

Liskid.Pokedex Entry: They are able to run across the branches of trees with great speed and agility. It loves sunbathing.

Lisking.Pokedex Entry: It fires its black leaves out of its back like spikes. They are able to camouflage themselves in tall grass and sneak up on prey.

Honicras.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon's honey is extremely sticky and hard to get out of. It dangles from tree branches, drooling the sweet nectar on the ground in order to attract prey.

Drooluny.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon hangs from its lower body and sometimes its arms dripping honey on the ground. When prey gets close, it spits up a blob of honey, immobilizing it.

Dandeseed.Pokedex Entry: It loves letting the wind blow it around. It is a very docile and gentle Pokemon that loves to be around humans.

Fluffelion.Pokedex Entry: It scatters its fluff around fields in order for more Dandeseed to be born. It acts as a parent among a group.

Pastrub.Pokedex Entry: They bury themselves in the ground, disguised as everyday shrubs. They have a tendency to rest on people's heads because they enjoy the feeling of hair and stubble.

Krabbush.Pokedex Entry: It stands still with its head and claws tucked into its bushy back, disguising itself as a normal bush. They sometimes use their claws to mow long grass for berries.

Jouby.Pokedex Entry: Beloved by women, these little Pokemon are sometimes seen riding in purses. They love eating bitter berries and playing in wide open fields.

Jougrou.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon only eat berries that it deem worthy to be eaten. It uses Jouby to complete tasks for itself such as bathing, feeding, and grooming.

Galagrow.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are known for gathering berries for people they befriend. Groups of them compete to see who can gather the most items.

Leefril.Pokedex Entry: The leaf on each of their tails can release intense light. They use their leaf frills to absorb sunlight in order to charge up and heal itself.

Frilleave.Pokedex Entry: Their frills absorb sunlight so quickly that they can initiate a Solar Beam attack immediately. They charge at anything that angers them.

Starvine.Pokedex Entry: Their vine whip techniques are unmatched, as their vine tails have minds of their own. Sometimes, the tail will whip around and trip up the Pokemon itself.

Midmow.Pokedex Entry: They train themselves to command and use their vine tails professionally in order to strike. Its tails always eat the grass that surrounds it as it hunts for prey, making finding food difficult.

Enbush.Pokedex Entry: They sit in dense grassy areas and wait for unsuspected prey to come so it can attack with its tails. It blends in with its surroundings so well that it is called "The Walking Grassland".

Dinaut.Pokedex Entry: They crack coconuts and drink the fluid inside before using the shell as a helmet. If its coconut shell helmet is damaged, it loses its will to battle.

Bexer.Pokedex Entry: As soon as it is born, it is able to photosynthesize with the single leaf on its neck. Their hooves can fire seeds at high speeds.

Foresire.Pokedex Entry: Owned by a king, this Pokemon was released when he died. They inhabit forests and act as rulers.

Agavaga.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon was considered sacred in past centuries for its unique appearance and techniques when it was discovered battling in the desert. If threatened, it jumps up and launches its sharp leaves while twirling.

Foliaffe.Pokedex Entry: They stretch their necks in order to get berries from high branches. Their bodies have great camouflage, allowing it to avoid predators easily.

Groveck.Pokedex Entry: They can extend their necks to reach higher tree branches. When a female finds a suitable mate, its leaves fall off, leaving it bare.

Cuberry.Pokedex Entry: Its body gives off a sweet, fruity scent. They love to wander in gardens and eat the fruit they find, which will immediately grow back thanks to its nutrient filled saliva.

Berroar.Pokedex Entry: They help gardeners plant fruits by gnawing on them. Despite their hostile appearance, they are very gentle and will give off a sweet scent that is able to calm people down.

Chimerry.Pokedex Entry: Their roars are able to make fruits and vegetables grow faster. Their tails grow delicious berries that can grow back if they are removed.

Seedling.Pokedex Entry: They bury themselves into the ground in order to allow their sprout to receive sunlight, They close and open their heads when they want to have fun and get water.

Floraline.Pokedex Entry: They dance when they are very healthy. They have been known to bathe in mountain springs and disappear at night.

Shrubur.Pokedex Entry: There are Shrubur that have different flowers and sometimes fruit growing from their tails. When it appears, it can make multiple flowers bloom.

Shrubria.Pokedex Entry: Its grassy back helps it generate energy via photosynthesis. It can harden the grass on its back, like spikes.

Prophege.Pokedex Entry: It wields a very mythical power that makes it able to control plants. Edible berries grow from its tail and shoulders from time to time.

Cornwol.Pokedex Entry: They hang from tree branches, sharing the nutrients the tree has. After capture, they sometimes disappear from their trainer's pokeball if they are not thoroughly attended to.

Kumizar.Pokedex Entry: This friendly Pokemon is very affectionate, always jumping onto those it calls friends. However, it does not realize that its spikes cause pain, causing trainers to avoid making it happy.

Kiwanon.Pokedex Entry: They retract into their bodies and roll into their opponents to knock them out. They always try their hardest to make friends and be friendly, but they always ends up unintentionally harming others.

Wilthy.Pokedex Entry: Wilthy take pleasure in tripping humans that walk by it unknowingly. Their leaves are very strong and are unable to be torn or cut.

Succuisk.Pokedex Entry: Its discarded spikes are often used in acupuncture in order to break language barriers for those who wish to learn more. It launches its spikes when it grows irritated.

Seedrake.Pokedex Entry: Its tail absorbs sunlight, turning it into both food and electricity for its body. The electricity in its blood causes its grass to stand on end, like spikes.

Candew.Pokedex Entry: The sap produced by these Pokemon is extremely sticky. The sap they produce is able to stick two cars together and keep them together.

Drostuck.Pokedex Entry: Their sap can be used as an industrial adhesive, being able to stick concrete together with ease. If one is not careful, he or she can end up getting stuck and unable to move.

Pebblith.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon appear to be simple pebbles, but they are actually soft plants. They live in mountainous areas, pretending to be rocks as they absorb energy from other rocks.

Feyolk.Pokedex Entry: Because of its egg-like appearance, it is often mistaken for a snack. The vine on its head can tangle you and leave you tangled for up to three days.

Traplant.Pokedex Entry: Their large branches are often used to trap unsuspecting people and Pokemon for their pleasure. Despite their friendly appearance, these Pokemon are very cruel, sometimes keeping humans captive for weeks at a time.

Snaravine.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon use their long, sharp legs to stab and drain those who get trapped in its tangles. You are advised to avoid these Pokemon at all costs, because there is a large chance that you may never be heard from again.

Weaki.Pokedex Entry: One of the weakest Grass-type Pokemon, they often keep to themselves and avoid human contact. The sensitive fuzz on their bodies help them sense incoming dangers.

Coltivus.Pokedex Entry: Their leaves are edible and promote healthy growth. They use their root-like feet to drain nutrients from the soil.

Joern.Pokedex Entry: They usually stay in trees until they're fully evolved. Their leafy tails can give off spores that put you to sleep.

Sprigaroo.Pokedex Entry: They are very hostile Pokemon who travel in groups of 5 to 6 to find food. Their strong legs allow them to hop as high as 678 ft.

Yenoh.Pokedex Entry: They are always seen inside of honey-covered plants. Their extremely small bodies are durable enough to withstand an explosion.

Sweetyke.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies give off a sweet and spicy aroma that can attract any Pokemon. Their spices are often harvested by chefs.

Belladino.Pokedex Entry: The berries around its neck vary in taste based on its mood. It stalks its prey in silence before hitting them with a barrage of its berries.

Atrepta.Pokedex Entry: Its body secretes a poisonous sweat that seeps into the berries on its body. Getting hit by one of its berries causes convulsions that eventually lead to death without immediate treatment.

Lilypond.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon reside in lakes and ponds, eating sediment around it. Despite its small size, it is able to carry Pokemon larger than itself across bodies of water without trouble.

Nelumboat.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's lilypads vary in size and shape, making the amount of Pokemon or people they are able to carry change. Its leaves never droop and are very resilient.

Cropsoil.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon survive by eating dirt and seeds from other, larger trees. When more leaves appear on its arms, it means that it is close to evolving.

Verdagrow.Pokedex Entry: They survive by embedding their roots into the trunks of fully grown trees and draining them, converting it into electricity. The leaves on its arms and tail are strange, as they are able conduct electricity.

Galeaf.Pokedex Entry: They attack by using leaves close to them as blades. They eat bitter fruit and small insects to keep themselves healthy.

Jutsco.Pokedex Entry: They construct fans made of leaves and sticks in order to defend themselves. They practice different techniques and hone their skills in order to become stronger in battles.

Cornall.Pokedex Entry: These tiny Pokemon use their small leaf-like arms to float off of the ground in short bursts. They usually stay underground and eat soil with their hair-like leaves sticking out of the ground.

Miracorn.Pokedex Entry: Resembling corn cobs, these Pokemon are often accidentally captured while sleeping in fields. They protect themselves with their leaves, which are said to be as strong as tempered steel.

Rusour.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are often seen marching back and forth from their colonies' home. They spray an extremely sour substance from their mouths that can stop any Pokemon, no matter the size.

Cactar.Pokedex Entry: The wander deserts, greeting travelers with their presence and acting as temporary companions. It enjoys dry, hot environments and are often seen tucked in the ground with their five vines sprouted slightly.

Cactusar.Pokedex Entry: Using their three vines, they search their desert homes for nutrients. Due to their large size, they sometimes allow travelers going through the desert to ride on their backs; their vines can fashion as a soft cushion for them.

Stingar.Pokedex Entry: Their leaves are covered in tiny toxic spines that cause a stinging sensation that lasts for 24 hours. At night, they lay on trees to regain their strength.

Nettwist.Pokedex Entry: The vines surrounding it control what it does all of the time. Getting touched or bitten by one of these Pokemon will cause a stinging sensation that will last for up to ten years.

Kitnip.Pokedex Entry: They often frequent snowy areas, their coats offering them camouflage from trainers. They are known to be very timid, but their strength shows that they have much more power.

Sligma.Pokedex Entry: They absorb sunlight through the flower on their backs, allowing them to slink away quickly when fully energized. Groups of them gather in meadows, clinging to flower stems so that Florallen can give them more energy.

Narslath.Pokedex Entry: The viscous slime that they produce is full of vital nutrients that aid in the growth of plants. Flowers grow on their backs in the Spring.

Anamary.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are nocturnal, only hunting in the dead of night to find their prey. Their yellow eyes allow them to see in any environment.

Hyacuana.Pokedex Entry: Very territorial and quick-tempered, this Pokemon is not fond of social interaction. They fight hard using their horns. If their horn is chipped or broken during a fight, its rage increases and it behaves recklessly.

Purrtinent.Pokedex Entry: By shaking its head, it scatters seeds that aid in the growth of plants. Purrtinent absorbs sunlight into its fur, which gives it enough energy to last two days; on cloudy days, they grow sluggish.

Purrsistent.Pokedex Entry: Once they lock onto a target, they don't ever stop pursuing them until they're able to strike. As they run, their fur releases seeds that are nutritious to other Grass-type Pokemon and also helps plants grow quickly.

Blossunia.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's dances are said to help wilted plants blossom again. They give off a strong aroma that can attract any other Pokemon.

Tefrin.Pokedex Entry: If the crust on its back vibrates, it is a sign that an earthquake is going to occur. They are sometimes called 'Forest Facilitators' because of their authoritative personalities.

Alpacott.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon's drool is full of vitamins and nutrients that are able to heal any injury. It constantly drools on itself in order to keep its wool healthy.

Alpaking.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon drool all day and night in order to release excess fluid from their bodies. The soles on their feet absorb water into their bodies in order to keep their wool healthy.

Mintot.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is admired because of its adorable appearance and cheery personality. The peppermint on top of its head is very sweet and can be used as a medicine.

Marqint.Pokedex Entry: The peppermints they produce are considered to be better than ones manufactured. They attack on MINTRIL's command.

Mintril.Pokedex Entry: They use their indestructible peppermint canes as weapons against foes. Its cries make MINTOT and MARQINT follow their every command.

Buddee.Pokedex Entry: Buddee wraps its vine around people and Pokemon that they like. They are vastly known for the butter they secrete from their mouth.

Buddelf.Pokedex Entry: It leaks butter from its flower when it is happy and when it makes new friends. It is said that if you taste its butter, you will be granted eternal happiness.

Budderor.Pokedex Entry: Once you taste the butter it gives off, you will blessed with eternal joy. They love to help others who need happiness.

Conutor.Pokedex Entry: They create armor by smashing coconut shells and using vines to connect it. The armor is strong enough to resist a cannonball.

Eradolor.Pokedex Entry: They create powerful armor using discarded coconut shells. Their tails have a single coconut at the end that is able to enlarge and smash with the force equivalent to a wrecking ball.

Bexile.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon always live alone and spend time strengthening their antlers. If anything crosses into its mountainous territory, it will immediately headbutt them off of the mountain.

Thornick.Pokedex Entry: They pretend to be average plants until they are approached. They fire iron spikes to protect themselves.

Foliarch.Pokedex Entry: The mystical power that it has is sometimes released into the berries that grow on its body. They may spend hours gnawing on a branch in order to make it smooth so that it may use it to amplify its power.

Mischievich.Pokedex Entry: Getting touched by one of its leaves results in a burning sensation that will make you itch uncontrollably. They float along the wind, allowing them to find victims with ease.

Ichafe.Pokedex Entry: Groups of them lock leaves and entangle victims. Their leaves can cause paralysis if they get touched.

Toxivy.Pokedex Entry: Getting touched by their leaves can cause a rash to appear all over your body. Their claws turn purple when they get ready to poison someone or something.

Noflibus.Pokedex Entry: They spend most of their time with their feet buried in the ground. As more flowers appear on its grassy chest, it shows that it about to evolve.

Emult.Pokedex Entry: Flowers bloom all over its body in the springtime. The one with the most flowers is considered to be the leader of a group.

Kukumetis.Pokedex Entry: No longer caring about making actual friends, its power has drastically increased, as well as its faithfulness to itself. If someone tries to be friendly towards them, they may accept, but on the inside it will not really sit in.

Vieweed.Pokedex Entry: The berries that grow on its stem resemble eyes, causing many trainers and Pokemon alike to become very unnerved by them. The eye-like berries that grow from its head are toxic to humans, but are known to heighten the senses of Pokemon that ingest them.

Triowth.Pokedex Entry: The three beans communicate with each other via telepathy, as they work better when all three are present. They are known to collect leaves and vines in order to create barriers to protect themselves.

Mastalk.Pokedex Entry: The vine around its body is able to unravel itself and strike quickly. The leaves on their bodies, if ingested, can give someone luck for 72 hours.

Cutox.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon float around, spreading toxic pollen in the air. Touching these Pokemon can cause mild spasms, stomach aches, and sudden chills.

Dangeous.Pokedex Entry: These graceful and beautiful Pokemon flow with the wind while release faint, toxic particles from their leaves. Contact with this Pokemon can cause the feeling of impending death.

Growny.Pokedex Entry: Eating their leaves is said to cause severe indigestion. When they use their legs to absorb nutrients, they cause nearby plants to wilt.

Kestridis.Pokedex Entry: By absorbing nutrients via its root-like legs, it can cause an entire garden to rot and wilt. Eating one of its leaves will cause you to vomit uncontrollably and have a burning sensation in your chest.

Scentar.Pokedex Entry: Their footprints always leave behind a lot of sweet spices. Inhaling their scents is known to calm the nerves.

Fragross.Pokedex Entry: Majority of their bodies are made of sweet spice, so chefs always chase after these Pokemon. Inhaling their minty aroma makes one feel extremely calm.

Meweed.Pokedex Entry: If its tail is wilted, it is a sign that it is very sick. When it hears music, it can't help but dance and play.

Phalyne.Pokedex Entry: If the oxygen in the air is contaminated, it grows angry. They act as mother figures to other Grass-type Pokemon.

Katypha.Pokedex Entry: If they see the habitat in which they live damaged in any way, they will either hunt down the culprit or try to come up with a solution. They ensnare their opponents and prey in sharp, thorny vines to keep them from escaping, allowing them to do as they please.

Beradon.Pokedex Entry: They attack using the berries that grow from the foliage around their necks, as well as the ones adorning their bodies. They have a quick-tempered nature and get angry if anyone enters their territory, slashing them with their toxic claws.

Chocolad.Pokedex Entry: Due to their sweet taste and appearance, they are often the targets of bird Pokemon. Their aroma is reminiscent to that of chocolate.

Sapotaste.Pokedex Entry: The leaves on its head are covered in an oily substance that disguises its scent from predators. They are often collected for their droppings, which are often sold as local delicacies in shops.

Diosparse.Pokedex Entry: Their lower bodies regenerate quickly, so they happily give away pieces of their bodies to others they are friends with. There are often festivals celebrated once a year that are dedicated to these Pokemon.

Podrink.Pokedex Entry: The milk that they produce is full of good vitamins and nutrients that can heal minor injuries. When their milk is sour, it is a sign that they are sick.

Ascal.Pokedex Entry: They are usually collected in order to get their milk. If one offers you milk, it means that it feels a deep connection with you.

Excalcior.Pokedex Entry: Their milk has cleansing and nutritional properties, as it is good for the skin and the body. A group of five is able to fill up an entire Olympic-size swimming pool with milk in less than a day.

Popuff.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon have a tendency to hop around whenever they move and sometimes float on occasion. Their bodies have a delicious taste, causing other Pokemon to sometimes hunt them down for food.

Foalish.Pokedex Entry: When its horn break off, it takes two weeks to grow back; during that time it displays very depressed behavior. It is an old folktale that as soon as one of them is born, a new tree begins to grow immediately.

Hornicus.Pokedex Entry: As they gallop, their hooves embed seeds into the growth to make new plants grow. Vines often dangle from their manes. Using them to their advantage, these Pokemon utilize them to ensnare enemies.

Bracamo.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon make tea by drinking water, mixing it in a special organ, and streaming it by lowering its head. They often make people sleepy by yawning, as their mouths have special spores that spread to nearby people and Pokemon.

Chamorian.Pokedex Entry: Their tea is known to cause a deep slumber with one taste. They are extremely docile despite their large size and will emanate a soothing aura when around someone they trust

Florush.Pokedex Entry: In Saigo myths, it is said to have been the reason that forests, and foliage in general, grow to be very healthy and beautiful. It has complete control over foliage.

Vulpolar.Pokedex Entry: It always arrives when it is snowing, but even then it's only seen as a shadow. They use their tails to collect snow before converting them into spikes to fire off.

Glasolemos.Pokedex Entry: When furious, it whips up intense snowstorms, that include icy spears, from its tail. They reside in snowy mountains, eating the plants that have frozen from the cold.

Lobelura.Pokedex Entry: Known as "The Walking Forest", these Pokemon grow numerous flowers and berries on its back during the spring and summer. Their skin is extremely tough and moist, being able to withstand the harshest of fires.

Grindor.Pokedex Entry: Created by farmers to help plant crops, they leave indentations in the ground as they move in order to evenly plant seeds. Their bodies are coated in a sap that causes them to deflect heat.

Eukawala.Pokedex Entry: They love playing with other Pokemon, especially ones that are the same height. These Pokemon love to snack on leaves that grow from their tails.

Kelgae.Pokedex Entry: It lives underwater, using the water currents to move it from place to place Moving past each other often causes them to get tangled up.

Kelphlow.Pokedex Entry: It is one of the fastest water Pokemon in the Xenioh Region. It is so agile that it can swim across an entire ocean in less than a minute.

Snoseed.Pokedex Entry: They bury themselves in the ground, using their snowman-like plant, in order to evade capture. When they sense a human's presence, they will follow them, making them extremely uncomfortable until they leave the area.

Cakaseed.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon came to life when young slaves possessed a scarecrow. It is said that they see their past lives through their blood red eye.

Recrowile.Pokedex Entry: After a farmer died in his barn, it was thought that this Pokemon was his reincarnation. It wanders fields and gardens, reliving every moment of his life by looking through its bloody eye.

Moeboe.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon reside in small ponds feeding on the tiny microorganisms on the floor. They multiply quickly when parts of them are torn apart.

Amoeblob.Pokedex Entry: They multiple rapidly when chunks of them are dismembered. They are very tiny Pokemon that don't really have much significance.

Burroot.Pokedex Entry: They hide underneath the ground, eating dirt for nutrients. Eating its leaves can cause depression.

Soilurk.Pokedex Entry: They hide underground, eating damp dirt to strengthen their bodies. They have the ability to change their form based on what type of move they use.

Cirrious.Pokedex Entry: Once it finds a nice rock home, it stays there for the rest of its life. Their tentacles can grow to be 20 inches in length and can be used as whips.

Barnacool.Pokedex Entry: Their tentacles can stretch as far as 150 feet. The rock it lived in as a Cirrious has now trapped its body, forcing it to hop around in order to move.

Scretump.Pokedex Entry: They bury themselves in the ground and pretend to be growing stumps. They take pleasure in scaring passersby by screeching when they walk past them.

Communitree.Pokedex Entry: At night, these Pokemon pull themselves out of the ground and wander into large communities to wreak havoc. According to one folklore, when one of them was hungry one day, it kidnapped and devoured a child.

Kishikae.Pokedex Entry: It worked alongside ENALIDIRE as they ravaged and nearly destroyed the environment of Marva centuries ago. Using its claws and tail, it drained all of the forests of Marva of their nutrients, fueling its power .

Okave.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon embed their legs into the ground, giving them the appearance of a cave. Once unsuspecting Pokemon or human climb inside of its mouth, it keeps them inside for as long as they want; whether they are digested or not is up to them.

Irongil.Pokedex Entry: They eat thorny plants, as well as knives and forks. The spikes that grow on their backs are made of a combination of keratin, steel, and leaves.

Keratren.Pokedex Entry: They have the ability to make their leaves spiky and smooth based on its mood. They can launch bony spikes from holes in their legs without pain or difficulty.

Kapang.Pokedex Entry: They fold their arms and build up heat and gas in their bodies before blasting their spikes in all directions. By imitating a tree, this Pokemon is able to ambush prey and mutilate them with ease.

Finacroak.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are often found in swamps sleeping on lilypads. They only move by hopping, as their back legs are unable to be used.

Stemby.Pokedex Entry: The fungus on this Pokemon's body was believed to be its food source. They spread spores whenever they ran.

Foliensus.Pokedex Entry: The large mushroom on its back acted as a cover during storms. They ate rotten leaves and berries.

Costas.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon lie in the bottom of small ponds and lakes absorbing light that shines down. They feed on sediment at the bottom of bodies of water.

Roshima.Pokedex Entry: They lay on the surface of water, absorbing sunlight through their feelers. They eat kelp and sediment along river banks.

Icepike.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon grow on the sides of snow-covered trees, sharing the nutrients. Getting pricked by one of their spikes is said to make one shiver uncontrollably.

Tricickle.Pokedex Entry: Its three heads always share the same thoughts, making things rather easy for it. When enraged, it unleashes an array of frozen spikes.

Weedrench.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are slathered in a slimy film that make it difficult for them to be grabbed. They enjoy swimming in swampy waters, as they are easily disguised there.

Aqweedra.Pokedex Entry: It is able to camouflage among seaweed and kelp, allowing it to catch prey with ease. They despise being out in the sun for too long, as it causes their leaves to dry out.

Spiroll.Pokedex Entry: Strangely, these Pokemon are commonly found in normal gardens and forests. They roll around to move, the small spikes in their vines picking up grass and soil particles as they do so.

Gargon.Pokedex Entry: Looking into these Pokemon's eyes is said to paralyze you for up to 48 hours. They use their vine-like hair to ensnare victims and prey.

Cytobulb.Pokedex Entry: They release a potent gas that will cause a burning sensation in the chest and throat. If one is enveloped in the gas it emits for too long, they will suffer from burns and brain damage.

Sulflor.Pokedex Entry: When they feel threatened, they emit a strong, toxic gas that will cause burning from the inside out. Getting too close to one is very dangerous without protection.

Mossome.Pokedex Entry: The moss that grows on its back helps it feed itself. It has a hardy disposition, being able to endure the worst conditions, but still turn out fine.

Mossatude.Pokedex Entry: They have been known to guard ancient civilizations by standing around the entrances. They were created over 5,000 years ago to protect civilians.

Gardvark.Pokedex Entry: They sleep underground during the day, leaving their leaves exposed in order to absorb sunlight. They have been known to infiltrate into other Pokemon's dens and steal their rations.

Gardwolf.Pokedex Entry: Gardwolf are often found where lush plants grow. They produce a variety of seeds based on the food that they eat; the healthier the food, the healthier the plant will be.

Nuderma.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are very disturbing and strange looking, as they always love stretching their skin while giving a blank look of happiness. They fight off Dermeat daily.

Dirrun.Pokedex Entry: It runs across desert roads so fast that you can't see it. It neglects using its wings due to the fact that its legs are more powerful.

Blurrun.Pokedex Entry: You never see these "Desert Blurs" because they run so fast that you only see dust. They are said to only stop running once a month.

Erthaur.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are able to create minuscule earthquakes by laying on their backs and spinning rapidly. They travel in groups and the one with the biggest crest is the leader.

Terraur.Pokedex Entry: They cause massive earthquakes by driving their legs into the ground and vibrating them. They live buried deep underground.

Dillar.Pokedex Entry: They roll into hard balls in order to protect themselves. Their shells are made of solidified mud.

Armadril.Pokedex Entry: They withdraw into their shells in order to look like spiked rocks. They dig deep into the earth in order to eat meal worms.

Desigill.Pokedex Entry: Despite being fish, DESIGILL hate being in the water. They use their long whiskers as hands in order to dig through the ground.

Anhyvaunt.Pokedex Entry: They use their whiskers as claws in order to both attack and dig quickly. They frighten anyone entering their territory by using their sharp fins to slice through the ground from underground.

Crispup.Pokedex Entry: Their fur is extremely crisp and flaky, resulting in crumb like features to flake off. They are very scared Pokemon and keep themselves in a fetal position.

Barkrisp.Pokedex Entry: They have an extremely heightened sense of smell. Their skin can flake off when they have been critically damaged.

Jishuta.Pokedex Entry: It resides deep underground and uses its large arms and legs to stir up earthquakes in order to destroy parts of Kisek. It never comes out of the ground unless it is disturbed.

Claybo.Pokedex Entry: Discovered in ancient ruins, this Pokemon was thought to be the bringer of rain during a drought. They bounce on their small feet in order to get around.

Nenclay.Pokedex Entry: They can detach their arms and legs and launch them as rockets using psychic energy. Their legs aren't attached to their bodies, so they use their minds to move them as if they are attached.

Radig.Pokedex Entry: They cannot really see that well, so they rely on the feelers on its nose to guide them around. They dig elaborate tunnel systems that are difficult to navigate through.

Burrole.Pokedex Entry: Now completely blind, these Pokemon have to rely on their nose to navigate them places. They use their drill tails to make burrows to sleep in.

Chompace.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's claws exert a force of 200lbs. They use their claws to crack open the shells of nuts in order to feed.

Casamin.Pokedex Entry: They allow any smaller Pokemon to inhabit their bodies. They are docile Pokemon who simply lay on the beach without moving a muscle.

Emege.Pokedex Entry: Its body is not fully developed, so it keeps the shell it is born from around its body for safety. It hops around on its one free foot in means of getting around.

Yudyg.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon sometimes work alongside miners and construction workers. They dig elaborate tunnel systems to help them effectively complete a task.

Aechin.Pokedex Entry: It can reach speeds of up to 900 mph. It races across the land to strengthen its body, mind, and spirit.

Dinameau.Pokedex Entry: Dinameau are hardly ever seen, as they spend majority of their lives underground. They whip up huge sandstorms by shaking their feathers.

Calirole.Pokedex Entry: They create elaborate burrows in dry areas in order to store food. When threatened, it attacks with its sharp claws and spiky tail.

Secressa.Pokedex Entry: They create large holes in walls and the ground of caves and other arid areas to trap and surprise enemies, as well as prey. They sweat mud, which helps them camouflage themselves better in barren or muddy areas.

Hoole.Pokedex Entry: Using their claws, they dig out holes at a fast pace. It is a very picky Pokemon, creating numerous burrows before picking one that it likes.

Burrowl.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are perfectionists; they never stop working on a single burrow until it is flawless. They are unable to fly, so they instead get around by sprinting.

Quarrene.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon spend their time digging large pits in order to find minerals to eat. Their large wings are able to whip up an intense sandstorm with one flap.

Casamass.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon resemble sandcastles, so they lie on beaches and sometimes deserts, allowing small Pokemon to inhabit them If they grow tired of one spot, they will travel to another area carrying any small Pokemon with them.

Fenneak.Pokedex Entry: They dig burrows in their usual hot environments in order to provide themselves with shade. They are very playful and mischievous Pokemon that like scaring other Pokemon by sneaking up on them.

Necorrode.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies secrete a viscous fluid that can eat away at any surface. They are usually dormant and avoid human contact, but when threatened, they will try to find the nearest human to help them.

Diggoph.Pokedex Entry: Their blunt teeth allow them to chew through anything that may block their way underground. Their teeth often crack, but they take a short amount of time to heal.

Womburrow.Pokedex Entry: They are very slow when above ground, but when underground, they are able to move at 60 mph. Its short whiskers allow it to sense its surroundings, as it cannot see very well.

Hiplash.Pokedex Entry: Their noses all have an internal pouch under their nasal cavities that allow them to breathe and absorb water through their nostrils simultaneously. They like to jump into water and splash those around them.

Hiphoon.Pokedex Entry: They jump into water from a great height, creating a massive wave that soaks everything around it. They blast high pressured water from their nasal cavities.

Princada.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon live in the desert and use their feathery crests to find prey. If they find suitable prey, they inject them with a paralyzing poison, and bury them in the sand, waiting for them to die.

Kinang.Pokedex Entry: This devious Pokemon uses its body to hypnotize prey; while hypnotized, the victim will feel no pain as KINANG eats it alive. It buries whatever is left in the ground and comes back for it the next day.

Armordilo.Pokedex Entry: They curl into a ball and roll into its enemies to inflict major damage. Their shells are extremely durable and can break solid concrete.

Zable.Pokedex Entry: Its sack-like tail holds sand that can induce sleeping with one grain. Zable always feels tired, but its brain won't allow it to sleep.

Dustzee.Pokedex Entry: Its tail, which usually holds a bunch of sand, can open and spill the sand out, but when it does, Dustzee can't help but lie on it. Its brain still won't allow it to sleep, so it is a tortuous act, as the sand is extremely comfortable.

Yogoth.Pokedex Entry: They are very flexible, which allows them to move quickly and dodge attacks slowly, but efficiently. By stretching its limbs, it can increase its psychic power.

Slowily.Pokedex Entry: They slowly and carefully use tricks to help them win battles. Their psychic attacks are powerful, but because of its recklessness, they sometimes backfire.

Sentioth.Pokedex Entry: They sit in silence in order to harness their brain energy. It can blast away an entire forest if its psychic energy is at its highest peak.

Excatun.Pokedex Entry: They are known to help construction workers dig holes for architecture. Their noses are very sensitive to smell, allowing them to navigate well despite their lack of sight.

Caragai.Pokedex Entry: Their claws are strong enough to crush a train. They are often mistaken as open coconuts, which prompts passersby to reach for them, resulting in a loss of an appendage on some occasions.

Tuskwine.Pokedex Entry: Their hides are rough enough to scrape metal. They use their tusks to skewer fruit.

Hogrind.Pokedex Entry: They charge into large stones with their tusks extended, launching them afar They ram into enemies at high speed, knocking the wind out if them.

Sheruff.Pokedex Entry: They dig pit traps to catch thieves and robbers before they strike. Its scarf acts as a personality stabilizer, and if it is removed, it becomes extremely depressed.

Terrageus.Pokedex Entry: It was first discovered in an old, abandoned mine centuries ago. Rumors have surfaced that it is the creator of the Pokemon world, though no one really knows the truth.

Shisin.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon enjoy their environment and absolutely hate being confined to Pokeballs. Once they are captured, they never allow their trainers to care for them, as they prefer individuality.

Yashinean.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are very intense rivals with Kachanusis, as they fight savagely whenever they are in the same location. There was a large war, where dozens of these Pokemon fought with Kachanusis over territory, as humans were taking their land.

Anuby.Pokedex Entry: They are lazy Pokemon that always expect to be pampered and cared for. They always seek attention and approval from their trainers, despite their arrogance.

Kachanusis.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon were worshiped in ancient times after their great war against Yashinean. They absolutely despite Yashinean and every time their eyes meet, they engage in a fierce fight.

Swallord.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon do not discriminate when it comes to their hunger; they eat any and everything, whether it be alive or not. Their large mouths are able to suck in an entire 20-story building without resistance.

Grainest.Pokedex Entry: They fashion old branches into flutes that they can use to control sand and dirt. By playing its flute, it is able to create small sandstorms that can last up to two hours.

Moundoll.Pokedex Entry: They spend majority of their lives underground, only popping up when there are invaders in their territory. Moundoll despise the rain, as it makes their mounds soft and weak.

Geezone.Pokedex Entry: They have the ability to control dirt with a snap of their fingers. Each one claims 80 square feet of land as their territory. Anyone who enters is immediately pelted by clods of dirt.

Rokozin.Pokedex Entry: Its body is very bulky, allowing it to protect itself from injury while battling or digging. They use their single tooth to dig at high speeds.

Calfrid.Pokedex Entry: Its large hump on its back is actually a cloak it is born with. CALFRID is able to shed its cloak in favor of a new one, which is then able to be worn by humans.

Frigiox.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is known for helping people stuck in mountains and avalanches. They tread in snowy mountains, looking for adequate places to create burrows for smaller Pokemon that get stranded or lost.

Aedaragia.Pokedex Entry: She is known to have created the land of the Qiloh Region. It works alongside with Patanoros to keep Qiloh a prospering region.

Humoist.Pokedex Entry: The crest on its head helps it navigate to vast water sources. It creates thick steam to hide itself and deliver fatal blows.

Rakudren.Pokedex Entry: It stores vast amounts of water in the pyramidal hump on its back, which is then immediately turned to steam. It was highly worshiped because of its activity and knowledge.

Dreidull.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon was discovered 100 years ago in ancient ruins. By spinning, it can generate massive amounts of psychic energy that could grow unstable.

Marmoby.Pokedex Entry: Their chubby bodies help them bounce back from rough hits. They make large underground tunnels that help them around faster.

Marmast.Pokedex Entry: Their large appetites help them maintain their chubby appearances. They are able to bounce back those who try to attack it physically.

Odontate.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is able to swim in both water and land thanks to its more developed legs. There is a special organ in its body that keeps its skin and insides moist and slippery.

Quintore.Pokedex Entry: They are often found buried under sand on shores They swallow water, boiling it with a special organ in their body, in order to fire off their limbs like rockets.

Staruck.Pokedex Entry: They lay on their backs, buried in the sand. When it senses an approaching figure, it elongates its spikes in defense, usually with the figure receiving a painful poke. Their limbs fall off when in battle, but they immediately grow back within seconds.

Turosof.Pokedex Entry: Its shell is composed of a soft mud, making it very weak. It swims very slowly in water in order to give the shell time to adjust.

Dholake.Pokedex Entry: They roll around in mud puddles in order to absorb the dirt and water into its body. Their fur is naturally absorbent, so it can store up to 30 gallons of water in its fur at a time.

Dhomange.Pokedex Entry: Muddy water constantly drips off of their fur, making a mess wherever they go. When their hair is trimmed, they get extremely depressed and weak.

Dohewl.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon could not fly at all, so instead they dug tunnels and walked from place to place. It is speculated that their poor decision making resulted in them going extinct very quickly.

Demoris.Pokedex Entry: Groups of them destroy and devour buildings. They bury themselves underground to escape chase.

Malistroy.Pokedex Entry: The opening in its chest expels a thick dust that allows it to escape with ease. They use their tails and claws to slash their opponents.

Horidevis.Pokedex Entry: Many of them are strong enough to collapse a skyscraper with one swing of their powerful tails. One roar is enough to paralyze even the strongest Pokemon in fear.

Scrawnude.Pokedex Entry: Their skin has a high elasticity, allowing them to stretch their skin endlessly without pain. They create burrows near ponds to keep themselves hydrated.

Ghlifo.Pokedex Entry: Discovered underground in a desert over 100 years ago, this Pokemon's existence is an enigma. The hand-like appendages on its body seem to always remain in a stiff position, but it has been proven that they actually do move in order to enhance its power.

Celsieti.Pokedex Entry: The fur covering its body aids in keeping its actual body warm in frigid climates. They create snowballs using their claws, using them to attack.

Manticub.Pokedex Entry: They contaminate water at the source by injecting toxins from its tail inside of it, but are also able to absorb contaminants into its body. They thrive by devouring trash and soil and extruding it through its tail and into water.

Venevore.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon contaminate water with poison so powerful that it can dissolve skin and bone in seconds. They absorb toxins and trash into their bodies through their tails to nourish themselves.

Fecutsar.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is said to take residence in extremely unsanitary areas. It despises clean locations and tries to spread its filth to large areas, no matter what

Trageleak.Pokedex Entry: Its perspiration has the consistency of mud due to the amount that it eats. It despises dry areas, so it always tries to keep itself wet by absorbing water into its fur.

Tyngasea.Pokedex Entry: By swinging its fur, it can create large, muddy whirlpools that can demolish an entire forest. Its fur is always wet, so riders are advised to wear a swimsuit or bring a towel when riding them.

Stackem.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon have a strange obsession with balancing items around them. They often compete with each other to see who is able to balance the most rocks on their heads.

Pupreez.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon entertain themselves by wresting and playing in the snow. The ice crystals on its head and neck absorb moisture in order for it to create its own snow.

Loneti.Pokedex Entry: It wanders the snowy mountains looking for someone to play with. When spotted, people run away, thinking it is a dangerous creature, when in actuality, it is very docile.

Dimacrisal.Pokedex Entry: They were created when the moon's energy had an impact on an icicle. They keep their heads stuck in the roofs of icy caves in order to keep their bodies from melting.

Coolyn.Pokedex Entry: They freeze their fur, making it as sharp as needles, whenever they are petted by someone they don't like. They can release a mist from their foreheads so that they can escape enemies.

Frosleet.Pokedex Entry: They are great companions for eskimos and travelers venturing snowy mountains. By shaking their fur, they can whip up mild snowstorms.

Lynorth.Pokedex Entry: It has a rough, durable body thanks to his extremely strong icy bones, which scientists have proven are made of Never Melt Ice. Their claws generate freezing air that can slow any down any opponent.

Frosnow.Pokedex Entry: Brought to life by a strange power, these Pokemon inhabit frosty areas. They are friendly Pokemon that will happily play with younger kids by creating snow.

Paslush.Pokedex Entry: It can turn any body of water into slush just by sitting on it. It can cause small snowstorms accidentally if it is upset.

Sluslurr.Pokedex Entry: They spit slushy water to defend themselves. They use their smooth, yet chunky bodies to get into small spaces.

Glacischk.Pokedex Entry: Their white fur helps them blend in with their snowy environments. They can create ice crystals and snowstorms by flicking their fur.

Yakalf.Pokedex Entry: It is important that those who ride these Pokemon wear gloves, or else they will immediately get frostbite by touching their horns. These Pokemon have no problem letting others ride on its back, but only as long as they have the right gear.

Yaking.Pokedex Entry: Always wear at least three pairs gloves when riding these Pokemon, as holding onto their horns will cause immediate frostbite. It eats frozen grass and mushrooms to help its body stay healthy; if it eats warm food, it gets sick.

Burnipp.Pokedex Entry: There is a lot of carbon dioxide in its body that gets expelled as cold air bubbles. Bursting these Pokemon's bubbles will cause you to suffocate and freeze to death within 3 minutes if you do not get away in time.

Coolem.Pokedex Entry: They hide their paws in their fur and bounce and roll to get to places quickly. Their fur contains a large amount of snow particles and shaking furiously can cause blizzards.

Permafur.Pokedex Entry: They produce air that is as low as -147 degrees. Their fur is able to stiffen and function as freezing spikes.

Parafrost.Pokedex Entry: The crystals that grow from its head are extremely valuable, as they are unable to melt and can change color by refracting light. They are able to drop the temperature of their environment to -800 degrees in a matter of seconds.

Moosicle.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon love to slide and skate across surfaces, so they freeze flat surfaces in order to play. They sleep in groups of up to thirty.

Humdrard.Pokedex Entry: A rather unimpressive Pokemon, it spends majority of its time sleeping, only eating when absolutely necessary for it. Those who come across these Pokemon in their habitat often ignore them, as they find nothing remarkable about them.

Wulfreeze.Pokedex Entry: Its howl can send chills down the spines of the innocent. A group of them can cause an avalanche just by howling at the same time.

Snokami.Pokedex Entry: Packs of them are known to destroy villages and devour everything in sight. Their howls can create blizzards and hailstorms that last for 2 whole months.

Tuskria.Pokedex Entry: They are extremely clumsy and slow because of their large tusk. They usually have to crawl on all fours in order to keep balance across slippery surfaces.

Cubite.Pokedex Entry: Their tails are encased in ice, allowing it to block attacks that hit it. They freeze particles in the air in order to create snow.

Rayookie.Pokedex Entry: They can breathe out snowflakes, making a fun time for children who encounter it. Their tails can fire snowballs and icicles as it swallows moisture in the air.

Koserobo.Pokedex Entry: Influenced by the darkness it was raised in, this Pokemon is known for mischief. They steal from innocent civilians and Pokemon and will sometimes even steal from its own allies.

Thinkose.Pokedex Entry: It stands still in vast, snowy areas, increasing its psychic power by staying at peace. The daylight helps its body gain more mental strength.

Elflet.Pokedex Entry: They work nonstop until they finish something. If they see someone hurt, they use their bells to heal them.

Santoho.Pokedex Entry: By jingling the bells around their neck, they increase their power. Each one orders ten Elflet to work on a specific task.

Minsurro.Pokedex Entry: It has constantly battled for control of Zinco against Wasepach, with battles engaging every 10 years. Its icy body is extremely durable and is unable to be melted.

Frostic.Pokedex Entry: Discovered inside of a fallen meteor, these Pokemon are said to be from another planet. They reside inside of cold caves and embed themselves in the wall.

Titadilla.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon strictly rolls around to get to all of its locations, leaving lines in all terrain it passes through. Their bones and scales are made of a strong, heat resistant steel alloy.

Celprick.Pokedex Entry: When threatened, they roll into spiky balls and roll towards targets at high speeds. Their bodies are able to resist over 450,000 degree heat for a certain amount of time.

Frozone.Pokedex Entry: Using their noses, they absorb pollution in the air, making their bodies toxic. They are able to expel toxic gases that can cause nausea and fainting.

Gelidome.Pokedex Entry: The shell on its back is comprised of frozen bricks of poison gas. Its entire body is poisonous, so it never gets to show affection without causing health issues.

Nippine.Pokedex Entry: They unleash a barrage of toxic quills from their backs when threatened. Their saliva is poisonous, but because its breath is very cold, it can create poisonous shards of ice by spitting.

Frigidine.Pokedex Entry: Its body is covered in small, toxic spikes that immediately cause you to be poisoned upon contact. If one of their spikes snap off, they immediately grow back longer and much more toxic.

Alcelsius.Pokedex Entry: It is able to skate across any surface, as its hooves freeze anything that they touch. They slide into each other at high speeds in order to show dominance.

Monkeep.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are always upset, but scientists are unable to figure out why. They cause hailstorms when they cry.

Geladour.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon view excitement and friendliness as weakness and, as a result, are never seen smiling. Being grabbed by this Pokemon is said to cause frostbite.

Konaustrea.Pokedex Entry: They inhabit snowy mountains and enjoy solitude, so they pound their chests in order to cause avalanches and keep humans away. Its glare fills people and Pokemon with unrelenting fear, driving them away from its territory.

Platypund.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon enjoys swimming deep below sea level and absorbing the frigid, salty water through the gills on its fin. The icicle in its chest is connected to its heart, which allows its body to survive for months in extremely frigid water.

Platygue.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon can freeze an entire pond with one touch. Its entire body is covered in substance that allows it to live in very frigid conditions.

Reefawn.Pokedex Entry: They use their sharp, elongated canine to pierce berries for their juice. They can run across any surface, water or land, because their hooves are fully insulated.

Frigeer.Pokedex Entry: They are highly aggressive and will often attack each other with their icy horns to assert dominance. They roam in Arctic areas, using their teeth and antlers to skewer berries.

Staglacie.Pokedex Entry: They often test each other's strength by ramming into each other with their icy horns. To assert dominance, they charge at weaker members of their herd.

Whaleet.Pokedex Entry: Their noses are able to pierce concrete. They are very docile and won't attack unless they are threatened.

Naryst.Pokedex Entry: They are able to spin around like a drill in order to pierce hard surfaces. Their species are hunted because of the ice crystals covering their lower bodies.

Tokub.Pokedex Entry: Their fangs are made of ice, so they are very fragile and crack easily. By biting something, they are able to make it icy, but they may also break a tooth.

Frostear.Pokedex Entry: Their fangs are much more stronger, so they do not break as easily as they used to. Their fangs are very sharp and can pierce the bones of their prey in one go.

Fureeze.Pokedex Entry: Their fur has sheltered them from the cold for eons. Their tusks were very weak, often melting or breaking off whenever they tried to find food.

Tusking.Pokedex Entry: They were hunted for their fur for more than 300,000 years, eventually causing their extinction. The age of this Pokemon could be determined by looking at its icy tusks; the younger ones' tusks were longer and conjoined, while the older ones' were shorter and separate.

Seilyon.Pokedex Entry: The water that it distributes from its body is full of so many nutrients that a single drop can help an entire forest grow. It was seen as a healer across the Marva Region after it helped restore the region back to its flourishing state after ENALIDIRE AND KISHIKAE almost destroyed it.

Aqueriol.Pokedex Entry: Aqueriol are often seen walking on the surface of lakes, freezing the liquid with every step. Only four of them are seen occupying a body of water at any given time.

Chillent.Pokedex Entry: Very vindictive and cold, these Pokemon are fierce competitors when it comes to battling. It will almost always try to take the leadership role in a team and attempt to train its teammates until they run ragged.

Getsura.Pokedex Entry: It appears on cold nights when the moon is the brightest. It has been hypothesized that it was born inside of the moon.

Neiburr.Pokedex Entry: It remains completely still when it senses humans or other Pokemon around it. They despise being touched and instantly freeze anything that gets too close to them.

Stallith.Pokedex Entry: They remain motionless for days to months, not moving from a single spot until captured or attacked. They freeze anything that they view as a threat and then crush it.

Yuthief.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon only appear around holidays to steal gifts, replacing them with random objects that they find. There are rare occasions were these Pokemon will steal numerous children, freeze them, and keep them as sculptures in their dens.

Cryena.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon freeze their prey solid before using their large, sharp teeth to take them apart and devour them. Once they start fighting, they never want to stop and will continue attacking even if the opponent is knocked out.

Pinnipola.Pokedex Entry: They sleep all together in a tight group to keep their body temperatures up in the cold environment in which they live. The icy film in its tail aid in its swimming.

Frigidon.Pokedex Entry: Using their tusks, they skewer fish Pokemon while sitting on ice floes in order to feed themselves, as well as and Pinnipola. They don't swim as well as they walk on land, so they always prefer to stay up.

Hygenial.Pokedex Entry: It produces ice that has both healing and cleansing properties. If it sees any dirt in a vicinity, it quickly blasts a beam of ice that melts in seconds, leaving the area spotless.

Zokorode.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon love digging for things underground. They have internal ears that they use to listen far away.

Lynobca.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon live in mountains and hate travelers who invade their territory. They are very vicious towards other LYNOBCA that they encounter, especially if there is food involved.

Martemid.Pokedex Entry: A very agile Pokemon, Martemid is able to run extremely quick in order to escape its enemies. If approached, they will shake erratically out of fright and release heat.

Skweek.Pokedex Entry: Its genetic structure has been influenced by scientists, allowing it to evolve into three different creatures. They love to gnaw on wood and cheese.

Miningo.Pokedex Entry: Years ago, these Pokemon were worshiped and loved by humans, but these days they are seen as a nuisance. As a result, they are often abandoned. They travel in close nit packs and typically avoid human contact.

Dingrowl.Pokedex Entry: Very few humans are able to catch these Pokemon, and even if they are, the Pokemon ignores their trainers' orders. If it sees a human, it will attack immediately because of their hatred towards them.

Fleetah.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon race against each other to strengthen their limbs. They are really quick to run from trainers.

Speedah.Pokedex Entry: It runs at 175 mph. It blends in perfectly with its hunting grounds and uses sharp claws to attack its prey.

Cerleu.Pokedex Entry: It hates getting attention, as it makes them feel inferior, which is difficult for them because of their fur's lack of pigment. Nobody knows why, but it is born with gray fur, which turns white as it continues to grow.

Leucervid.Pokedex Entry: If anyone makes eye contact with it, it goes into a blind rage. Its fur color makes it feel worthless, causing it become enraged because of its own insecurity.

Norvisc.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are very territorial and will attack anything that invades. They are rivals with SORACH.

Sorach.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are very durable and will take many hits. They are rivals with NORVISC.

Puprieve.Pokedex Entry: Its long ears and excellent sense of smell allow it to retrieve many objects that may be hidden or missing. It loves to find BANEFFUS and play with them, even though the other Pokemon hate it.

Yanyin.Pokedex Entry: They have the power to become a dual-type Pokemon, but only if the types are weak or strong against each other. Their markings are able to show what type they are.

Breezent.Pokedex Entry: They can give off a variety of scents that can be either good or bad depending on its mood. They are able to spin at high speeds and vanish into thin air in battles, making it hard for their opponents to actually see them.

Mannid.Pokedex Entry: They are highly obedient and will remain loyal to their trainers no matter what they do. They are not comfortable in the wild, so they always choose to stay in their Pokeballs unless forced out.

Bobynx.Pokedex Entry: They spend most of their lives in small caves located in the mountains. They attack with sharp claws and fangs.

Bokshel.Pokedex Entry: They take residence in abandoned boxes and keep traveling with them as a shell. It is a very sensitive Pokemon that always cries and hides under its box shell when it feels threatened.

Hermirt.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies have now combined with the box they had when they were Bokshels. Sharp blades extend from their shell when they feel that they are threatened.

Fuzzie.Pokedex Entry: Their genetic structure is directly connected to the fur on their bodies. Its fur always captures and absorbs different particles that help it adapt to its surroundings.

Fluffur.Pokedex Entry: Its extremely soft fur can absorb water, making it even more fluffy. They like keeping their fur clean, so they will always help each other if they see each other dirty.

Fuzzoft.Pokedex Entry: They are sometimes used by models to help find the right outfits. They continuously groom themselves so that they look their best.

Beautifur.Pokedex Entry: A model's favorite Pokemon, they always try to look their best. They are able to change the color of certain parts of their body once they are groomed.

Loopur.Pokedex Entry: They are able to rip off their body parts and use them as weapons. Their limbs grow back automatically without complication.

Dismemper.Pokedex Entry: They are able to tear off their limbs and regrow them within seconds. Their rate of regeneration is so fast that scientists observe it so that they can see how it can help mankind.

Pinoge.Pokedex Entry: When these Pokemon are angry, their spikes emerge from their backs and their bodies give off a musky odor. If it seems to trust you, their spikes will stay withdrawn unless you do something that scares it, accidentally or purposely.

Ferring.Pokedex Entry: The rings around its body allows it to stretch very far. Sometimes, it may launch the rings at its opponents for defense, but will always try to retrieve them quickly.

Rainboa.Pokedex Entry: They can change the color of any object that they please using the emblem around its neck. Its bodily fluids are very thick and are often used to create paint.

Serpaint.Pokedex Entry: They aren't particularly fond of Monochrow and Crowme. It has the unique ability to make itself appear invisible by changing the color of its scales to match its environment.

Nubby.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon train by ramming into each other with their antlers. If their antlers chip, they scrape them against a rock.

Pudhole.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are almost always seen with wet mud covering their fur. They have a strong sense of smell that allows them to find the nearest mud puddle.

Crowial.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are often owned by people from royal families. They enjoy riding on the heads of their trainers.

Shoodie.Pokedex Entry: They take enjoyment in clamping onto the heads of humans and riding on their backs, giving them the appearance of a custom hoodie. They can suck up food from far away thanks to its large mouth.

Nuticool.Pokedex Entry: They are usually found in groups under the guidance of Chillent. Their fur is unusually cold to the touch.

Bambabe.Pokedex Entry: Curious and playful, these graceful Pokemon spend most of their time jumping around and exploring the world around them Their curiosity sometimes gets them in dangerous situations in which Buckrown may have to save them from.

Buckrown.Pokedex Entry: They always have to help Bambabe when they get into dangerous areas and situations that they can't handle. They are known as 'Protectors of the Forest'.

Pleino.Pokedex Entry: They usually reside alongside Shrubur in fields and gardens. Their fur is very rough and resilient, making it able to withstand even the harshest conditions.

Naitizar.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon appears in legends; its mysterious powers are used to compel others to make moral choices. It appears before those who wish to have an honest world.

Chubunny.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon always stuff their mouths with food until they can no longer hold any. They fire off bombs from their stomachs made of the food they digest.

Lagobese.Pokedex Entry: Their extremely large bodies can crush a semi-truck. Their saliva's acid is so powerful that they can dissolve anything that enters its mouth.

Blockon.Pokedex Entry: Often ignored and mocked because of their appearances, they link together to create large structures. Their bodies are so resilient that they can withstand an atomic explosion.

Capygo.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is very popular with little girls and women in general because of its cute appearance. They are very curious Pokemon take pleasure in small things.

Papibara.Pokedex Entry: To give themselves distinguished looks, they fashion apparel that they see humans wear out of forest material. They are very protective and harsh towards Capygo.

Kidden.Pokedex Entry: They are able to enter the bodies of other Pokemon or humans in order to give them plentiful energy. They are able to produce energy in a variety of ways and expel it in a grand fashion.

Esqurrel.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can sense danger from over 20 miles away, so they take the initiative to get away as fast as possible. They have very bad nerves, leading them to be scared very easily.
