Squreact.Pokedex Entry: They have very quick reflexes, making them difficult to sneak up on. They glide on hard winds in order to get a large distance away from danger.

Hobor.Pokedex Entry: An old folktale says that abandoned orphans became this Pokemon on the night of a blue moon. They fashion clothes out of rags and old papers to keep themselves warm.

Glammink.Pokedex Entry: Its fur is highly sought after by collectors and designers because of its unique texture and feel. Groups of them keep each other clean by grooming each other with pine cones.

Vogaze.Pokedex Entry: To keep its fur glossy and neat, it eats various berries on a daily basis. Clothing made from its fur is often much more expensive and mainly worn by the rich.

Shiftyke.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon have the unique ability to change their type based on the environment or Pokemon around them. These rare Pokemon are often sought after by trainers because of the great power.

Dunnis.Pokedex Entry: Their diminutive stature allow them to sneak into the tiniest of spaces. They are relatively friendly Pokemon, but it may grow a bit too attached.

Funnart.Pokedex Entry: Always in a jovial mood, these Pokemon always try to make the best out of bad situations. Their fur is able sense bad vibes and they automatically try to lighten up the mood, sometimes with poor results...

Chuey.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are often seen wandering around alleys or empty areas while chewing on their hair. Their teeth aren't fully developed, so they constantly gnaw on their long hair to aid in the process.

Bacclaw.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon retract their long claws and keep their paws clenched to give an element of surprise. Their fur is very sensitive to air currents, letting them know when someone is near.

Markub.Pokedex Entry: They love creating elegant paintings, and hate when they get removed. The fluid in their body varies in color depending on the location where they are found and the mood they are in.

Saigra.Pokedex Entry: Its appearance is said to signify the peak of an era. With a clap of its paws, it is able to help people reach the highest point of their lives.

Nibbler.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon always gnaw on twigs and branches because they enjoy the taste of the wood. Removing a branch from this Pokemon's mouth is extremely dangerous, as it will bite whatever gets close to its maw.

Kaffini.Pokedex Entry: They eat special berries called 'Feinnow' that cause them to become extremely hyperactive. Their bodies emit an extremely strong, sweet odor, so their sweat is often collected and transformed into perfume.

Civelry.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are always full of energy and spend their time running and jumping through different environments. Civelry normally travel on all fours, but can easily run on their hind legs when racing through forests and cities.

Tardie.Pokedex Entry: These peculiar, minuscule Pokemon were discovered around a pond two centuries ago, but further research concludes that they have lived for thousands of years without issue. The hard skin around its body has been proven to be indestructible, making these Pokemon nearly impossible to eliminate.

Treseek.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are often used as starters due to their strength and ability to evolve into either a Grass, Fire, or Water-type. Their genetic makeup has been discovered to be somewhat similar to Fuzzie, so they are often captured in groups and studied frequently.

Crookoin.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon has an extreme obsession with coins. Its tail acts like a bag, allowing it to store all of the items it takes.

Raccoin.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is mostly active during nighttime. It breaks into people's home silently and steal all of their coins without making a single sound.

Thievoin.Pokedex Entry: It breaks into banks and houses, stealing every coin that they see silently. It orders CROOKOIN and RACCOIN to steal from the innocent and bring the valuables to it when it is tired.

Bunnoon.Pokedex Entry: They are said to have come to Earth from an asteroid. Their crescent markings glow brightly when in danger.

Stripeleon.Pokedex Entry: It has the ability to melt into water, as well as vanish into thin air. They enjoy swimming and get startled very easily.

Steleo.Pokedex Entry: Their steel bodies are said to be unable to melt. These Pokemon are quick to start fights when they are bored.

Leobliter.Pokedex Entry: The metal inside of its mane helps it repel attacks that come towards its facial area. If these Pokemon are ever challenged, they will never back down, even if they are at a disadvantage.

Pontaur.Pokedex Entry: As soon as it is born, it is able to run as fast as a jet. Their legs lack hooves, making them slightly defenseless, but the muscles inside make up for it.

Rokinka.Pokedex Entry: The rings on its tail glow brightly as it brings newly found ideas and power to those who wish to have them. It has a very kind, but mischievous nature, taking and bringing cultures and ideas to different places in the world.

Doraji.Pokedex Entry: The branches they carry around grow toxic berries that splatter on contact. They throw the berries at those who bother them.

Nindor.Pokedex Entry: They move swiftly, avoiding any and all contact with others. They are very skilled in accuracy and will make sure that their poisonous ammo always hits its mark.

Sticute.Pokedex Entry: The honey it secretes from its pores is extremely toxic to every being except itself. It attacks by slashing with its poisonous claws.

Honoger.Pokedex Entry: They launch their toxic honey at enemies when enraged. If they get hungry, they lick themselves.

Swidonery.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon does not care about anyone but itself. The honey secreting from its body allows blows to slide off and also gets its opponents stuck, giving it the perfect opportunity to attack.

Figurisk.Pokedex Entry: Discovered in an abandoned observatory, this Pokemon has baffled both scientists and astronomers for centuries. Its genetic structure allows it to evolve based on the stars its horn is pointed to or near at night.

Thorpeedo.Pokedex Entry: The musky odor that they emit can peel the paint off a skyscraper. They are usually dormant, but if agitated, the spikes on their backs unsheathe and they begin chasing you.

Selong.Pokedex Entry: They stretch their bodies to remarkable lengths to constrict and hypnotize their opponents. It is very rare, but sometimes, a SELONG will have a dark conscience that will lead them to do unspeakable and disturbing acts.

Chamerge.Pokedex Entry: It has the ability to revert to a liquid form and merge with any object. They use their long, sticky tongues to catch prey at a fast rate.

Screechimp.Pokedex Entry: When threatened, they let out ear-splitting shrieks that will drive away any opponents. Their stomachs can amplify their screeches.

Shriekong.Pokedex Entry: By clenching their fists tightly, they amplify their screeches and howls. They are able to burst over 60 windows with one howl.

Torsuri.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's training sessions are strenuous, as they always come up with new dances that can counter enemy attacks. If one looks at it for too long while it is dancing, they fall under its control.

Suripula.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are always looking for Pokemon and humans to seduce into doing its bidding. By dancing, it builds up its psychic energy and emanates an aura that can control anyone.

Mesmerich.Pokedex Entry: It procures rare items by manipulating Pokemon and humans with its dancing. Its movements generate enough psychic energy to control an entire town

Shellace.Pokedex Entry: Whatever is inside of the egg has never been seen, as it always vanishes when people attempt to get close to it. Its hard shell is even able to protect it from nuclear detonation.

Petu_Kado.Pokedex Entry: According to folklore, it devoured an entire city in the span of three days. Its insatiable appetite leads it to eat anything, living or not.

Aggor.Pokedex Entry: They run as soon as they are born in order to strengthen their legs. Groups of them used to be killed for food until their species died off.

Semagrisso.Pokedex Entry: They almost never stop running because they love having their hearts beat fast. They were hunted for centuries.

Paraja.Pokedex Entry: This shyest of the beasts, it remained hidden as it aided the people of the Mirus Region after the war. They give off a strong odor that is used to signify the approaching holidays, as well as cure all internal injuries.

Furbaitem.Pokedex Entry: It sits on shores and edges of water and stabs fish with its tail to capture them. They are often found alongside fisherman.

Purruse.Pokedex Entry: It sits on the edge of bodies of water and uses its tail to lure other fish to itself. The end of its tail is able to open and close, giving the illusion of being a live fish.

Dahma.Pokedex Entry: They are usually seen training either themselves or other Pokemon near the water. It is able to predict its opponents' next move and counter it.

Dahlla.Pokedex Entry: Dahlla often relax themselves by soaking in tepid water. The orbs on its back are able to give wisdom to anyone that touches them.

Sprunk.Pokedex Entry: By drinking large amounts of water, it can muster enough energy to spray from its mouth and tail simultaneously. When dehydrated, their coat turns into a pale-greenish color.

Sloris.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's fingers and toes are covered in small toxic spikes. They move very slowly, but make up for it with great accuracy and strength.

Lorisept.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon spray a toxic fluid from its palms when agitated. They are slow, but tactical hunters, waiting until prey is close before poisoning it with one bite.

Mullurk.Pokedex Entry: The fins on its head are made of keratin. They allow Mullurk to sense others' body heat. These Pokemon are the most common ones found in all of Ocramia, as they are able to survive in all types of water.

Vibrine.Pokedex Entry: They swim in sync with each other while underwater. In Summer, they are often seen jumping out of water in a dancing-like formation.

Walala.Pokedex Entry: Their feet have special pads that allow them to walk up and down the sides of objects and buildings without trouble. When they sleep, they tuck their arms, legs, and tail into their body and topple over, giving the appearance of a striped monolith.

Patterok.Pokedex Entry: When threatened, they are able to expand their waists in order to intimidate. They are able to pound large boulders into dust with continuous punches.

Helodra.Pokedex Entry: Jewel makers use their beads, which contain toxins, to make necklaces and earrings. Their tongues are long and sharp, allowing them to deliver a dose of venom instantly into the body.

Beadread.Pokedex Entry: Their beads are full of toxins that can paralyze the muscles in your body. All jewelry makers attempt to get beads to make necklaces and earrings, but end up getting paralyzed from bite wounds.

Skinner.Pokedex Entry: They keep their shed skin on their bodies in order to deflect attacks. Their venom isn't that potent, so they just rely on the sharpness of their fangs to deal damage.

Anigvis.Pokedex Entry: They are able to squeeze through the tightest of cracks in order to enter residences and infect the inhabitants. The germs and bacteria in its body are extremely powerful.

Vibrani.Pokedex Entry: It uses its tail to trip victims and licks them to paralyze them. Their vibrant colors act as a warning sign to those who attempt to come close to them.

Armorink.Pokedex Entry: The poison it secretes from its spikes is used in lethal injections. Their colors may seem dull, but they can signal each other using the lights that they emit from their tails.

Poissom.Pokedex Entry: Poissom's saliva has the capability to cure any poison damage. The irony in them is that their fur is very dusty and full of toxins, but their bite can dispel poison from the body!

Wiskra.Pokedex Entry: They follow the orders of Musneak and try their hardest to impress it. They emit a poisonous gas from their fur that can stop up the noses of those who inhale it.

Bumpeck.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are extremely dangerous, as they are able to give you chicken pox as soon as contact is made. They never stop scratching their little bodies, leaving numerous scars and scratches.

Contagizz.Pokedex Entry: One flap of these Pokemon's wings can infect an entire town with a virus. They never stop scratching themselves, making them vulnerable to attack, but it is so dangerous that no Pokemon dare to touch it, not even with long distance attacks.

Rashin.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies have a virus inside that causes their skin to splotch. They have the urge to scratch, but their arms are too small.

Burinash.Pokedex Entry: They use their large arms to scratch their skin, which only worsens their condition. Ingesting their skin flakes unknowingly can make you sick for a week.

Flead.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies secrete a toxic substance that keeps them safe from enemies. They create burrows by eating dirt and stones inside of caves.

Cyanice.Pokedex Entry: Being scratched by these Pokemon will cause you to be very sick. Their sweat is extremely toxic and can cause paralysis and intense vomiting if it makes contact with skin.

Egosumobi.Pokedex Entry: They latch onto unsuspecting people and Pokemon, releasing a toxin into their body that renders them incapable of moving on their own. They control other people and Pokemon by embedding their tentacles into their bodies and using their heads to guide them around.

Etonestri.Pokedex Entry: Latching onto Pokemon with their tendrils, they release a potent neurotoxin that erases the Pokemon's memories. They latch onto the heads of humans and drain them of all of their information.

Quissum.Pokedex Entry: It secretes a toxic gas and fluid that causes instant amnesia if it is inhaled or touched. It is able to enter a liquid state and enter bodies of water in order to enter the bodies of Pokemon and people.

Parasuck.Pokedex Entry: They attach themselves to larger Pokemon in order to feed off of their body fluids. They don't stop sucking until they feel full; any attempt to pry them off results in the victim becoming poisoned.

Sporish.Pokedex Entry: If you breathe in the spores emitted from this Pokemon, you will have excruciating headaches. After breathing in the spores, you experience many hallucinations.

Guspore.Pokedex Entry: Their spores are known to cause hallucinations. They are sometimes used by therapists in order to usher patients into expressing their problems.

Nibbid.Pokedex Entry: Its tongue is covered in over 100 potent toxins. If a NIBBID bites you, you have 24 hours to get healed or its poison will kill you.

Chomodo.Pokedex Entry: One lick from it is the equivalent to 1,000 doses of ARBOK venom. Its poison is toxic enough to melt the skin off of a human in two minutes.

Wastox.Pokedex Entry: WASTOX is the outcome of a experiment gone horribly wrong in which a pile of rocks was merged with a vat of toxic waste. Anything that they touch turns radioactive.

Paraka.Pokedex Entry: They sit underwater with the flower on its head on the surface in order to scare approaching trainers. They leak poison from their chest when they are threatened.

Kappote.Pokedex Entry: It is able to make one arm longer than the other by moving it through its body. One touch from them can make you sick for a month.

Toxappa.Pokedex Entry: They spray a toxic fluid from their wrists. They are known to be the cause of a massive epidemic that happened 10 years ago.

Slithood.Pokedex Entry: They are known to have reckless and violent tendencies, wrapping around enemies and injecting them with a powerful venom. Their hoods, made of their old skin, have different patterns depending on their location.

Entidead.Pokedex Entry: Many scientists and doctors have lost their lives trying to extract the proteins from this Pokemon's body in order to make antidotes. Their fur is full of a toxic dust, that causes an uncontrollable rash; the only way to cure it is to use its saliva.

Spewder.Pokedex Entry: They spray venom at anything that encroaches on its territory. The sac on its chest holds a toxic venom that can dissolve almost anything.

Trasmania.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon devour trash at a fast pace before leaving a horrible stench behind. Their sharp teeth can shred through dumpsters.

Junkrunch.Pokedex Entry: Their large mouths are able to fit 300 pounds of trash. Their jaws are strong enough to crush garbage trucks.

Musneak.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are hardly ever trustworthy unless they are owned by a trainer. One Musneak can command a single Muskuff and up to twenty Wiskra to do whatever it says at any time.

Hissune.Pokedex Entry: Their numerous tails have minds of their own and lash out when they are attacked from behind. It sometimes uses seduction techniques to get male species to follow it to its lair, where it paralyzes them with a kiss before devouring them.

Leadread.Pokedex Entry: The metal in its body is extremely toxic; any exposure to it causes one to become very ill. The lead in their body was once used in pencils, but was removed due to causing many kids to become sick.

Plumbeast.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are very poisonous, as contact with them could cause one to need immediate medical treatment. They blast molten lead from their arms to attack.

Delistan.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are able to change their colors in a rapid manner, mesmerizing those who see it. Their bodies are covered in a substance that causes hallucinations.

Moneten.Pokedex Entry: They extend their feelers to unimaginable lengths in order to inject their prey with a potent toxin. It sticks to the bottom of the sea, using their long, poisonous feelers to grab their prey.

Cubera.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are independent and never want to be given much attention. Their snake-like tails can actually attack and bite anyone that comes to close to it, giving them a non-lethal dose of venom that only eats away the skin.

Meravage.Pokedex Entry: They are merciless when hunting prey. Their tails bite the victim and paralyze it, giving them the time enjoy eating it while it is still alive.

Chimeroar.Pokedex Entry: They pretend to be asleep to give people and Pokemon a false sense of security as they move past, but their tails act as a second head and will inject them will a venom that causes instant paralysis. Their sharp teeth can shatter bones with just one crunch.

Epidose.Pokedex Entry: They give off a poisonous gas that is used by both plague and witch doctors in order to heal certain symptoms. While the gas they give off can help cure diseases, their bodies are completely infected.

Epidoc.Pokedex Entry: The gas that they release is very potent, but it is actually very helpful when it comes to curing diseases. Ironically, this Pokemon was the cause of a massive outbreak of disease in the Mirus Region long ago, and also served as the savior.

Yrucrem.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are extremely toxic, so trainers are advised to always be careful when handling this Pokemon. They melt into puddles when they are frightened.

Mercurath.Pokedex Entry: They are able to shift their bodies into different forms in order to get into the most toughest of places. They can blast poisonous liquid from their right arms as a defense mechanism.

Shelture.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon hide themselves in toxic coral branches in order to protect themselves from enemies. Unusually, they are able to survive underwater, yet they are weak against it.

Potonis.Pokedex Entry: Their entire bodies are covered in small toxic scales, so anything that touches it will automatically be poisoned. These Pokemon lie dormant near coral reefs, blending in with their surroundings in order to attack unsuspecting prey.

Monithur.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are known for their confident and serious natures. Their saliva, sweat, bubbles, and spikes are full of toxins, so touching these Pokemon will cause you to get sick.

Oshoradin.Pokedex Entry: Their saliva is highly corrosive. They live in swamps in large groups. The one with the largest crown is considered the leader.

Ringuzzle.Pokedex Entry: They are covered in a toxic film to keep themselves safe from possible predators. The are able to stretch their mouths open wide and belch poisonous bubbles that trap prey.

Pimpole.Pokedex Entry: The large bumps on their bodies are full of toxic fluids. Their bodies are covered in a viscous film that causes numerous bumps to appear wherever it has made contact on the human body.

Wartoad.Pokedex Entry: Touching the bumps on its body is said to cause similar bumps to appear on your body. Their bodies secrete a toxic film that causes nausea on contact.

Blemishab.Pokedex Entry: The slimy film that covers its body is known to cause rashes and bumps to appear on one's skin. All of Blemishab's bumps contain a poisonous fluid, so it will launch them at anyone and anything that enters its territory, covering them in the toxic ooze.

Polioka.Pokedex Entry: One of the Ultra Beasts, it has been observed destroying cities by leaving a toxic, sticky substance behind it as it moves. Appearing from another world, it absorbs buildings, humans, other Pokemon, and vehicles into its body to increase its size.

Echawn.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon's yawn can cause anyone in a city to fall asleep simultaneously. Its mouth has special glands inside of it that amplifies its yawn.

Zeeyawn.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon can amplify its yawn throughout an entire state. The rings on their tails can tighten, making the yawn be amplified longer.

Monori.Pokedex Entry: By achieving enlightenment, this Pokemon's attack power increases tenfold. Its fluffy tail is made of mind fog, which allows it to read people's minds.

Psytori.Pokedex Entry: They float on their tails, which are composed of multiple stressful mists that it gives off as it meditates. The pearls around its neck helps it stay calm.

Kakonas.Pokedex Entry: Born from an orange crystal that fell from the sky, it, along with Genzanas and Shoranas, are able to time travel. KAKONAS' specialty is the past and it is said that it cannot return those who go to the past if it disappears.

Genzanas.Pokedex Entry: A part of the orange crystal it is born from stays embedded in its chest, giving it is power. It can influence things in the present, and make them turn out positively or negatively, depending on the type of person you are.

Shoranas.Pokedex Entry: It is assumed that it was the one born as the leader over its siblings because of its old appearance. It was later revealed that it transports people to the future and can only work depending on Genzanas' antics.

Ryinka.Pokedex Entry: It is often mistaken as a bad omen because of its grisly and rugged appearance, when it actually kind-hearted. Its nose is able to detect truth and deceit within multiple people and Pokemon.

Caapaw.Pokedex Entry: Gnawing on a specific type of root gives them an extremely relaxed feeling that heightens their senses. They get extremely agitated if they are without their roots for too long.

Caaprowl.Pokedex Entry: They hate being away from their roots, so they always carry it in their mouths, limiting their hunting. If their roots are damaged or missing, they will not hesitate to attack anyone or anything they see.

Dianetha.Pokedex Entry: It is said to symbolize feminine beauty and knowledge, and will appear when there is lack of confidence. Their beautiful fluff is able to give knowledge to anyone who touches it, but this has not been confirmed.

Lullabaa.Pokedex Entry: Their cry can lull anyone into a deep sleep. Their wool is as soft as a cloud.

Sleebaa.Pokedex Entry: It creates duplicates of itself to make their opponents sleep. The wool it has it very soft and sometimes used for mattresses.

Slumbaa.Pokedex Entry: By manipulating the minds of its opponents, SLUMBAA could win a battle while sleeping. When a SLUMBAA does fall asleep, it can cause anyone who sees it to fall asleep as well.

Irisig.Pokedex Entry: People who own Irisig often have them float on the outside of their homes and businesses to prevent bad luck. It is said to stare into your soul and gain information about you.

Polyphase.Pokedex Entry: After these Pokemon are knocked out, they heal themselves immediately by changing form. These Pokemon are observed by scientists to see if their ability can be used to help humans.

Hueval.Pokedex Entry: It is constantly pursued by DELINKID, as they are enemies. They usually roam cities and towns in order to learn and later copy the customs of humans.

Valexcel.Pokedex Entry: Its large yellow brain is now exposed due to BRUTANOR. The more it learns, the larger its brain grows.

Merpsy.Pokedex Entry: Their hearts and brains are exceptionally large, causing them be very analytical and friendly. They are able to blow away entire buildings with one psychic wave.

Snoutrance.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon often lie next to their trainers while they are asleep, as it is the only time they are able to feed. They use their trunks to place a drowsing spell on their enemies and devour their dreams.

Sleepir.Pokedex Entry: Their white fur has numerous sensors that tell it where someone is sleeping. Their tusks turn pitch black when they are gorged with dreams.

Somnolun.Pokedex Entry: They use their white fur to suffocate others in order to induce involuntary slumber for its feeding. The dreams that it eats gets turned into dark, psychic energy that is shown in its tusks.

Ducklown.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon like entertaining large crowds with its tricks and antics. Their pranks often result in injury, but they simply laugh it off.

Tretina.Pokedex Entry: With their third eye, they can see into the future and past, as well as increase their strength. Getting bitten by one of these Pokemon is said to give a lot of knowledge.

Mystara.Pokedex Entry: A Pokemon that can bend the minds of others with the slightest gesture, they look for more ways to get powerful. Their third eye is a very weak point on their bodies, as it supplies them with majority of their power.

Propheak.Pokedex Entry: Most of their senses are highly advanced, but their eyesight is very poor. They use their whiskers to get around because of their poor eyesight.

Mousense.Pokedex Entry: Its limbs have a mind of their own, and only act on command of the central head when its whiskers are straight. Its highly developed senses make its blindness not a hindrance.

Kumbasia.Pokedex Entry: They emit bright lights to communicate with each other across long distances. Their bodies are gelatinous, but strong, being able to deflect even a Hyper Beam.

Hidowei.Pokedex Entry: They keep themselves hidden in their self-made shells made of trash and foliage. Its actual body is small and weak, so its shell gives it extra protection.

Covelurk.Pokedex Entry: The heads on their shells intimidate their opponents. Its soft, small body is located underneath the shell, and it only pops its head out when it meets someone friendly.

Kunskard.Pokedex Entry: Its horn fires high power psychic pulses that could cause ones brain to melt. Those that encounter this Pokemon have been known to acquire great knowledge.

Brushund.Pokedex Entry: They paint their typically white bodies with fluid that seeps from their tails and ears. Brushund despise having clean fur and decorate each other with markings to make themselves feel good.

Fasutagon.Pokedex Entry: It fought with TAWARTAGUN over whether the earth should fall into darkness or purity. After the battle, it was confined to a White Shard, which now resides in the Light Palace. It awakens when evil takes over most of the world, thus commencing the battle with TAWARTAGUN once again.

Nemoro.Pokedex Entry: They hypnotize enemies my moving in a special pattern and flashing its multiple colors. They are very dopey Pokemon who will take pleasure in bumping into coral reefs.

Goofin.Pokedex Entry: They spend their time playfully attacking each other with orbs of color. It sways in a hypnotic motion in order to confuse its enemies.

Kitsphere.Pokedex Entry: The orb in their tails are the source of their power. If they lose their orbs, they grow very weak and depressed.

Orbrillia.Pokedex Entry: They protect the orbs in their furry tails with their lives The orbs in their tails supply them with ample knowledge.

Marigan.Pokedex Entry: When all life was in danger due to complete and utter chaos, this Pokemon is said to have reset everything to avoid it. Its body is small, but it is harder than chromium and extremely heavy; without its abilities, it would be unable to move at all.

Petu_Muchi.Pokedex Entry: It is said that touching its tusks causes a feeling of freedom to wash over whoever touched them. The calmest of the 'Fiendish Four', it remains placid until approached aggressively.

Glystone.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon float around ancient ruins, pretending to be rare artifacts. Grave robbers find these Pokemon, expecting them to be artifacts, but they are actually living beings.

Stonivate.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon use their antennae on their face to sense their surroundings. The number of cracks on their body determines how old they are.

Gravonevis.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon gather in groups during full moons and absorb energy in their antennae. When angered, its antennae glow and they fling people into the air as if they're weightless.

Aqusus.Pokedex Entry: They walk on the water's surface as if they are looking for something. Their green eyes are said to project images that only it can see.

Susparill.Pokedex Entry: They run on the water's surface at high speeds and disappear from view. It is believed that they travel to an alternate dimension when they disappear.

Orbro.Pokedex Entry: It uses the floating orbs around it to amplify its Psychic-type power. Its body is as hard as diamond and can't be scratched.

Doublorb.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can frighten its opponents because if both heads are aligned, they can give the appearance of being eyeballs with arms. This Pokemon is formed when one of ORBRO's floating orbs attaches itself to its tail.

Quadross.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is formed when the orbs floating in the palms of DOUBLORB attach to them. They are able to blast beams from each eye and the opening between them.

Tarespo.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are born on the sticks they float on. Their yellow eyes are said to enable them to sense anything that will happen in the past, present, or future as well as give them mystical powers.

Espowtar.Pokedex Entry: Their eyes are more powerful, and allow them to see into anybody's past or future. According to old folktales, an Espowtar is able to destroy a person's past, causing them to vanish into thin air.

Watullius.Pokedex Entry: Fully grown, it is able to to walk perfectly on all fours and on two legs. It is able to scale waterfalls and create giant holes in the sea using its magic orbs in order to catch prey.

Tikeye.Pokedex Entry: They are highly recognized as guide Pokemon because it is able to show people the errors that they make in the future. They can sense hostility and will match it by blasting beams from the mouth on its body.

Doseyedo.Pokedex Entry: They are said to read auras and bend ones mind to their will. They use their eyes to view into the past, present, and future.

Pseye.Pokedex Entry: It is said to be the wisest Rock-type Pokemon. The multiple eyes on its body are the source of it massive power.

Trics.Pokedex Entry: They are able to make themselves invisible thanks to the red gem on their chests. They are often mistaken for ghosts when they float and disappear right before your eyes.

Phokus.Pokedex Entry: They vanish into thin air because of the refracting light from their gem. They scare trainers and their Pokemon when in the water because of their large fins.

Lunabbi.Pokedex Entry: Said to be from another planet, these Pokemon are researched by scientists fluently. They are able to make clones of themselves by flashing the lights in its body.

Pennec.Pokedex Entry: Their origins are linked to an explosion that occurred at a mint. They use their mental prowess to impress their trainers.

Daipen.Pokedex Entry: Their brains have linked together, unfortunately connecting their bodies in the process. Their combined brainpower is strong enough to blast away a stadium.

Haecus.Pokedex Entry: They always keep themselves cloaked in order to keep their eyes from being seen. The magic tricks that they do always end up causing a negative effect.

Badical.Pokedex Entry: Gazing into their eyes gives a sense of uneasiness that lasts a lifetime. Their tricks are very dangerous.

Magishun.Pokedex Entry: Their tricks always last a lifetime and cause nothing but pain. The orbs on its body contain most of its power.

Sharite.Pokedex Entry: It was discovered in a crater found in a field three centuries ago. The crystal shards in its body give off a strange aura.

Meteron.Pokedex Entry: They have to ability to travel to and fro from space without difficulty. The crystals adorning its body are often sought after, though they are easily protected due to its strength and durability.

Scripen.Pokedex Entry: By staring at its glowing lights, these Pokemon can order you to do anything it wants. They are able to stick to any flat surface and effectively control anyone within a 10 mile radius.

Healish.Pokedex Entry: They were discovered in the same place that all Potions are manufactured. These Pokemon resemble Potions, leading to groups of them being captured and put in Pokemon Centers while asleep.

Maxious.Pokedex Entry: They absorb water through their flat bottoms, which they then turn into medicine with psychic energy. They float around looking for people to heal.

Aquaror.Pokedex Entry: It is able to summon rain by moving its eyebrows. In Saigo myths, it is known to put out intense fires by drenching them in rain.

Felifevo.Pokedex Entry: A Legendary Pokemon that focuses on ancestry and growth, it is believed to have created a common ancestor to both humans and Pokemon that adapted over time. It is said that evolution stones exist because of it.

Peccarious.Pokedex Entry: They can create violent tornadoes made of water by blasting water from their palms and controlling it mentally. They have been known to control the minds of weaker Pokemon and put them in dangerous situations as a form of training.

Kwarzite.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are highly recognized by the crystals on its head and back. Their crystals glow when they are threatened.

Mortierok.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's crystals are extremely valuable, as they glow white according to emotion. They are sought by miners because they are known to know where the rarest minerals are located.

Cragmodon.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are known to guard precious and valuable crystals in caves and mountains by firing rocks at intruders. Their durable, sturdy bodies are able to deflect different attacks.

Jarotion.Pokedex Entry: Its 'hands' are actually heads that perform the same functions as a normal being. It floats around ruins, eating the worn down structures.

Stalloway.Pokedex Entry: They stand motionless in caves, observing everything that happens inside. They are mostly nocturnal and will travel at night in order to eat cold sand.

Lagmine.Pokedex Entry: They sleep in crevices on the ceilings of caves. They enjoy falling on unsuspecting people and Pokemon and injuring them.

Hournbyl.Pokedex Entry: They spend most of their time running into trees and tearing them down to eat their leaves and fruit. These Pokemon often travel in large groups.

Gargone.Pokedex Entry: Its arms are always extended in a zombie-like fashion. It always stares blankly from the tops of buildings, observing everything it sees.

Stonfant.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are very unique in that there are more than nine different forms of them because of the different stones they each have. It is supposedly stated that if you catch a STONFANT that has your birthstone, you will be lucky, but only in your birth month.

Stonite.Pokedex Entry: They can deliver devastating blows from their disjointed arms when they are agitated. Multiple forms of this Pokemon are sought out by collectors.

Lunite.Pokedex Entry: They are said to have come from the moon. It launches the smaller rock like a cannon ball.

Ecluna.Pokedex Entry: Apparently they were discovered in a desert crater over 500 years ago. These Pokemon are able to absorb light, as well make an entire area dark whenever it wants.

Eradorn.Pokedex Entry: Existing more than a million years ago, these Pokemon were known for their sharp horns and odd body marks. They battled each other using their horns to see who was more dominant.

Tripierce.Pokedex Entry: It is constantly debated whether Tripierce inspired the creation of bricks or not. Tripierce's horns were allegedly strong enough to pierce bedrock, making them very dangerous to approach.

Coalite.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are known to be proud collectors of coal, making them a miner's best bet for working fast. These Pokemon are hardly ever really seen in caves because of their body's color.

Compacoal.Pokedex Entry: The diamonds that are embedded in its body are a result of it living compressed underground for years. They eat all of the coal and gems that they find around their homes.

Royun.Pokedex Entry: They stand still as a statue in caves if undisturbed. At night, they are sometimes seen marching in a straight line towards large mountains in a zombie-like trance.

Rhinaut.Pokedex Entry: They are sometimes seen charging into large boulders in order to strengthen their small bodies. If trained well, they are able to toss boulders or humans over 5 feet away from them.

Boldrit.Pokedex Entry: Their harsh skin make them suitable for mountainous areas. Their skin is hard enough to withstand a Focus Punch.

Dexther.Pokedex Entry: Because their hands were unable to be used to the full potential, they relied on their tail feathers to grip objects. They went extinct over 20,000 years ago, but have slowly been reintroduced into the modern age thanks to technology.

Epidextrous.Pokedex Entry: Their hands have now transformed into wings, but because it has become so accustomed to using its tail and legs, it hardly uses them. They are able to hang upside down for hours using their tails.

Sauree.Pokedex Entry: Back in these Pokemon's time period, they always got themselves into trouble. Their reckless natures are what scientists believe the cause of their extinction are.

Torvore.Pokedex Entry: Because their arms offered little help to gather food, they resorted to headbutting trees and attacking other Pokemon for food. Their extremely large legs were able to shatter bones with one kick.

Pebbole.Pokedex Entry: They are often mistaken for normal pebbles and rocks. They burrow into the ground to avoid being stepped on.

Kroakore.Pokedex Entry: They create rocky, layered armor from metamorphic rock that they find. Their blood is full of heavy minerals, making them very sluggish.

Mineiss.Pokedex Entry: They are heavy and strong enough to smash through bedrock. They are often hunted down in order to collect their rare droppings.

Rockey.Pokedex Entry: It is unknown where this Pokemon first originated from and what its key-like tail unlocks. It resides in deep caves, using its key as a shovel in order to dig out small gems and pebbles to eat.

Geotyne.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are strong enough to survive an explosion. These Pokemon spend most of their time sleeping with their eyes open in caves.

Perimetur.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon lie inside cave floors, blending in with their surroundings to avoid detection. They feed by eating other stones and pebbles on the ground.

Constrokt.Pokedex Entry: It coils around the necks of larger Pokemon vibrates the rocks on its body in order to dig into their skin. It has been observed wrapping smaller Pokemon with its left side, and larger Pokemon with its right, as the amount of rocks embedded in its body differ on each side.

Wrapyrith.Pokedex Entry: It wraps around larger Pokemon and digs into their bodies using its rocky skin. It is extremely difficult to escape its grasp once it is wrapped around you, as removing it often results in multiple scars.

Bonaw.Pokedex Entry: Their strong jaws allow them to snap bones like twigs. Under Tibiate's command, they harvest all of the bones of their prey in order to both eat and adorn themselves with them.

Spinorus.Pokedex Entry: It is said to have existed 20, 000 years ago. Their spikes were once used for weapons, as they could never shatter or bend.

Kentrike.Pokedex Entry: It is able to fire its spikes at high speeds and they always instantly grow back. Their bodies are covered in piercing sharp spikes.

Dimeno.Pokedex Entry: The fins on its head and back helped it sense ocean currents over 30,000 years ago. Their fins gave them a scary illusion of being a dangerous creature.

Dimoiston.Pokedex Entry: Said to have lived over 30,000 years ago, this Pokemon relied on its fins for survival. It blends into water in order to catch prey.

Stygilil.Pokedex Entry: This ancient Pokemon used horrific tactics to catch and devour its prey. It skewered its prey on its extendable horns and waited for them to stop moving before scraping them off and eating them savagely.

Styxol.Pokedex Entry: It rammed into prey and skewered them on its horns. If its prey was still alive after an attack, it would take pleasure in devouring it while it was still alive.

Relcalf.Pokedex Entry: They used to roll around on the sea floor, as their tail fins didn't allow them to swim that well. Their chests are extremely hard because of the rigid bones underneath.

Stellow.Pokedex Entry: Thanks to the membrane on its tail, it was now able to swim somewhat better. They were hunted for their hard bones, which were used to create weapons and armor.

Gobslobber.Pokedex Entry: Their tackle is hard enough to knock out teeth. They often lick themselves when they are exhausted in order to keep themselves strong.

Suckob.Pokedex Entry: They spin at high speeds, giving off a sweet scent in order to calm those who smell it. They often bury their thin legs in the ground of caves and shoot themselves upwards to scare those who get close.

Fizerok.Pokedex Entry: The pebbles that levitate around them have a sweet, divine taste. It is able to launch the pebbles around it like bullets and make them explode on contact.

Gravizzon.Pokedex Entry: It controls the pebbles around it so it is able to launch them like speeding bullets. It sometimes serves as a guardian and helper to candy makers who need more sweetness in their treats.

Kinbread.Pokedex Entry: As soon as it is seen, it takes off running out of fear. This Pokemon came to be after a scientist dropped a cookie into an unstable mixture.

Solidia.Pokedex Entry: Its body is so strong that it can crush a tank just by stepping on it. The diamonds on its body are sought after by jewel thieves, but it protects itself by throwing them out of their habitats.

Gocha.Pokedex Entry: Gocha used to attach itself to other Pokemon and drain them of all of their energy. Its plant-like appearance fools those who encounter it, leaving them open to a swift attack.

Atacha.Pokedex Entry: In groups of twenty, Atacha used to sink their tentacles into the bodies of larger Pokemon, draining them of all of their fluids. Its species is said to have gone extinct due to larger Pokemon stomping on them unknowingly.

Rokko.Pokedex Entry: Their constant diet of stones help them digest food easier. They have the ability to upchuck stones at will, firing them at opponents.

Reptone.Pokedex Entry: They eat a number of stones all at once before they go after large prey. Their spikes absorb heat into their bodies, which they then use to fire rocks from their maws like cannonballs.

Crinovor.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are quick tempered and will rampage through large cities if angered. They toss boulders over 45 feet away from itself in order to help.

Opaluck.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are great healers that only try to offer help to others. The stone on their tails can give off positive energy to those feeling glum.

Opalique.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are bad news, as they always attempt to lose and give off bad luck. The stone on their tails can give off negative energy to anyone.

Dekrab.Pokedex Entry: They find and attach sediment to their shells in order to further protect their fragile bodies. Rare minerals are often found embedded in their carapaces, leading treasure hunters to catch them and remove their carapaces by force.

Sedipace.Pokedex Entry: Their extremely strong bodies can crush a tank with one tackle. Almost every season, they switch their minerals out for new ones in order to make themselves feel more comfortable.

Trilopod.Pokedex Entry: They swim on the surface of water like jetskis. The hard scales on its body protect it from enemies; the middle of its back remains exposed, however.

Trilodon.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are covered in hard scales that are as hard as diamonds. Its feeds on plants and other organisms that enter its mouth as it dives underwater.

Bluntalon.Pokedex Entry: When angered, they run wild, swinging their heads violently. They are able to file their noses to a point using the edges of their arms, but they always end up returning blunt after a few hours.

Monolash.Pokedex Entry: Swinging its arms, it is able to slice clean through solid steel. Its fallen claws can be collected and used to create weapons.

Excalibold.Pokedex Entry: It was said that this Pokemon has existed since the medieval times. Attempting to pry the sword out of its back has become a well-known challenge.

Godzalla.Pokedex Entry: They have been known to devour mountains one bite at a time. Their 16 foot tall bodies make them extremely slow, but their durability makes up for it.

Tibiate.Pokedex Entry: When dealing with larger prey, they hunt in packs of ten, flaying their victim in order to collect their bones. A Tibiate's teeth are so strong that they are able to bite through tempered steel like paper.

Skullunge.Pokedex Entry: They adorn themselves with the bones of their victims in order to assert their place in the pack. The one with the most bones serves as the pack leader. With their strong jaws and sharp teeth, they are able to crush a human skull with just one brutal snap.

Fogold.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are comprised of a mineral that resembles gold, so they are often captured and sold. However, the mineral is worthless. They spit out mineral dust in self-defense.

Pyraud.Pokedex Entry: When discovered in caves, they immediately throw nearby Fogold at the intruders. The minerals embedded in their bodies resemble gold, making them highly sought after. They sometimes break off pieces of their body so that hunters will leave them alone.

Chompurt.Pokedex Entry: Their jaws are strong enough to break metal. Their shells are made of solidified sand and dirt that is extremely hard to break.

Lasame.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon love to hang around the necks of their trainers, acting as a living necklace. They like to swim in water and scare other Pokemon by clinging to their necks and legs.

Luminesin.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are extremely durable, making it unable for them to chip or feel any pain. The glowing orbs on its body are extremely valuable and are often used to make jewelry.

Craniun.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon headbutt Clammince and crack their shells open to feed on their insides. They stay dormant at the bottom of lakes and ponds, as well as oceans, pretending to be old skulls; when prey approaches, they paralyze it with a glare before melting it with digestive juices.

Deepress.Pokedex Entry: Their bony spines are very sharp, being able to slice through a Maliciark's body with little resistance. Moving its skull 'cap' down gives them the appearance of a swimming skeleton, striking fear in those who see it.

Maflano.Pokedex Entry: Using its tail as a weapon, MAFLANO can defend itself. Its tail is small and stubby at birth, but it grows blunter as it grows.

Macernio.Pokedex Entry: Once used alongside knights, this Pokemon can cause massive damage by making its tail enlarge It slashes quick, causing critical damage.

Virubic.Pokedex Entry: They reside in a cyber world where no one is able to find it without the help of computer specialists. It was said to have been created to solve an unknown software problem;it seems to have failed...

Virubic2.Pokedex Entry: An upgraded version of Virubic thanks to an Ionatt's influence, it combats them in order to fix computer software. It has been very effective, though it is known to have a few errors.

Scampick.Pokedex Entry: They help trainers make correct decisions as they continue their journey. They always take time to decide what they want and sometimes pick up random objects without knowing it.

Virubic3.Pokedex Entry: Once a thriving solution to a software issue, it has been modified by an inexperienced developer. They link up to others of their kind and are powerful enough to short circuit a supercomputer.

Elephium.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are known for their playful nature and tackle other trainers and Pokemon out of joy. Their bodies are extremely tough, unable to be melted even by high temperature flames.

Bracaderm.Pokedex Entry: They have been known to charge at each other in order to help build courage and strength. Their tusks are indestructible, so when they inevitably fall off, they are used as weapons.

Emasei.Pokedex Entry: After a long war, this Pokemon helped the Mirus Region with a roar that brought a shower of gold. Out of the three beasts, it is shown to be the most courageous and modest.

Jawreck.Pokedex Entry: Its bite is strong enough to crush a tank. It was made to keep wild Pokemon away from food supplies, but it seems to have malfunctioned...

Cobalaw.Pokedex Entry: It lays on its stomach in order to absorb sunlight to strengthen itself. It was discovered in an abandoned factory more than 32 years ago and has remained unchanged.

Nicklank.Pokedex Entry: It absorbs heat and light with the crest on his head. It lives by eating iron through its claws.

Allodon.Pokedex Entry: Its claws have minds of their own and will fly wildly after a target until it is able to strike it hard. It taunts Fire-types until they are so upset that they attack, which doesn't do anything but increase its power.

Jiyugine.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon remains underground, dormant, until it senses the energy of Minsurro and Wasepach with its spikes. Its hard as steel body is able to withstand any blow.

Ralam.Pokedex Entry: Its horn-like arms help amplify its cry, making it suitable for watching over banks and jewelry shops. It was discovered in an old workshop where alarm clocks and traps were produced.

Troubot.Pokedex Entry: Created by a lonely scientist, this Pokemon was programmed to be an obedient companion, but it malfunctioned... They cause problems and trouble for any trainer and other Pokemon, especially when in large cities.

Blastro.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon blast other Pokemon and buildings with different beams based on how it is feeling. They can launch their hands and head away from their main body to terrorize civilians.

Platinew.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies can resist even the highest degrees of heat. They eat nuts and bolts for nourishment.

Goldeer.Pokedex Entry: Their horns are highly sought after by collectors because they are made of pure gold. They devour any metal that they find.

Minelope.Pokedex Entry: Its body is as hard as diamonds. These Pokemon are often used by miners, as they are able to locate minerals that are embedded as deep as 500 ft below the ground.

Scopure.Pokedex Entry: They are known to guard special artifacts that are hidden away. They float around in their scoop-like vehicles and launch those who get too close.

Tinture.Pokedex Entry: By shaking their chimes, they emit sounds that are able to soothe the soul and cleanse auras. If one of their chimes breaks off, it finds something metallic to take its place.

Slistar.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are often found embedded in trees and large buildings, as they like to fling themselves from beaches towards passersby. Their arms are extremely sharp and can slice clean through iron bars.

Apexpin.Pokedex Entry: Rotating at high speeds, they are able to slice clean through a semi in one swipe. They release spikes at high speeds while spinning.

Wishoot.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are said to have come from outer space. According to those who encounter it, it will grant wishes only to those who are pure of heart.

Gemeeny.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is nearly impossible to find, as they are often embedded in cave walls, disguised as minerals. Covect and Xecovitaga are always watching over them, ensuring that they are never taken from the caves that they call home.

Covect.Pokedex Entry: They are very protective of the gems in their caves. There was an account of someone who lost their arm while trying to steal from its cave.

Xecovitaga.Pokedex Entry: They occupy caves that have a vast quantity of valuable minerals and jewels, dedicating their lives to protecting them. Those who are caught taking gems from its territory are often hunted down and eradicated via unknown circumstances.

Jawtle.Pokedex Entry: They devour metal objects on a regular basis. Their powerful jaws are strong enough to crush cars.

Marlord.Pokedex Entry: Its bill is strong enough to pierce through bedrock. They battle against one another, using their beak swords, in order to show their dominance.

Clammince.Pokedex Entry: They have been known to launch themselves at beach-goers for no reason other than mischief. They can spin themselves at high speeds in order for their blades to slash through tough structures, although they make themselves dizzy in the process...

Anchrease.Pokedex Entry: If released, it is said to anchor and restrain anyone that it sees fit for revenge. Because its dark power was far too grotesque and malicious, it was bound to an iron ball shrouded in a mysterious energy, restraining its pure power.

Garazor.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can chomp through coral like butter. The blades on its body help it slice and dice their prey for easy digestion.

Dripride.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are independent and only eat food that they get themselves. They train on their own and sometimes ignore their trainers.

Roarifice.Pokedex Entry: With a heart of steel and an intimidating glare, these Pokemon do not tolerate any foolish behavior, whether it be from their trainers or teammates. Their fins can slice through boat hulls with one slice.

Amplitune.Pokedex Entry: Legends speak of it having the ability to help deaf people hear once again. It is able to produce any number of sounds with the help of its horns.

Slisaw.Pokedex Entry: If they ever encounter blocked areas when underwater, they work together to eat away at the object in the way. They are able to float on the surface of water.

Tarrafin.Pokedex Entry: Their fins and teeth are 10x sharper than ax blades. They are able to tear apart submarines in mere seconds.

Platosar.Pokedex Entry: It is often hunted for its armor, which is melted down in order to create stronger armor and weapons. It has a rather sadistic demeanor, tossing smaller Pokemon and sometimes humans onto its back to stab them with its spikes.

Yorodaga.Pokedex Entry: Very sadistic, these Pokemon love charging towards smaller Pokemon and critically injuring them with their spikes. These Pokemon have a violent temperament and have absolutely no problem with harming their own trainers if upset.

Platyke.Pokedex Entry: PLATYKE love to eat sweet berries. They use their fins to communicate with each other.

Babara.Pokedex Entry: They use their fins to help them swim faster underwater. They are able to inhale and extract salt from water using their big nose.

Baraqua.Pokedex Entry: Their fins allow them to swim at unimaginable speeds. They use their tooth to crack open CLAMPERL and devour them.

Shrimpy.Pokedex Entry: Its body's not able to withstand even a punch. It swims at high speeds underwater and eats the kelp and algae that grows on the bottom.

Prawnip.Pokedex Entry: It travels in groups in order to defend itself better because of its weak exterior. Its sharp claws and frills make it a force to be reckoned with.

Osmomso.Pokedex Entry: The band around its body allows the water inside of it to move freely. If its band is removed, it goes back to being a regular sphere.

Difflow.Pokedex Entry: The bands on its body allow liquid to flow into each section, forming its appendages. The liquid that makes up its body is closely related to water, but scientists have yet to prove what it is.

Osmodon.Pokedex Entry: Its bands block the fluid flowing throughout its body, forming its muscles. It is able to move using its huge arms instead of using its petite legs.

Rivard.Pokedex Entry: It moves across the ocean floor searching for prey. Its eyes are heat-seeking, allowing it to see things based on their infrared signature.

Serpond.Pokedex Entry: It slithers through the sea looking for prey. Its slim body allows it to slip through cracks in rocks and reefs.

Absorage.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon live under the sea and use the pores on their bodies to absorb freshwater in order to gain nutrients. Their bodies are torn easily, but they regenerate quickly.

Sorbunge.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon's pores are powerful enough to absorb anything into its body. Its body is comparable to a black hole, as few things that go in hardly ever come back out.

Teenee.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon often beach themselves in order to play with children. They are nicknamed "Balloons of the Sea" because of their cute, chubby appearances and the way their tails' ribbon-like ends sway while they swim.

Ballatee.Pokedex Entry: It floats across the surface of water for fun. It can twirl its tail's ends like a propeller in order to move quickly underwater.

Kamikazin.Pokedex Entry: When a worldwide drought plagued the Earth, it is said that he refilled the oceans and seas. He purifies oceans by dipping his mustache into them.

Quendro.Pokedex Entry: They spend most of their time playing in or near the water. Their furry tails are said to be a symbol of peace and if they are droopy or oily, it is a sign that QUENDRO has been injured.

Draquatik.Pokedex Entry: It loves laying at the bottom of the sea, viewing all battles from the dark crevices it calls home. Using its crest and whiskers, it is able to read water currents and know when the water has been tainted.

Maroden.Pokedex Entry: It is a role model to younger Water-Pokemon because of its calm and confident nature. Their tails sway from side to side in order for it to get a good sense of direction.

Seltzea.Pokedex Entry: They are able to create giant waves by blasting water from its tail. Known as a calm and admirable leader, these Pokemon mentor others in order for them to show their true strength.

Baitrap.Pokedex Entry: It hides in the darkness of underwater caverns. The hook-like spine attached to its head can help in attracting its prey.

Bubalo.Pokedex Entry: They make bubbles with their tails depending on how their feeling. It tries very hard to be menacing and territorial, blasting bubbles at those who come too close, but its cute appearance makes it hard for it to be taken seriously.

Bufflow.Pokedex Entry: It is able to dive to remarkable depths on a single breath thanks to its bubbles. It is able to absorb water into its body and create large bubbles.

Wotter.Pokedex Entry: They travel in groups and take multiple things from towns and buildings. They cause mischief wherever they go, but their cute appearance covers that fact.

Sailott.Pokedex Entry: They watch over Wotter's heists and antics to make sure that all of them make it back. Using both of its eyes, it can't see that well, but when one of them is closed, they can see extremely well as if they are using binoculars.

Wataloo.Pokedex Entry: Its lower body isn't as developed as its upper body, so it has a diaper made of foam and bubbles to aid in its walking. When it is hurt, it absorbs water through its bubble diaper to heal itself.

Manasea.Pokedex Entry: It gives off a strange aura whenever it falls down. Despite its legs being fully developed, it still has trouble walking.

Mollusym.Pokedex Entry: Inside of each of their mouths is a very valuable pearl, which the SYMBIA inside helps protects from intruders. They work in a symbiotic relationship, the SYMBIA gets a home and the MOLLUSYM has protection.

Camodden.Pokedex Entry: They stay in damp areas, absorbing water into their humps through their hooves. The water stored in their humps gets heated by the pressure and releases steam that can be used to heal.

Amini.Pokedex Entry: They cover themselves with old umbrellas in order to protect themselves. When it is raining, they will happily leave their cover, but for any other reason, they will not leave.

Monarme.Pokedex Entry: The cover it has helps moves slide off of it. They sometimes stand still in storms in order to get their fill of water.

Symbit.Pokedex Entry: They tuck their arms and legs into their bodies to avoid blows. They inhabit ponds and swamps and are able to use mysterious powers.

Darroak.Pokedex Entry: When they are threatened, their chest markings glow and they use mysterious powers. They stay still and act like dolls to trick their enemies.

Taipho.Pokedex Entry: Many fisherman and travelers have been lost due to this Pokemon. It whips up whirlpools, typhoons, and tsunamis in order to cause major damage in Kisek.

Glaucute.Pokedex Entry: If one of its feelers tears of, they immediately grow back. The colors of their feelers change depending on their emotions or health statuses.

Zaleidus.Pokedex Entry: They are able to regenerate body parts that are torn off during battle. Their feelers are very sensitive an react to even the slightest gesture.

Glaureus.Pokedex Entry: Their feelers are able to sense the movement of water based on the air. Their bodies are large, but they are still able to get into the smallest crevice.

Chroblob.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are made up of a gooey substance that makes them sluggish and unappealing. They ingest large amounts of water so they are able to survive on land.

Pakisea.Pokedex Entry: It uses its fin to sense ocean currents, enabling it to predict when a storm is coming. Its mouth is full of sharp teeth that it uses to eat barnacles and coral under the sea.

Rodonto.Pokedex Entry: With its new body structure and paws, it can swim as fast as a torpedo. The foam around its arms and tail can surround its entire body to cushion blows.

Splashant.Pokedex Entry: They like to jump into water and play by splashing around. The float-like appendages on its body help it float in water.

Pachydro.Pokedex Entry: Their trunks can spray over 30 gallons of water at one time. Although they seem aggressive and arrogant, they are very caring of their young, as well as their trainers.

Piravage.Pokedex Entry: They travel in groups, devouring anything that moves. They have over 30 sharp teeth that can shred through iron.

Wamoo.Pokedex Entry: Their pearl-like tails are filled with salt water, which makes it able to conduct electricity. They are usually hunted for their horns, rings, and tags, but the hunters always fail.

Barkrest.Pokedex Entry: They will use their hand-like tails to help them do tasks, such as hunting, more efficiently. It is not really friendly towards humans and will not trust them until they prove their worth.

Palmutt.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are extremely swift and creepy, as they may stalk you with their tail-hand bared. They can hang from different supports and watch others fluently to get an understanding of their pattern.

Ricalarva.Pokedex Entry: They are captured and used to create ink for pens willingly. Mysterious markings that are seen underwater are said to be created by these Pokemon.

Inkala.Pokedex Entry: They can use their arms to draw and create symbols and makings. Its ink is said to be extremely pure and rich, making it worth thousands of dollars.

Hideocea.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can use all of their arms to move across the ocean floor. Their appearance alone makes trainers and other Pokemon stay away from it, even though it is strong.

Jigglo.Pokedex Entry: They reside on the sea floor, eating plankton and kelp to keep their insides and outsides squishy and moist. Their squishy little bodies can withstand even a nuclear blast.

Oozeal.Pokedex Entry: They move very slowly and interact by touching each other with their horns. Oozeal's mustache-like growth acts as a vacuum, sucking in small organisms from the seafloor.

Kaibash.Pokedex Entry: Only its outline may be seen at times, as it moves quickly to evade sight. Touching the end of its tail causes memory loss.

Festivast.Pokedex Entry: They are said to appear in times of great prosperity and victory in order to celebrate. There are organs inside of its body can glow different colors, giving the effect of a strobe light.

Shtryke.Pokedex Entry: Their arm movements are extremely quick and strong, especially when its raining. Despite it having small legs, it is still able to travel on them at high speeds and strike hard at its opponent.

Nedlar.Pokedex Entry: To rejuvenate themselves, they inhale the water in which they live directly into their bodies through their nostrils. They sometimes fight over territory, using their long noses as spears.

Wadrop.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon have inflatable paw pads that allow it to walk and run on water. It has the ability to cause small rainstorms that only last a day.

Slippour.Pokedex Entry: The slippery film covering its body is great for plant growth. When on land, it is a bit sluggish and cannot easily get away from predators, but in the sea, it is very swift and is able to escape easier.

Eumian.Pokedex Entry: Typhoons occur as it speeds through the ocean at 500 mph. It is able to carry humans and Pokemon down to 50,000 ft below sea level without issue.

Squirtama.Pokedex Entry: Using their snouts, they are able to spray water at a very high accuracy. They are very calm and relaxed Pokemon who take pleasure in laying on the edge of bodies of water.

Mandren.Pokedex Entry: Their large arms are filled with air, allowing them to float through water. Their feet allow them to grip onto any surface, giving them room to attack from any location.

Claweird.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are able to boil water inside of their bodies and launch their claws at opponents. After they fire their claws, they act as heat seeking missiles, not stopping until they reach their target.

Ambishell.Pokedex Entry: Boiling water in their bodies, they launch their claws, which act like heat-seeking missiles, towards their targets. Their claws also act as fangs, draining their targets of their fluids before coming back to them.

Selagrow.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can swell to the size of a blimp by inhaling large amounts of water. The holes in its fins help its arms stay the same size as they grow.

Suckur.Pokedex Entry: They stroll across the ocean floor, sucking and eating anything they find. Their bodies are very soft, allowing them to squeeze into tight spaces.

Dorislurp.Pokedex Entry: Their soft bodies are able to absorb anything that it wants to eat. Using their feelers, they can feel the flow of ocean currents in order to find more food sources.

Vachroma.Pokedex Entry: They absorb nutrients into their bodies without using their mouths. They have large mouths that are able to suck up anything within a 250 mile radius.

Camerio.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon never forget what they see thanks to their excellent memories. When it witnesses something, it will stand still and stare at the scene until it is over, often getting attacked in the process.

Fringeaw.Pokedex Entry: They fool unsuspecting prey into coming close and surprise them with their large jaws. Many people who find these Pokemon are scared to actually make contact, as they are very aggressive towards humans.

Soakitt.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are often found in small ponds and lakes playing with each other. Their whiskers allow them to sense approaching rainstorms.

Shoom.Pokedex Entry: They spray water at different pressures based on its mood. They have extremely high precision and accuracy with their spray moves.

Arroe.Pokedex Entry: Using its cannon-like body, it launches itself towards its enemies. Blasting their heads out of their bodies, they tear through boulders with ease.

Rodfrey.Pokedex Entry: Fisherman absolutely despise these Pokemon because they clip their fishing lines and nets, releasing the Pokemon they were wanting to catch. Using their sharp claws, they can snip through any material.

Blashrimp.Pokedex Entry: They fire high pressure streams of water of of their mouths and claws by absorbing water through their absorbent legs. They are almost always seen with a Baygo, as they act as lookouts for them.

Baygo.Pokedex Entry: Their eyes act as flashlights underwater, allowing it to see easier. They work with Blashrimp, acting as lookouts for them in case larger predators get close.

Hoskunk.Pokedex Entry: Using their tails, they can adjust the pressure of their water sprays. To show affection, they coil their tails around each other and spray water simultaneously.

Cresshor.Pokedex Entry: They always have a serious attitude, no matter what is going on. They sometimes walk straight into oceans without stopping and stand at the bottom in order to compose themselves.

Kodd.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is highly praised in certain cities for pushing an heir, who was lost at sea, back to safety. The bubbles on their bodies inflate and deflate when they are exhausted.

Bubbrine.Pokedex Entry: Their bodies are very slippery, allowing them to get away from predators in a cinch. By rubbing their soapy hands together, they create a barrage of bubbles to distract their foes.

Rabubble.Pokedex Entry: They are able to control the bubbles they create, telling them where and when to explode. Making contact with water causes it to foam and bubble immediately.

Dolphish.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can't feel any pain, as their miniscule brains do not register any feelings. They spend majority of their time beaching themselves and flopping in the sand until someone knocks them back into the water.

Serpentide.Pokedex Entry: They thrive in shallow waters, feeding off of the skin of swimmers. Their large back fins give them a more hostile and dangerous appearance when they are relatively harmless.

Washao.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are obsessed with cleanliness and tend to go overboard with it. They secrete soapy fluid from their fur-covered hooves and tails in order to clean their environments.

Kalflow.Pokedex Entry: It often spends its time splashing in muddy water The gills on the back of its head allow it to stay underwater for long periods of time.

Koiler.Pokedex Entry: They work tirelessly through day and night constructing dens for smaller aquatic Pokemon for protection. These Pokemon never sleep, so even if they don't have the strength to work anymore, they continue anyway, causing some to die of exhaustion.

Swinerve.Pokedex Entry: Swinerve have a very cowardly disposition, running away from fights with even the weakest of opponents. When they gain your trust, they are known to battle as hard as they can.

Boarine.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon always remain calm, cool, and collected even through the most difficult of times. They radiate a special aura that is known to ease anxiety and stress.

Trumpisces.Pokedex Entry: It releases a loud honking sound that deafens its predators, allowing it to make a quick getaway. The volume and tone of their honks are dependent on their diets and size.

Droprin.Pokedex Entry: It can cause an unholy flood accidentally just by crying. They can create small rain clouds that will constantly follow you.

Donpour.Pokedex Entry: The raindrops on their heads act as helmets, reflecting every attack. These Pokemon can stir rain clouds by twirling their fingers.

Jawark.Pokedex Entry: Their skin is as rough as sandpaper. They have 50 razor sharp teeth that are considered extremely valuable by islanders.

Pierciark.Pokedex Entry: Scraping against these Pokemon causes you to lose skin. Despite only four being seen, they have over 100 teeth in their maws that are able to crush anything from concrete to tempered steel.

Maliciark.Pokedex Entry: They have over 300 teeth that are powerful enough to crush a semi. Their extremely rough skin is able to rip skin from bone.

Pirott.Pokedex Entry: They command Wotter and Sailott to steal and bring back any valuable items, which it keeps in a special place. It uses its iron claws, which can switch paws at any time, to intimidate those it is stealing from.

Alikrokor.Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is able to snap a boat in half with its powerful jaws. They are very vicious and territorial, attacking anything and anyone that invades its territory.

Gatorage.Pokedex Entry: They will shred anything that comes into their territory into pieces. They have random bursts of anger and will attack anything that is nearby.

Barbaliga.Pokedex Entry: They will randomly attack people in cities and town. They use their sharp teeth and claws to dismember and mutilate their prey.

Mizar.Pokedex Entry: The only account of this Pokemon's actual face being seen was 200 years ago. They have been known to damage boats and ships with their barbed tails, causing them to sink.

Damoat.Pokedex Entry: They snatch up fisherman with their spiked tails and drag them into the depths of the sea. Its body is extremely large, so usually only their tails are seen.

Brutear.Pokedex Entry: Despite their hostile appearance, these Pokemon are actually very friendly. Their teeth are able to shred a tank.

Coltide.Pokedex Entry: They sing a song as they sit on the edge of the ocean, watching the currents and waves. They use their front legs more efficiently than their hind legs.

Surfoal.Pokedex Entry: Their hind legs have devolved, limiting their movements on land. They are able to fly and move swiftly underwater by firing water from their hooves and gliding with their fins.

Stallake.Pokedex Entry: They are known to protect Pokemon under the sea, acting as a guardian. Deep sea divers who unknowingly enter its territory get caught in whirlpools.

Swanite.Pokedex Entry: They dance in ponds and lakes at night. Figurisk sometimes gather around them and admire what they think is pure beauty.

Typhang.Pokedex Entry: One glare from their eyes can paralyze an opponent, giving them time to do what they please. They are extremely observant and will watch you until it is ready to strike.

Kwakky.Pokedex Entry: They are usually found gathered in swamps and marshes, feeding off of the grime and dirt. Kwakky's lower feathers are hardly ever clean because of their environment's usual lack of clean water.

Dukwee.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon rely on the nutrients and usability of the dirt and soil around their swamp environments for survival. Dukwee are known to defend themselves, as well as Kwakky, from predators and attackers using mud and sticks.

Gooserene.Pokedex Entry: They are often owned by rich families, being used as caretakers for small children. It is said that if you manage to catch one, you will prosper.

Fountank.Pokedex Entry: Their tails are able to spray water from all six of their ends. They envelop themselves in water and charge towards their enemies when furious.

Lepoprine.Pokedex Entry: It creates a tornado of bubbles by swinging its ears around rapidly. The bubbles that it creates are highly explosive and have enough force to vaporize a tank.

Ribbrite.Pokedex Entry: Using their ribbon-like tentacles, they constrict their prey tightly, wringing out their bodily fluids. Divers who unknowingly wander into their territory are never heard from again.

Tasseloza.Pokedex Entry: Using their many tentacles, they are able to tear apart and crush the bones of their prey. If you unknowingly enter an aquatic habitat with bright, red lights around it, it is already too late.

Younsui.Pokedex Entry: It has been told to grant eternal youth to those that sip from its tub. It typically resides in warm seas, hidden away in a deep chasm.

Swashbeak.Pokedex Entry: They are able swim, dive, and fly as fast as a jet. They always have Flapscal fight battles for them when they are around, but do not be fooled, they are able to hit as hard as a semi-truck.

Nerisine.Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are said to be the cause of shipwrecks, as their beautiful singing usually lead captains off course. Their singing is said to cause migraines and slight infatuation.

Drizlil.Pokedex Entry: Groups of them dance around ponds in order to bring rain during droughts. They use their tails as whips to discipline others during their dance training.

Pourshang.Pokedex Entry: When there was a region-wise drought, this Pokemon's dance was able to bring a downpour that lasted an entire week. They train extensively to get their dances in order.

Maridica.Pokedex Entry: Maridica thrive in small lakes and swamps, making small homes out of the rocks and sticks that are around. When they find prey, they grab them in their jaws and claw at them viciously, tearing them apart.
